</div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#767-769">Source</a><a href="#impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;T, U&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html" title="trait core::convert::Into">Into</a>&lt;U&gt; for T<div class="where">where

<p>That is, this conversion is whatever the implementation of
<code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt; for U</code> chooses to do.</p>

class="width-limiter"><section id="main-content" class="content"><div class="main-heading"><div class="rustdoc-breadcrumbs"><a href="../index.html">device_kit</a>::<wbr><a href="index.html">button</a></div><h1>Enum <span class="enum">Pressed<wbr>To</span>&nbsp;<button id="copy-path" title="Copy item path to clipboard">Copy item path</button></h1><rustdoc-toolbar></rustdoc-toolbar><span class="sub-heading"><a class="src" href="../../src/device_kit/button.rs.html#28-40">Source</a> </span></div><pre class="rust item-decl"><code>pub enum PressedTo {
    Voltage,
    Ground,
}</code></pre><details class="toggle top-doc" open><summary class="hideme"><span>Expand description</span></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Describes how the button is physically wired.</p>
</div></details><h2 id="variants" class="variants section-header">Variants<a href="#variants" class="anchor">§</a></h2><div class="variants"><section id="variant.Voltage" class="variant"><a href="#variant.Voltage" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">Voltage</h3></section><div class="docblock"><p>Button connects pin to voltage (3.3V) when pressed.
Uses internal pull-down resistor. Pin reads HIGH when pressed.</p>
<p>Note: Pico 2 (RP2350) has a known silicon bug with pull-down resistors
that can cause pins to stay HIGH after button release. Use ToGround instead.</p>
</div><section id="variant.Ground" class="variant"><a href="#variant.Ground" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">Ground</h3></section><div class="docblock"><p>Button connects pin to ground (GND) when pressed.
Uses internal pull-up resistor. Pin reads LOW when pressed.
Recommended for Pico 2 due to pull-down resistor bug.</p>
</div></div><h2 id="trait-implementations" class="section-header">Trait Implementations<a href="#trait-implementations" class="anchor">§</a></h2><div id="trait-implementations-list"><details </div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#767-769">Source</a><a href="#impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;T, U&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html" title="trait core::convert::Into">Into</a>&lt;U&gt; for T<div class="where">where

<p>That is, this conversion is whatever the implementation of
<code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt; for U</code> chooses to do.</p>

id="rustdoc-modnav"><h2><a href="index.html">In device_<wbr>kit::<wbr>button</a></h2></div></div></nav><div class="sidebar-resizer" title="Drag to resize sidebar"></div><main><div class="width-limiter"><section id="main-content" class="content"><div class="main-heading"><div class="rustdoc-breadcrumbs"><a href="../index.html">device_kit</a>::<wbr><a href="index.html">button</a></div><h1>Struct <span class="struct">Button</span>&nbsp;<button id="copy-path" title="Copy item path to clipboard">Copy item path</button></h1><rustdoc-toolbar></rustdoc-toolbar><span class="sub-heading"><a class="src" href="../../src/device_kit/button.rs.html#103-106">Source</a> </span></div><pre class="rust item-decl"><code>pub struct Button&lt;'a&gt; { <span class="comment">/* private fields */</span> }</code></pre><details class="toggle top-doc" open><summary class="hideme"><span>Expand description</span></summary><div class="docblock"><p>A device abstraction for a button with debouncing and press duration detection.</p>
<h2 id="hardware-requirements"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#hardware-requirements">§</a>Hardware Requirements</h2>
<p>The button can be wired in two ways:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="enum.PressedTo.html#variant.Voltage" title="variant device_kit::button::PressedTo::Voltage"><code>PressedTo::Voltage</code></a>: Button connects pin to 3.3V when pressed (uses pull-down)</li>
<li><a href="enum.PressedTo.html#variant.Ground" title="variant device_kit::button::PressedTo::Ground"><code>PressedTo::Ground</code></a>: Button connects pin to GND when pressed (uses pull-up)</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Important</strong>: Pico 2 (RP2350) has a known silicon bug with pull-down resistors.
Use <a href="enum.PressedTo.html#variant.Ground" title="variant device_kit::button::PressedTo::Ground"><code>PressedTo::Ground</code></a> for Pico 2.</p>
<h2 id="usage"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#usage">§</a>Usage</h2>
<p>The <a href="struct.Button.html#method.wait_for_press_duration" title="method device_kit::button::Button::wait_for_press_duration"><code>wait_for_press_duration()</code></a> method returns as soon as it determines
whether the press is short or long, without waiting for the button to be released.
This allows for responsive UI feedback.</p>
<p>If you only need to detect when the button is pressed without measuring duration,
use <a href="struct.Button.html#method.wait_for_press" title="method device_kit::button::Button::wait_for_press"><code>wait_for_press()</code></a> instead.</p>
<h2 id="example"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#example">§</a>Example</h2>
<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code>
<span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::button::{Button, PressDuration, PressedTo};

<span class="kw">async fn </span>example(p: embassy_rp::Peripherals) {
    <span class="kw">let </span><span class="kw-2">mut </span>button = Button::new(p.PIN_15, PressedTo::Ground);

    <span class="comment">// Measure press durations in a loop
    </span><span class="kw">loop </span>{
        <span class="kw">match </span>button.wait_for_press_duration().<span class="kw">await </span>{
            PressDuration::Short =&gt; {
                <span class="comment">// Handle short press
            </span>}
            PressDuration::Long =&gt; {
                <span class="comment">// Handle long press (fires before button is released)
            </span>}
        }
    }
}</code></pre></div></div></details><h2 id="implementations" class="section-header">Implementations<a href="#implementations" class="anchor">§</a></h2><div id="implementations-list"><details class="toggle implementors-toggle" open><summary><section id="impl-Button%3C'a%3E" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/button.rs.html#108-191">Source</a><a href="#impl-Button%3C'a%3E" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;'a&gt; <a class="struct" href="struct.Button.html" title="struct device_kit::button::Button">Button</a>&lt;'a&gt;</h3></section></summary><div class="impl-items"><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.new" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/button.rs.html#115-124">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub fn <a href="#method.new" class="fn">new</a>&lt;P: Pin&gt;(pin: Peri&lt;'a, P&gt;, pressed_to: <a class="enum" href="enum.PressedTo.html" title="enum device_kit::button::PressedTo">PressedTo</a>) -&gt; Self</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Creates a new <code>Button</code> instance from a pin.</p>
<p>The pin is configured based on the connection type:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="enum.PressedTo.html#variant.Voltage" title="variant device_kit::button::PressedTo::Voltage"><code>PressedTo::Voltage</code></a>: Uses internal pull-down (button to 3.3V)</li>
<li><a href="enum.PressedTo.html#variant.Ground" title="variant device_kit::button::PressedTo::Ground"><code>PressedTo::Ground</code></a>: Uses internal pull-up (button to GND)</li>
</ul>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.is_pressed" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/button.rs.html#128-133">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub fn <a href="#method.is_pressed" class="fn">is_pressed</a>(&amp;self) -&gt; <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.bool.html">bool</a></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Returns whether the button is currently pressed.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.wait_for_press_duration" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/button.rs.html#165-177">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub async fn <a href="#method.wait_for_press_duration" class="fn">wait_for_press_duration</a>(&amp;mut self) -&gt; <a class="enum" href="enum.PressDuration.html" title="enum device_kit::button::PressDuration">PressDuration</a></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Measures the duration of a button press.</p>
<p>This method does not wait for the button to be released. It only waits
as long as necessary to determine whether the press was “short” or “long”.</p>
<p>See also: <a href="struct.Button.html#method.wait_for_press" title="method device_kit::button::Button::wait_for_press"><code>wait_for_press()</code></a> for simple press detection.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.wait_for_press" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/button.rs.html#187-190">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub async fn <a href="#method.wait_for_press" class="fn">wait_for_press</a>(&amp;mut self) -&gt; &amp;mut Self</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Waits for the button to be pressed.</p>
<p>This method returns immediately when the button press is detected,
without waiting for release or measuring duration.</p>
<p>Use this when you only need to detect button presses. If you need to
distinguish between short and long presses, use <a href="struct.Button.html#method.wait_for_press_duration" title="method device_kit::button::Button::wait_for_press_duration"><code>wait_for_press_duration()</code></a> instead.</p>
</div></details></div></details></div><h2 id="synthetic-implementations" class="section-header">Auto Trait Implementations<a href="#synthetic-implementations" class="anchor">§</a></h2><div id="synthetic-implementations-list"><section id="impl-Freeze-for-Button%3C'a%3E" class="impl"><a href="#impl-Freeze-for-Button%3C'a%3E" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;'a&gt; }</code></pre><details class="toggle top-doc" open><summary class="hideme"><span>Expand description</span></summary><div class="docblock"><p>A device abstraction for an HD44780-compatible character LCD.</p>

<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::char_lcd::{CharLcd, CharLcdStatic};

<span class="kw">async fn </span>example(
    p: embassy_rp::Peripherals,
    spawner: embassy_executor::Spawner,
) -&gt; device_kit::Result&lt;()&gt; {
    <span class="kw">static </span>CHAR_LCD_STATIC: CharLcdStatic = CharLcd::new_static();
    <span class="kw">let </span>lcd = CharLcd::new(<span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>CHAR_LCD_STATIC, p.I2C0, p.PIN_1, p.PIN_0, spawner)<span class="question-mark">?</span>;
    <span class="kw">let </span><span class="kw-2">mut </span>text: heapless::String&lt;<span class="number">64</span>&gt; = <span class="string">"Hello!"</span>.try_into().unwrap();
    lcd.write_text(text, <span class="number">1_000</span>).<span class="kw">await</span>;
    <span class="prelude-val">Ok</span>(())
}</code></pre></div></div></details><h2 id="implementations" class="section-header">Implementations<a href="#implementations" class="anchor">§</a></h2><div id="implementations-list"><details class="toggle implementors-toggle" open><summary><section id="impl-CharLcd" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/char_lcd.rs.html#66-101">Source</a><a href="#impl-CharLcd" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl <a class="struct" href="struct.CharLcd.html" title="struct device_kit::char_lcd::CharLcd">CharLcd</a></h3></section></summary><div class="impl-items"><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.new_static" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/char_lcd.rs.html#69-71">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.new_static" class="fn">new_static</a>() -&gt; <a class="struct" href="struct.CharLcdStatic.html" title="struct device_kit::char_lcd::CharLcdStatic">CharLcdStatic</a></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Create CharLcd resources</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.new" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/char_lcd.rs.html#77-93">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub fn <a href="#method.new" class="fn">new</a>&lt;SCL, SDA&gt;(
    char_lcd_static: &amp;'static <a class="struct" href="struct.CharLcdStatic.html" title="struct device_kit::char_lcd::CharLcdStatic">CharLcdStatic</a>,
    i2c_peripheral: Peri&lt;'static, I2C0&gt;,
    scl: Peri&lt;'static, SCL&gt;,
    sda: Peri&lt;'static, SDA&gt;,
    spawner: Spawner,
) -&gt; <a class="type" href="../type.Result.html" title="type device_kit::Result">Result</a>&lt;Self&gt;<div class="where">where
    SCL: SclPin&lt;I2C0&gt;,
    SDA: SdaPin&lt;I2C0&gt;,</div></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Create a new CharLcd device</p>
<p>Note: Hardcoded to I2C0 peripheral (like WiFi’s internal pins).
However, SCL and SDA can be any pins compatible with I2C0.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.write_text" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/char_lcd.rs.html#96-100">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub async fn <a href="#method.write_text" class="fn">write_text</a>(&amp;self, text: String&lt;64&gt;, duration_ms: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.u32.html">u32</a>)</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Send a message to the LCD (async, waits until queued)</p>

<p>That is, this conversion is whatever the implementation of
<code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt; for U</code> chooses to do.</p>

<p>That is, this conversion is whatever the implementation of
<code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt; for U</code> chooses to do.</p>

to clipboard">Copy item path</button></h1><rustdoc-toolbar></rustdoc-toolbar><span class="sub-heading"><a class="src" href="../../src/device_kit/clock.rs.html#1-411">Source</a> </span></div><details class="toggle top-doc" open><summary class="hideme"><span>Expand description</span></summary><div class="docblock"><p>A device abstraction that manages timekeeping and emits tick events.</p>
<p>The clock is headless: it uses the monotonic timer only—no external peripherals required—so
it can run in tests or alongside other devices without owning hardware.</p>
<p>See <a href="struct.Clock.html" title="struct device_kit::clock::Clock"><code>Clock</code></a> for usage and examples.</p>
</div></details><h2 id="structs" class="section-header">Structs<a href="#structs" class="anchor">§</a></h2><dl class="item-table"><dt><a class="struct" href="struct.Clock.html" title="struct device_kit::clock::Clock">Clock</a></dt><dd>A device abstraction that manages time keeping and emits time tick events.</dd><dt><a class="struct" href="struct.ClockStatic.html" title="struct device_kit::clock::ClockStatic">Clock<wbr>Static</a></dt><dd>Resources needed by Clock device</dd></dl><h2 id="constants" class="section-header">Constants<a href="#constants" class="anchor">§</a></h2><dl class="item-table"><dt><a class="constant" href="constant.ONE_DAY.html" title="constant device_kit::clock::ONE_DAY">ONE_DAY</a></dt><dd>Duration representing one day (24 hours).</dd><dt><a class="constant" href="constant.ONE_HOUR.html" title="constant device_kit::clock::ONE_HOUR">ONE_<wbr>HOUR</a></dt><dd>Duration representing one hour (60 minutes).</dd><dt><a class="constant" href="constant.ONE_MINUTE.html" title="constant device_kit::clock::ONE_MINUTE">ONE_<wbr>MINUTE</a></dt><dd>Duration representing one minute (60 seconds).</dd><dt><a class="constant" href="constant.ONE_SECOND.html" title="constant device_kit::clock::ONE_SECOND">ONE_<wbr>SECOND</a></dt><dd>Duration representing one second.</dd></dl><h2 id="functions" class="section-header">Functions<a href="#functions" class="anchor">§</a></h2><dl class="item-table"><dt><a class="fn" href="fn.h12_m_s.html" title="fn device_kit::clock::h12_m_s">h12_m_s</a></dt><dd>Extract hour (12-hour format), minute, second from OffsetDateTime</dd></dl></section></div></main></body></html>

href="#impl-SaturatingAs-for-T" title="SaturatingAs">SaturatingAs</a></li><li><a href="#impl-SaturatingCastFrom%3CSrc%3E-for-Dst" title="SaturatingCastFrom&#60;Src&#62;">SaturatingCastFrom&#60;Src&#62;</a></li><li><a href="#impl-TryFrom%3CU%3E-for-T" title="TryFrom&#60;U&#62;">TryFrom&#60;U&#62;</a></li><li><a href="#impl-TryInto%3CU%3E-for-T" title="TryInto&#60;U&#62;">TryInto&#60;U&#62;</a></li><li><a href="#impl-UnwrappedAs-for-T" title="UnwrappedAs">UnwrappedAs</a></li><li><a href="#impl-UnwrappedCastFrom%3CSrc%3E-for-Dst" title="UnwrappedCastFrom&#60;Src&#62;">UnwrappedCastFrom&#60;Src&#62;</a></li><li><a href="#impl-WrappingAs-for-T" title="WrappingAs">WrappingAs</a></li><li><a href="#impl-WrappingCastFrom%3CSrc%3E-for-Dst" title="WrappingCastFrom&#60;Src&#62;">WrappingCastFrom&#60;Src&#62;</a></li></ul></section><div id="rustdoc-modnav"><h2><a href="index.html">In device_<wbr>kit::<wbr>clock</a></h2></div></div></nav><div class="sidebar-resizer" title="Drag to resize sidebar"></div><main><div class="width-limiter"><section id="main-content" class="content"><div class="main-heading"><div class="rustdoc-breadcrumbs"><a href="../index.html">device_kit</a>::<wbr><a href="index.html">clock</a></div><h1>Struct <span class="struct">Clock</span>&nbsp;<button id="copy-path" title="Copy item path to clipboard">Copy item path</button></h1><rustdoc-toolbar></rustdoc-toolbar><span class="sub-heading"><a class="src" href="../../src/device_kit/clock.rs.html#144-152">Source</a> </span></div><pre class="rust item-decl"><code>pub struct Clock { <span class="comment">/* private fields */</span> }</code></pre><details class="toggle top-doc" open><summary class="hideme"><span>Expand description</span></summary><div class="docblock"><p>A device abstraction that manages time keeping and emits time tick events.</p>
<p>Pass <code>Some(duration)</code> to enable periodic ticks aligned to that interval; use <code>None</code> to emit
ticks only when time/offset changes. The clock is headless (no hardware ownership) and
supports time scaling for demos/tests via <a href="struct.Clock.html#method.set_speed" title="method device_kit::clock::Clock::set_speed"><code>Clock::set_speed</code></a>.</p>
<h2 id="examples"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#examples">§</a>Examples</h2>
<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::clock::{Clock, ClockStatic, ONE_SECOND, h12_m_s};
<span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::time_sync::UnixSeconds;

<span class="kw">async fn </span>run_clock(spawner: embassy_executor::Spawner) {
    <span class="kw">static </span>CLOCK_STATIC: ClockStatic = Clock::new_static();
    <span class="kw">let </span>clock = Clock::new(<span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>CLOCK_STATIC, -<span class="number">420</span>, <span class="prelude-val">Some</span>(ONE_SECOND), spawner); <span class="comment">// PDT offset (UTC-7)

    </span><span class="kw">let </span>current_utc_time = UnixSeconds(<span class="number">1_763_647_200</span>); <span class="comment">// 2025-11-20 14:00:00 UTC
    </span>clock.set_utc_time(current_utc_time).<span class="kw">await</span>;

    <span class="kw">let </span>now_local = clock.now_local();
    <span class="kw">let </span>(hour12, minute, second) = h12_m_s(<span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>now_local);
    <span class="macro">defmt::info!</span>(<span class="string">"Local time: {:02}:{:02}:{:02} PDT"</span>, hour12, minute, second);
    <span class="comment">// Logs: Local time: 07:00:00 PDT

    </span>clock.set_offset_minutes(-<span class="number">480</span>).<span class="kw">await</span>; <span class="comment">// Switch to PST (UTC-8)
    </span><span class="kw">let </span>(hour12, minute, second) = h12_m_s(<span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>clock.now_local());
    <span class="macro">defmt::info!</span>(<span class="string">"Local time: {:02}:{:02}:{:02} PST"</span>, hour12, minute, second);
    <span class="comment">// Logs: Local time: 06:00:00 PST

    </span><span class="kw">loop </span>{
        <span class="kw">let </span>tick = clock.wait_for_tick().<span class="kw">await</span>;
        <span class="kw">let </span>(hour12, minute, second) = h12_m_s(<span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>tick);
        <span class="macro">defmt::info!</span>(<span class="string">"Tick: {:02}:{:02}:{:02}"</span>, hour12, minute, second);
        <span class="comment">// Logs: Tick: 06:00:01, Tick: 06:00:02, ...
    </span>}
}</code></pre></div></div></details><h2 id="implementations" class="section-header">Implementations<a href="#implementations" class="anchor">§</a></h2><div id="implementations-list"><details class="toggle implementors-toggle" open><summary><section id="impl-Clock" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/clock.rs.html#154-329">Source</a><a href="#impl-Clock" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl <a class="struct" href="struct.Clock.html" title="struct device_kit::clock::Clock">Clock</a></h3></section></summary><div class="impl-items"><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.new_static" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/clock.rs.html#157-167">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.new_static" class="fn">new_static</a>() -&gt; <a class="struct" href="struct.ClockStatic.html" title="struct device_kit::clock::ClockStatic">ClockStatic</a></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Create Clock resources</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.new" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/clock.rs.html#170-188">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub fn <a href="#method.new" class="fn">new</a>(
    clock_static: &amp;'static <a class="struct" href="struct.ClockStatic.html" title="struct device_kit::clock::ClockStatic">ClockStatic</a>,
    offset_minutes: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.i32.html">i32</a>,
    tick_interval: <a class="enum" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/option/enum.Option.html" title="enum core::option::Option">Option</a>&lt;Duration&gt;,
    spawner: Spawner,
) -&gt; Self</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Create a new Clock device and spawn its task. See <a href="struct.Clock.html" title="struct device_kit::clock::Clock"><code>Clock</code></a> docs for a full example.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.wait_for_tick" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/clock.rs.html#193-196">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub async fn <a href="#method.wait_for_tick" class="fn">wait_for_tick</a>(&amp;self) -&gt; OffsetDateTime</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Wait for and return the next clock tick event. If constructed with <code>None</code> tick interval,
ticks occur only when time or offset changes. Passing <code>Some(duration)</code> enables periodic
ticks aligned to that interval. See <a href="struct.Clock.html" title="struct device_kit::clock::Clock"><code>Clock</code></a> for usage.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.now_local" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/clock.rs.html#200-239">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub fn <a href="#method.now_local" class="fn">now_local</a>(&amp;self) -&gt; OffsetDateTime</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Get the current local time (offset already applied) without waiting for a tick.
Computed from atomics + <code>Instant::now()</code> - no async needed.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.set_utc_time" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/clock.rs.html#242-253">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub async fn <a href="#method.set_utc_time" class="fn">set_utc_time</a>(&amp;self, unix_seconds: <a class="struct" href="../time_sync/struct.UnixSeconds.html" title="struct device_kit::time_sync::UnixSeconds">UnixSeconds</a>)</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Set the current UTC time. See <a href="struct.Clock.html" title="struct device_kit::clock::Clock"><code>Clock</code></a> docs for usage.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.set_offset_minutes" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/clock.rs.html#256-266">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub async fn <a href="#method.set_offset_minutes" class="fn">set_offset_minutes</a>(&amp;self, minutes: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.i32.html">i32</a>)</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Update the UTC offset used for subsequent <a href="struct.Clock.html#method.now_local" title="method device_kit::clock::Clock::now_local"><code>now_local</code></a> results and tick events.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.offset_minutes" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/clock.rs.html#269-271">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub fn <a href="#method.offset_minutes" class="fn">offset_minutes</a>(&amp;self) -&gt; <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.i32.html">i32</a></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Get the current UTC offset in minutes.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.set_tick_interval" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/clock.rs.html#275-286">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub async fn <a href="#method.set_tick_interval" class="fn">set_tick_interval</a>(&amp;self, interval: <a class="enum" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/option/enum.Option.html" title="enum core::option::Option">Option</a>&lt;Duration&gt;)</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Set the tick interval (e.g., <code>Some(ONE_SECOND)</code>, <code>Some(ONE_MINUTE)</code>, <code>Some(ONE_HOUR)</code>).
Use <code>None</code> to disable periodic ticks (only emit on time/offset changes). See <a href="struct.Clock.html" title="struct device_kit::clock::Clock"><code>Clock</code></a>.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.set_speed" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/clock.rs.html#295-328">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub async fn <a href="#method.set_speed" class="fn">set_speed</a>(&amp;self, speed_multiplier: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.f32.html">f32</a>)</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Update the speed multiplier (1.0 = real time). Changing speed resets the base time to
the current real time so returning to 1.0 resumes the correct clock.</p>
<p>Internally this stores real wall-clock ticks (<code>Instant::now</code>) and a base Unix timestamp
in microseconds. When you speed up (e.g., <code>2.0</code>), elapsed real ticks are scaled before
converting back to Unix time; when you slow down (e.g., <code>0.5</code>), they are scaled down.
Useful for fast-forwarding demos or accelerating tests without sleeping in real time.</p>
</div></details></div></details></div><h2 id="synthetic-implementations" class="section-header">Auto Trait Implementations<a href="#synthetic-implementations" class="anchor">§</a></h2><div </div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#767-769">Source</a><a href="#impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;T, U&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html" title="trait core::convert::Into">Into</a>&lt;U&gt; for T<div class="where">where
    U: <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt;,</div></h3></section></summary><div class="impl-items"><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.into" class="method trait-impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#777">Source</a><a href="#method.into" class="anchor">§</a><h4 class="code-header">fn <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html#tymethod.into" class="fn">into</a>(self) -&gt; U</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Calls <code>U::from(self)</code>.</p>
<p>That is, this conversion is whatever the implementation of
<code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt; for U</code> chooses to do.</p>

</div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#767-769">Source</a><a href="#impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;T, U&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html" title="trait core::convert::Into">Into</a>&lt;U&gt; for T<div class="where">where
    U: <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt;,</div></h3></section></summary><div class="impl-items"><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.into" class="method trait-impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#777">Source</a><a href="#method.into" class="anchor">§</a><h4 class="code-header">fn <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html#tymethod.into" class="fn">into</a>(self) -&gt; U</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Calls <code>U::from(self)</code>.</p>
<p>That is, this conversion is whatever the implementation of
<code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt; for U</code> chooses to do.</p>

</div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#767-769">Source</a><a href="#impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;T, U&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html" title="trait core::convert::Into">Into</a>&lt;U&gt; for T<div class="where">where

<p>That is, this conversion is whatever the implementation of
<code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt; for U</code> chooses to do.</p>

class="sidebar-resizer" title="Drag to resize sidebar"></div><main><div class="width-limiter"><section id="main-content" class="content"><div class="main-heading"><div class="rustdoc-breadcrumbs"><a href="../index.html">device_kit</a></div><h1>Module <span>flash_<wbr>array</span>&nbsp;<button id="copy-path" title="Copy item path to clipboard">Copy item path</button></h1><rustdoc-toolbar></rustdoc-toolbar><span class="sub-heading"><a class="src" href="../../src/device_kit/flash_array.rs.html#1-396">Source</a> </span></div><details class="toggle top-doc" open><summary class="hideme"><span>Expand description</span></summary><div class="docblock"><p>A device abstraction for type-safe persistent storage in flash memory.</p>
<p>This module provides a generic flash block storage system that allows storing any
<code>serde</code>-compatible type in Raspberry Pi Pico’s internal flash memory using postcard
serialization.</p>
<h2 id="features"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#features">§</a>Features</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>“Type safety”</strong>: Uses whiteboard semantics—any data left over from other types or
past runs is treated as empty from the current type’s perspective. Reading with a
different type than what was saved returns <code>None</code> (type hash mismatch).</li>
<li><strong>Postcard serialization</strong>: Compact, no_std-compatible binary format</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="block-allocation"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#block-allocation">§</a>Block Allocation</h2>
<p>Conceptually, flash is treated as an array of fixed-size erase blocks counted from the end of
memory backwards. Code can carve out disjoint partitions at compile time (similar to using
<code>split_at_mut</code> on slices) and hand those partitions to subsystems that need persistent storage.</p>
<p>⚠️ <strong>Warning</strong>: The RP2040 stores firmware, vector tables, and user data in the same flash
device. Only request block handles from regions you have explicitly reserved for storage.
Writing to an arbitrary block can erase the running program and leave the device unbootable.</p>
<p><strong>Important</strong>: Users are responsible for avoiding block_id collisions. Using the same
block_id for different types will cause type hash mismatches and return <code>None</code> on reads.</p>
<p>See <a href="struct.FlashArray.html" title="struct device_kit::flash_array::FlashArray"><code>FlashArray</code></a> for usage examples.</p>
</div></details><h2 id="structs" class="section-header">Structs<a href="#structs" class="anchor">§</a></h2><dl class="item-table"><dt><a class="struct" href="struct.FlashArray.html" title="struct device_kit::flash_array::FlashArray">Flash<wbr>Array</a></dt><dd>A device abstraction for type-safe persistent storage in flash memory.</dd><dt><a class="struct" href="struct.FlashArrayStatic.html" title="struct device_kit::flash_array::FlashArrayStatic">Flash<wbr>Array<wbr>Static</a></dt><dd>Static type for constructing flash arrays.</dd><dt><a class="struct" href="struct.FlashBlock.html" title="struct device_kit::flash_array::FlashBlock">Flash<wbr>Block</a></dt><dd>Handle to a single flash erase block.</dd></dl></section></div></main></body></html>

device_<wbr>kit::<wbr>flash_<wbr>array</a></h2></div></div></nav><div class="sidebar-resizer" title="Drag to resize sidebar"></div><main><div class="width-limiter"><section id="main-content" class="content"><div class="main-heading"><div class="rustdoc-breadcrumbs"><a href="../index.html">device_kit</a>::<wbr><a href="index.html">flash_array</a></div><h1>Struct <span class="struct">Flash<wbr>Array</span>&nbsp;<button id="copy-path" title="Copy item path to clipboard">Copy item path</button></h1><rustdoc-toolbar></rustdoc-toolbar><span class="sub-heading"><a class="src" href="../../src/device_kit/flash_array.rs.html#233">Source</a> </span></div><pre class="rust item-decl"><code>pub struct FlashArray&lt;const N: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.usize.html">usize</a>&gt;;</code></pre><details class="toggle top-doc" open><summary class="hideme"><span>Expand description</span></summary><div class="docblock"><p>A device abstraction for type-safe persistent storage in flash memory.</p>
<p>This provides type-safe persistent storage using postcard serialization with whiteboard
semantics—reading with a different type than what was saved returns <code>None</code>. Rather than
manually juggling partitions, you reserve a contiguous prefix of flash blocks (0..N-1) and
destructure the returned array however you like.</p>
<h2 id="examples"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#examples">§</a>Examples</h2><h3 id="storing-custom-device-configuration"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#storing-custom-device-configuration">§</a>Storing custom device configuration</h3>
<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::flash_array::{FlashArray, FlashArrayStatic};

<span class="comment">// Define your configuration type
</span><span class="attr">#[derive(serde::Serialize, serde::Deserialize, Debug, Default)]
</span><span class="kw">struct </span>DeviceConfig {
    brightness: u8,
    timezone_offset: i16,
    display_mode: u8,
}

<span class="kw">async fn </span>example(p: embassy_rp::Peripherals) -&gt; device_kit::Result&lt;()&gt; {
    <span class="kw">static </span>FLASH_STATIC: FlashArrayStatic = FlashArray::&lt;<span class="number">1</span>&gt;::new_static();
    <span class="kw">let </span>[<span class="kw-2">mut </span>device_config_block] = FlashArray::new(<span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>FLASH_STATIC, p.FLASH)<span class="question-mark">?</span>;

    <span class="comment">// Load existing config if present.
    </span><span class="kw">let </span><span class="kw-2">mut </span>device_config: DeviceConfig = device_config_block
        .load()<span class="question-mark">?
        </span>.unwrap_or_default();

    <span class="comment">// Modify and save
    </span>device_config.brightness = <span class="number">255</span>;
    device_config_block.save(<span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>device_config)<span class="question-mark">?</span>;

    <span class="comment">// Can also clear storage with: device_config_block.clear()?;
    </span><span class="prelude-val">Ok</span>(())
}</code></pre></div><h3 id="whiteboard-semantics-demonstration"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#whiteboard-semantics-demonstration">§</a>Whiteboard semantics demonstration</h3>
<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::flash_array::{FlashArray, FlashArrayStatic};
<span class="kw">async fn </span>example() -&gt; device_kit::Result&lt;()&gt; {
    <span class="kw">let </span>p = embassy_rp::init(Default::default());
    <span class="kw">static </span>FLASH_STATIC: FlashArrayStatic = FlashArray::&lt;<span class="number">1</span>&gt;::new_static();
    <span class="kw">let </span>[<span class="kw-2">mut </span>string_block] = FlashArray::new(<span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>FLASH_STATIC, p.FLASH)<span class="question-mark">?</span>;
    string_block.save(<span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>heapless::String::&lt;<span class="number">64</span>&gt;::try_from(<span class="string">"Hello"</span>)<span class="question-mark">?</span>)<span class="question-mark">?</span>;

    <span class="comment">// Reading with a different type returns None (whiteboard semantics)
    </span><span class="kw">let </span>result: <span class="prelude-ty">Option</span>&lt;u64&gt; = string_block.load()<span class="question-mark">?</span>;
    <span class="macro">assert!</span>(result.is_none());  <span class="comment">// Different type (u64 vs String&lt;64&gt;)!
    </span><span class="prelude-val">Ok</span>(())
}</code></pre></div>
<p>Marker type used as a namespace for creating flash-backed arrays of length <code>N</code>.</p>
</div></details><h2 id="implementations" class="section-header">Implementations<a href="#implementations" class="anchor">§</a></h2><div id="implementations-list"><details class="toggle implementors-toggle" open><summary><section id="impl-FlashArray%3CN%3E" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/flash_array.rs.html#235-251">Source</a><a href="#impl-FlashArray%3CN%3E" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;const N: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.usize.html">usize</a>&gt; <a class="struct" href="struct.FlashArray.html" title="struct device_kit::flash_array::FlashArray">FlashArray</a>&lt;N&gt;</h3></section></summary><div class="impl-items"><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.new_static" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/flash_array.rs.html#238-240">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.new_static" class="fn">new_static</a>() -&gt; <a class="struct" href="struct.FlashArrayStatic.html" title="struct device_kit::flash_array::FlashArrayStatic">FlashArrayStatic</a></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Get static resources for creating flash arrays.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.new" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/flash_array.rs.html#244-250">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub fn <a href="#method.new" class="fn">new</a>(
    flash_static: &amp;'static <a class="struct" href="struct.FlashArrayStatic.html" title="struct device_kit::flash_array::FlashArrayStatic">FlashArrayStatic</a>,
    peripheral: Peri&lt;'static, FLASH&gt;,
) -&gt; <a class="type" href="../type.Result.html" title="type device_kit::Result">Result</a>&lt;[<a class="struct" href="struct.FlashBlock.html" title="struct device_kit::flash_array::FlashBlock">FlashBlock</a>; <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.array.html">N</a>]&gt;</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Reserve <code>N</code> contiguous blocks (starting from block 0 on the first call) and return them as
an array that you can destructure however you like.</p>

</div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#767-769">Source</a><a href="#impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;T, U&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html" title="trait core::convert::Into">Into</a>&lt;U&gt; for T<div class="where">where
    U: <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt;,</div></h3></section></summary><div class="impl-items"><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.into" class="method trait-impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#777">Source</a><a href="#method.into" class="anchor">§</a><h4 class="code-header">fn <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html#tymethod.into" class="fn">into</a>(self) -&gt; U</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Calls <code>U::from(self)</code>.</p>
<p>That is, this conversion is whatever the implementation of
<code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt; for U</code> chooses to do.</p>

</div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#767-769">Source</a><a href="#impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;T, U&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html" title="trait core::convert::Into">Into</a>&lt;U&gt; for T<div class="where">where

<p>That is, this conversion is whatever the implementation of
<code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt; for U</code> chooses to do.</p>

</div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#767-769">Source</a><a href="#impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;T, U&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html" title="trait core::convert::Into">Into</a>&lt;U&gt; for T<div class="where">where

<p>That is, this conversion is whatever the implementation of
<code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt; for U</code> chooses to do.</p>

description</span></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Device abstractions for peripherals for Pico 1 and 2 (with and without WiFi).</p>
<h2 id="glossary"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#glossary">§</a>Glossary</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>PIO (Programmable I/O):</strong> Pico 1 has 2. Pico 2 has 3.</li>
<li><strong>DMA (Direct Memory Access):</strong> Both Pico1 and 2 have 12 channels.</li>
</ul>
</div></details><h2 id="modules" class="section-header">Modules<a href="#modules" class="anchor">§</a></h2><dl class="item-table"><dt><a class="mod" href="button/index.html" title="mod device_kit::button">button</a></dt><dd>A device abstraction for buttons with debouncing and press duration detection.</dd><dt><a class="mod" href="char_lcd/index.html" title="mod device_kit::char_lcd">char_<wbr>lcd</a></dt><dd>A device abstraction for HD44780-compatible character LCDs (e.g., 16x2, 20x2, 20x4).</dd><dt><a class="mod" href="clock/index.html" title="mod device_kit::clock">clock</a></dt><dd>A device abstraction that manages timekeeping and emits tick events.</dd><dt><a class="mod" href="flash_array/index.html" title="mod device_kit::flash_array">flash_<wbr>array</a></dt><dd>A device abstraction for type-safe persistent storage in flash memory.</dd><dt><a class="mod" href="ir/index.html" title="mod device_kit::ir">ir</a></dt><dd>A device abstraction for infrared receivers using the NEC protocol.</dd><dt><a class="mod" href="ir_kepler/index.html" title="mod device_kit::ir_kepler">ir_<wbr>kepler</a></dt><dd>A device abstraction for the SunFounder Kepler Kit IR remote control.</dd><dt><a class="mod" href="ir_mapping/index.html" title="mod device_kit::ir_mapping">ir_<wbr>mapping</a></dt><dd>A device abstraction for mapping IR remote buttons to application-specific actions.</dd><dt><a class="mod" href="led4/index.html" title="mod device_kit::led4">led4</a></dt><dd>A device abstraction for a 4-digit, 7-segment LED display for text with optional animation and blinking.</dd><dt><a class="mod" href="led2d/index.html" title="mod device_kit::led2d">led2d</a></dt><dd>A device abstraction for rectangular NeoPixel-style (WS2812) LED panel displays.
For 1-dimensional LED strips, see the <a href="led_strip/index.html" title="mod device_kit::led_strip"><code>led_strip</code></a> module.</dd><dt><a class="mod" href="led_strip/index.html" title="mod device_kit::led_strip">led_<wbr>strip</a></dt><dd>A device abstraction for 1-dimensional NeoPixel-style (WS2812) LED strips. For 2-dimensional
panels, see the <a href="led2d/index.html" title="mod device_kit::led2d"><code>led2d</code></a> module.</dd><dt><a class="mod" href="rfid/index.html" title="mod device_kit::rfid">rfid</a></dt><dd>A device abstraction for RFID readers using the MFRC522 chip.</dd><dt><a class="mod" href="servo/index.html" title="mod device_kit::servo">servo</a></dt><dd>A device abstraction for SG90 servo motors.</dd><dt><a class="mod" href="servo_animate/index.html" title="mod device_kit::servo_animate">servo_<wbr>animate</a></dt><dd>A device abstraction for animating a loop of servo actions.</dd><dt><a class="mod" href="time_sync/index.html" title="mod device_kit::time_sync">time_<wbr>sync</a></dt><dd>A device abstraction for Network Time Protocol (NTP) time synchronization over WiFi.</dd><dt><a class="mod" href="wifi/index.html" title="mod device_kit::wifi">wifi</a></dt><dd>A device abstraction for WiFi connectivity; see <a href="wifi_auto/struct.Wifi.html" title="struct device_kit::wifi_auto::Wifi"><code>Wifi</code></a> for details.</dd><dt><a class="mod" href="wifi_auto/index.html" title="mod device_kit::wifi_auto">wifi_<wbr>auto</a></dt><dd>A device abstraction for WiFi auto-provisioning with captive portal fallback.</dd></dl><h2 id="macros" class="section-header">Macros<a href="#macros" class="anchor">§</a></h2><dl class="item-table"><dt><a class="macro" href="macro.led2d.html" title="macro device_kit::led2d">led2d</a></dt><dd>Macro to generate an LED-panel struct type (includes syntax details). </div></details><h2 id="variants" class="variants section-header">Variants<a href="#variants" class="anchor">§</a></h2><div class="variants"><section id="variant.Press" class="variant"><a href="#variant.Press" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">Press</h3></section><div class="docblock"><p>Button press with 16-bit address and 8-bit command.
Supports both standard NEC (8-bit address) and extended NEC (16-bit address).</p>

</div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#767-769">Source</a><a href="#impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;T, U&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html" title="trait core::convert::Into">Into</a>&lt;U&gt; for T<div class="where">where

<p>That is, this conversion is whatever the implementation of
<code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt; for U</code> chooses to do.</p>

protocol.</p>
<h2 id="examples"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#examples">§</a>Examples</h2>
<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::ir::{Ir, IrEvent, IrStatic};

<span class="kw">async fn </span>example(
    p: embassy_rp::Peripherals,
    spawner: embassy_executor::Spawner,
) -&gt; device_kit::Result&lt;()&gt; {
    <span class="kw">static </span>IR_STATIC: IrStatic = Ir::new_static();
    <span class="kw">let </span>ir = Ir::new(<span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>IR_STATIC, p.PIN_15, spawner)<span class="question-mark">?</span>;

    <span class="kw">loop </span>{
        <span class="kw">let </span>IrEvent::Press { addr, cmd } = ir.wait_for_press().<span class="kw">await</span>;
        <span class="macro">defmt::info!</span>(<span class="string">"IR: addr=0x{:04X}, cmd=0x{:02X}"</span>, addr, cmd);
    }
}</code></pre></div></div></details><h2 id="implementations" class="section-header">Implementations<a href="#implementations" class="anchor">§</a></h2><div id="implementations-list"><details class="toggle implementors-toggle" open><summary><section id="impl-Ir%3C'_%3E" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/ir.rs.html#80-114">Source</a><a href="#impl-Ir%3C'_%3E" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl <a class="struct" href="struct.Ir.html" title="struct device_kit::ir::Ir">Ir</a>&lt;'_&gt;</h3></section></summary><div class="impl-items"><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.new_static" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/ir.rs.html#85-87">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.new_static" class="fn">new_static</a>() -&gt; <a class="struct" href="struct.IrStatic.html" title="struct device_kit::ir::IrStatic">IrStatic</a></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Create static channel resources for IR events.</p>
<p>See <a href="struct.Ir.html" title="struct device_kit::ir::Ir"><code>Ir</code></a> for usage examples.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.new" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/ir.rs.html#95-106">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub fn <a href="#method.new" class="fn">new</a>&lt;P: Pin&gt;(
    ir_static: &amp;'static <a class="struct" href="struct.IrStatic.html" title="struct device_kit::ir::IrStatic">IrStatic</a>,
    pin: Peri&lt;'static, P&gt;,
    spawner: Spawner,
) -&gt; <a class="type" href="../type.Result.html" title="type device_kit::Result">Result</a>&lt;Self&gt;</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Create a new IR receiver on the specified pin.</p>
<p>See <a href="struct.Ir.html" title="struct device_kit::ir::Ir"><code>Ir</code></a> for usage examples.</p>
<h5 id="errors"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#errors">§</a>Errors</h5>
<p>Returns an error if the background task cannot be spawned.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.wait_for_press" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/ir.rs.html#111-113">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub async fn <a href="#method.wait_for_press" class="fn">wait_for_press</a>(&amp;self) -&gt; <a class="enum" href="enum.IrEvent.html" title="enum device_kit::ir::IrEvent">IrEvent</a></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Wait for the next IR event.</p>
<p>See <a href="struct.Ir.html" title="struct device_kit::ir::Ir"><code>Ir</code></a> for usage examples.</p>

</div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#767-769">Source</a><a href="#impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;T, U&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html" title="trait core::convert::Into">Into</a>&lt;U&gt; for T<div class="where">where

<p>That is, this conversion is whatever the implementation of
<code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt; for U</code> chooses to do.</p>

</div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#767-769">Source</a><a href="#impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;T, U&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html" title="trait core::convert::Into">Into</a>&lt;U&gt; for T<div class="where">where

<p>That is, this conversion is whatever the implementation of
<code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt; for U</code> chooses to do.</p>

</div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#767-769">Source</a><a href="#impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;T, U&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html" title="trait core::convert::Into">Into</a>&lt;U&gt; for T<div class="where">where
    U: <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt;,</div></h3></section></summary><div class="impl-items"><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.into" class="method trait-impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#777">Source</a><a href="#method.into" class="anchor">§</a><h4 class="code-header">fn <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html#tymethod.into" class="fn">into</a>(self) -&gt; U</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Calls <code>U::from(self)</code>.</p>
<p>That is, this conversion is whatever the implementation of
<code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt; for U</code> chooses to do.</p>
</div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-LosslessTryInto%3CDst%3E-for-Src" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://docs.rs/fixed/~1.28/src/fixed/traits.rs.html#3660-3662">Source</a><a href="#impl-LosslessTryInto%3CDst%3E-for-Src" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;Src, Dst&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://docs.rs/fixed/~1.28/fixed/traits/trait.LosslessTryInto.html" title="trait fixed::traits::LosslessTryInto">LosslessTryInto</a>&lt;Dst&gt; for Src<div class="where">where

class="content"><div class="main-heading"><div class="rustdoc-breadcrumbs"><a href="../index.html">device_kit</a>::<wbr><a href="index.html">ir_kepler</a></div><h1>Struct <span class="struct">IrKepler</span>&nbsp;<button id="copy-path" title="Copy item path to clipboard">Copy item path</button></h1><rustdoc-toolbar></rustdoc-toolbar><span class="sub-heading"><a class="src" href="../../src/device_kit/ir_kepler.rs.html#107-109">Source</a> </span></div><pre class="rust item-decl"><code>pub struct IrKepler&lt;'a&gt; { <span class="comment">/* private fields */</span> }</code></pre><details class="toggle top-doc" open><summary class="hideme"><span>Expand description</span></summary><div class="docblock"><p>A device abstraction for the SunFounder Kepler Kit IR remote.</p>
<p>This provides a simple interface for the Kepler remote with built-in button mappings.</p>
<h2 id="examples"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#examples">§</a>Examples</h2>
<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::ir_kepler::{IrKepler, IrKeplerStatic};

<span class="kw">async fn </span>example(
    p: embassy_rp::Peripherals,
    spawner: embassy_executor::Spawner,
) -&gt; device_kit::Result&lt;()&gt; {
    <span class="kw">static </span>IR_KEPLER_STATIC: IrKeplerStatic = IrKepler::new_static();
    <span class="kw">let </span>ir_kepler = IrKepler::new(<span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>IR_KEPLER_STATIC, p.PIN_15, spawner)<span class="question-mark">?</span>;

    <span class="kw">loop </span>{
        <span class="kw">let </span>button = ir_kepler.wait_for_press().<span class="kw">await</span>;
        <span class="macro">defmt::info!</span>(<span class="string">"Button: {:?}"</span>, button);
    }
}</code></pre></div></div></details><h2 id="implementations" class="section-header">Implementations<a href="#implementations" class="anchor">§</a></h2><div id="implementations-list"><details class="toggle implementors-toggle" open><summary><section id="impl-IrKepler%3C'a%3E" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/ir_kepler.rs.html#111-148">Source</a><a href="#impl-IrKepler%3C'a%3E" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;'a&gt; <a class="struct" href="struct.IrKepler.html" title="struct device_kit::ir_kepler::IrKepler">IrKepler</a>&lt;'a&gt;</h3></section></summary><div class="impl-items"><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.new_static" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/ir_kepler.rs.html#116-118">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.new_static" class="fn">new_static</a>() -&gt; <a class="struct" href="struct.IrKeplerStatic.html" title="struct device_kit::ir_kepler::IrKeplerStatic">IrKeplerStatic</a></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Create static channel resources for IR events.</p>
<p>See <a href="struct.IrKepler.html" title="struct device_kit::ir_kepler::IrKepler"><code>IrKepler</code></a> for usage examples.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.new" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/ir_kepler.rs.html#131-138">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub fn <a href="#method.new" class="fn">new</a>&lt;P: Pin&gt;(
    ir_kepler_static: &amp;'static <a class="struct" href="struct.IrKeplerStatic.html" title="struct device_kit::ir_kepler::IrKeplerStatic">IrKeplerStatic</a>,
    pin: Peri&lt;'static, P&gt;,
    spawner: Spawner,
) -&gt; <a class="type" href="../type.Result.html" title="type device_kit::Result">Result</a>&lt;Self&gt;</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Create a new Kepler remote handler.</p>
<h5 id="parameters"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#parameters">§</a>Parameters</h5>
<ul>
<li><code>ir_kepler_static</code>: Static reference to the channel resources</li>
<li><code>pin</code>: GPIO pin connected to the IR receiver</li>
<li><code>spawner</code>: Embassy spawner for background task</li>
</ul>
<p>See <a href="struct.IrKepler.html" title="struct device_kit::ir_kepler::IrKepler"><code>IrKepler</code></a> for usage examples.</p>
<h5 id="errors"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#errors">§</a>Errors</h5>
<p>Returns an error if the background task cannot be spawned.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.wait_for_press" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/ir_kepler.rs.html#145-147">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub async fn <a href="#method.wait_for_press" class="fn">wait_for_press</a>(&amp;self) -&gt; <a class="enum" href="enum.KeplerButton.html" title="enum device_kit::ir_kepler::KeplerButton">KeplerButton</a></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Wait for the next button press.</p>
<p>Ignores button presses that are not recognized by the Kepler remote.</p>
<p>See <a href="struct.IrKepler.html" title="struct device_kit::ir_kepler::IrKepler"><code>IrKepler</code></a> for usage examples.</p>
</div></details></div></details></div><h2 id="synthetic-implementations" class="section-header">Auto Trait Implementations<a href="#synthetic-implementations" class="anchor">§</a></h2><div id="synthetic-implementations-list"><section id="impl-Freeze-for-IrKepler%3C'a%3E" class="impl"><a href="#impl-Freeze-for-IrKepler%3C'a%3E" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;'a&gt; </div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#767-769">Source</a><a href="#impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;T, U&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html" title="trait core::convert::Into">Into</a>&lt;U&gt; for T<div class="where">where
    U: <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt;,</div></h3></section></summary><div class="impl-items"><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.into" class="method trait-impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#777">Source</a><a href="#method.into" class="anchor">§</a><h4 class="code-header">fn <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html#tymethod.into" class="fn">into</a>(self) -&gt; U</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Calls <code>U::from(self)</code>.</p>
<p>That is, this conversion is whatever the implementation of
<code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt; for U</code> chooses to do.</p>

</div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#767-769">Source</a><a href="#impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;T, U&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html" title="trait core::convert::Into">Into</a>&lt;U&gt; for T<div class="where">where

<p>That is, this conversion is whatever the implementation of
<code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt; for U</code> chooses to do.</p>

item-decl"><code>pub struct IrLedLayout&lt;'a, B, const N: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.usize.html">usize</a>&gt; { <span class="comment">/* private remote button presses to user-defined button types.</p>
<h2 id="examples"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#examples">§</a>Examples</h2>
<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::ir_mapping::{IrLedLayout, IrLedLayoutStatic};
<span class="attr">#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy)]
</span><span class="kw">enum </span>RemoteButton { Power, Play, Stop }
<span class="kw">async fn </span>example(
    p: embassy_rp::Peripherals,
    spawner: embassy_executor::Spawner,
) -&gt; device_kit::Result&lt;()&gt; {
    <span class="kw">let </span>button_map = [
        (<span class="number">0x0000</span>, <span class="number">0x45</span>, RemoteButton::Power),
        (<span class="number">0x0000</span>, <span class="number">0x0C</span>, RemoteButton::Play),
        (<span class="number">0x0000</span>, <span class="number">0x08</span>, RemoteButton::Stop),
    ];

    <span class="kw">static </span>IR_MAPPING_STATIC: IrLedLayoutStatic = IrLedLayout::&lt;RemoteButton, <span class="number">3</span>&gt;::new_static();
    <span class="kw">let </span>ir_mapping: IrLedLayout&lt;RemoteButton, <span class="number">3</span>&gt; = IrLedLayout::new(<span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>IR_MAPPING_STATIC, p.PIN_15, <span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>button_map, spawner)<span class="question-mark">?</span>;

    <span class="kw">loop </span>{
        <span class="kw">let </span>button = ir_mapping.wait_for_press().<span class="kw">await</span>;
        <span class="comment">// Use button...
    </span>}
}</code></pre></div></div></details><h2 id="implementations" class="section-header">Implementations<a href="#implementations" class="anchor">§</a></h2><div id="implementations-list"><details class="toggle implementors-toggle" open><summary><section id="impl-IrLedLayout%3C'a,+B,+N%3E" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/ir_mapping.rs.html#67-128">Source</a><a href="#impl-IrLedLayout%3C'a,+B,+N%3E" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;'a, B, const N: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.usize.html">usize</a>&gt; <a class="struct" href="struct.IrLedLayout.html" title="struct device_kit::ir_mapping::IrLedLayout">IrLedLayout</a>&lt;'a, B, N&gt;<div class="where">where
    B: <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/marker/trait.Copy.html" title="trait core::marker::Copy">Copy</a>,</div></h3></section></summary><div class="impl-items"><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.new_static" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/ir_mapping.rs.html#75-77">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.new_static" class="fn">new_static</a>() -&gt; <a class="struct" href="struct.IrLedLayoutStatic.html" title="struct device_kit::ir_mapping::IrLedLayoutStatic">IrLedLayoutStatic</a></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Create static channel resources for IR mapping events.</p>
<p>See <a href="struct.IrLedLayout.html" title="struct device_kit::ir_mapping::IrLedLayout"><code>IrLedLayout</code></a> for usage examples.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.new" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/ir_mapping.rs.html#91-109">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub fn <a href="#method.new" class="fn">new</a>&lt;P: Pin&gt;(
    ir_mapping_static: &amp;'static <a class="struct" href="struct.IrLedLayoutStatic.html" title="struct device_kit::ir_mapping::IrLedLayoutStatic">IrLedLayoutStatic</a>,
    pin: Peri&lt;'static, P&gt;,
    button_map: &amp;[(<a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.u16.html">u16</a>, <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.u8.html">u8</a>, B)],
    spawner: Spawner,
) -&gt; <a class="type" href="../type.Result.html" title="type device_kit::Result">Result</a>&lt;Self&gt;</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Create a new IR remote button mapper.</p>
<h5 id="parameters"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#parameters">§</a>Parameters</h5>
<ul>
<li><code>ir_mapping_static</code>: Static reference to the channel resources</li>
<li><code>pin</code>: GPIO pin connected to the IR receiver</li>
<li><code>button_map</code>: Array mapping (address, command) pairs to button types</li>
<li><code>spawner</code>: Embassy spawner for background task</li>
</ul>
<p>See <a href="struct.IrLedLayout.html" title="struct device_kit::ir_mapping::IrLedLayout"><code>IrLedLayout</code></a> for usage examples.</p>
<h5 id="errors"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#errors">§</a>Errors</h5>
<p>Returns an error if the background task cannot be spawned.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.wait_for_press" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/ir_mapping.rs.html#116-127">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub async fn <a href="#method.wait_for_press" class="fn">wait_for_press</a>(&amp;self) -&gt; B</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Wait for the next recognized button press.</p>
<p>Ignores button presses that are not in the button map.</p>
<p>See <a href="struct.IrLedLayout.html" title="struct device_kit::ir_mapping::IrLedLayout"><code>IrLedLayout</code></a> for usage examples.</p>

<p>Fonts with <code>Trim</code> suffix remove blank spacing to pack text more tightly on small displays.</p>
