class="content"><div class="main-heading"><div class="rustdoc-breadcrumbs"><a href="../index.html">device_kit</a></div><h1>Module <span>led2d</span>&nbsp;<button id="copy-path" title="Copy item path to clipboard">Copy item path</button></h1><rustdoc-toolbar></rustdoc-toolbar><span class="sub-heading"><a class="src" href="../../src/device_kit/led2d.rs.html#1-1724">Source</a> </span></div><details class="toggle top-doc" open><summary class="hideme"><span>Expand description</span></summary><div class="docblock"><p>A device abstraction for rectangular NeoPixel-style (WS2812) LED panel displays.
For 1-dimensional LED strips, see the <a href="../led_strip/index.html" title="mod device_kit::led_strip"><code>led_strip</code></a> module.</p>
<p>This page provides the primary documentation and examples for programming LED panels.
The device abstraction supports text, graphics, and animation.</p>
<p><strong>After reading the examples below, see also:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><a href="../macro.led2d.html" title="macro device_kit::led2d"><code>led2d!</code></a> — Macro to generate an LED-panel struct type (includes syntax details). See <a href="led2d_generated/struct.Led2dGenerated.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::led2d_generated::Led2dGenerated"><code>Led2dGenerated</code></a> for a sample of a generated type.</li>
<li><a href="led2d_generated/struct.Led2dGenerated.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::led2d_generated::Led2dGenerated"><code>Led2dGenerated</code></a> — Sample struct type generated by the <a href="../macro.led2d.html" title="macro device_kit::led2d"><code>led2d!</code></a> macro, showing all methods and constants.</li>
<li><a href="layout/struct.LedLayout.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::layout::LedLayout"><code>LedLayout</code></a> — Compile-type description of panel geometry and wiring, including dimensions (with examples)</li>
<li><a href="struct.Frame2d.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::Frame2d"><code>Frame2d</code></a> — 2D pixel array used for general graphics (includes examples)</li>
<li><a href="../macro.led_strips.html" title="macro device_kit::led_strips"><code>led_strips!</code></a> — Alternative macro to share a PIO resource with other panels or LED strips (includes examples)</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="example-write-text"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#example-write-text">§</a>Example: Write Text</h2>
<p>In this example, we render text on a 12×4 panel. Here, the generated struct type is named <code>Led12x4</code>.</p>
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="LED panel preview" /></p>

<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::{<span class="prelude-ty">Result</span>, led2d, led2d::layout::LedLayout, led2d::Led2dFont, led_strip::colors};

<span class="comment">// Tells us how the LED strip is wired up in the panel
// in this case, a common snake-like pattern.
</span><span class="kw">const </span>LED_LAYOUT_12X4: LedLayout&lt;<span class="number">48</span>, <span class="number">12</span>, <span class="number">4</span>&gt; = LedLayout::serpentine_column_major();

<span class="comment">// Generate a type named `Led12x4`.
</span><span class="macro">led2d!</span> {
    Led12x4 {
        pin: PIN_3,                          <span class="comment">// GPIO pin for LED data signal
        </span>led_layout: LED_LAYOUT_12X4,         <span class="comment">// LED layout mapping (defines dimensions)
        </span>font: Led2dFont::Font3x4Trim,        <span class="comment">// Font variant
    </span>}
}

<span class="kw">async fn </span>example(spawner: Spawner) -&gt; <span class="prelude-ty">Result</span>&lt;Infallible&gt; {
    <span class="kw">let </span>p = init(Default::default());

    <span class="comment">// Create a device abstraction for the LED panel.
    // Behind the scenes, this creates a channel &amp; background task to manage the display.
    </span><span class="kw">let </span>led12x4 = Led12x4::new(p.PIN_3, p.PIO0, p.DMA_CH0, spawner)<span class="question-mark">?</span>;

    <span class="comment">// Write text to the display with per-character colors.
    </span><span class="kw">let </span>colors = [colors::CYAN, colors::RED, colors::YELLOW];
    <span class="comment">// Each character takes the next color; when we run out, we start over.
    </span>led12x4.write_text(<span class="string">"Rust"</span>, <span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>colors).<span class="kw">await</span><span class="question-mark">?</span>;

    future::pending().<span class="kw">await </span><span class="comment">// run forever
</span>}</code></pre></div><h2 id="example-animated-text-on-a-rotated-panel"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#example-animated-text-on-a-rotated-panel">§</a>Example: Animated Text on a Rotated Panel</h2>
<p>This example animates text on a rotated 12×8 panel built from two stacked 12×4 panels.</p>
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="LED panel preview" /></p>

<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::{<span class="prelude-ty">Result</span>, led2d, led2d::layout::LedLayout, led2d::Frame2d, led2d::Led2dFont, led_strip::{Current, Gamma, colors}};
<span class="kw">use </span>embassy_time::Duration;

<span class="comment">// Our panel is two 12x4 panels stacked vertically and then rotated clockwise.
</span><span class="kw">const </span>LED_LAYOUT_12X4: LedLayout&lt;<span class="number">48</span>, <span class="number">12</span>, <span class="number">4</span>&gt; = LedLayout::serpentine_column_major();
<span class="kw">const </span>LED_LAYOUT_12X8: LedLayout&lt;<span class="number">96</span>, <span class="number">12</span>, <span class="number">8</span>&gt; = LED_LAYOUT_12X4.combine_v(LED_LAYOUT_12X4);
<span class="kw">const </span>LED_LAYOUT_12X8_ROTATED: LedLayout&lt;<span class="number">96</span>, <span class="number">8</span>, <span class="number">12</span>&gt; = LED_LAYOUT_12X8.rotate_cw();

<span class="comment">// Generate a type named `Led12x8Animated`.
</span><span class="macro">led2d!</span> {
    <span class="kw">pub</span>(<span class="self">self</span>) Led12x8Animated {               <span class="comment">// Can provide a visibility modifier
        </span>pin: PIN_4,                           <span class="comment">// GPIO pin for LED data signal
        </span>led_layout: LED_LAYOUT_12X8_ROTATED,  <span class="comment">// Two 12×4 panels stacked and rotated
        </span>font: Led2dFont::Font4x6Trim,         <span class="comment">// Use a 4x6 pixel font without the usual 1 pixel padding
        </span>pio: PIO1,                            <span class="comment">// PIO resource, default is PIO0
        </span>dma: DMA_CH1,                         <span class="comment">// DMA resource, default is DMA_CH0
        </span>max_current: Current::Milliamps(<span class="number">300</span>), <span class="comment">// Power budget, default is 250 mA.
        </span>gamma: Gamma::Linear,                 <span class="comment">// Color correction curve, default is Gamma2_2
        </span>max_frames: <span class="number">2</span>,                        <span class="comment">// maximum animation frames, default is 16
    </span>}
}

<span class="kw">async fn </span>example(spawner: Spawner) -&gt; <span class="prelude-ty">Result</span>&lt;Infallible&gt; {
    <span class="kw">let </span>p = init(Default::default());

   <span class="comment">// Create a device abstraction for the rotated LED panel.
    </span><span class="kw">let </span>led_12x8_animated = Led12x8Animated::new(p.PIN_4, p.PIO1, p.DMA_CH1, spawner)<span class="question-mark">?</span>;

    <span class="comment">// Write "Go" into an in-memory frame buffer.
    </span><span class="kw">let </span><span class="kw-2">mut </span>frame_0 = Frame2d::new();
    <span class="comment">// Empty text colors array defaults to white.
    </span>led_12x8_animated.write_text_to_frame(<span class="string">"Go"</span>, <span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>[], <span class="kw-2">&amp;mut </span>frame_0)<span class="question-mark">?</span>;

    <span class="comment">// Write "Go" into a second frame buffer with custom colors and on the 2nd line.
    </span><span class="kw">let </span><span class="kw-2">mut </span>frame_1 = Frame2d::new();
    <span class="comment">// "/n" starts a new line. Text does not wrap but rather clips.
    </span>led_12x8_animated.write_text_to_frame(
        <span class="string">"\nGo"</span>,
        <span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>[colors::HOT_PINK, colors::LIME],
        <span class="kw-2">&amp;mut </span>frame_1,
    )<span class="question-mark">?</span>;

    <span class="comment">// Animate between the two frames indefinitely.
    </span><span class="kw">let </span>frame_duration = Duration::from_secs(<span class="number">1</span>);
    led_12x8_animated
        .animate([(frame_0, frame_duration), (frame_1, frame_duration)])
        .<span class="kw">await</span><span class="question-mark">?</span>;

    future::pending().<span class="kw">await </span><span class="comment">// run forever
</span>}</code></pre></div></div></details><h2 id="reexports" class="section-header">Re-exports<a href="#reexports" class="anchor">§</a></h2><dl class="item-table reexports"><dt id="reexport.LedLayout"><code>pub use layout::<a class="struct" href="layout/struct.LedLayout.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::layout::LedLayout">LedLayout</a>;</code></dt></dl><h2 id="modules" class="section-header">Modules<a href="#modules" class="anchor">§</a></h2><dl class="item-table"><dt><a class="mod" href="layout/index.html" title="mod device_kit::led2d::layout">layout</a></dt><dd>Module containing <a href="layout/struct.LedLayout.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::layout::LedLayout"><code>LedLayout</code></a>, the struct for compile-time description of
panel geometry and wiring.</dd><dt><a class="mod" href="led2d_generated/index.html" title="mod device_kit::led2d::led2d_generated">led2d_<wbr>generated</a></dt><dd>Module containing <a href="led2d_generated/struct.Led2dGenerated.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::led2d_generated::Led2dGenerated"><code>Led2dGenerated</code></a>, the sample struct type generated by the <a href="../macro.led2d.html" title="macro device_kit::led2d"><code>led2d!</code></a> macro.</dd></dl><h2 id="macros" class="section-header">Macros<a href="#macros" class="anchor">§</a></h2><dl class="item-table"><dt><a class="macro" href="macro.led2d.html" title="macro device_kit::led2d::led2d">led2d</a></dt><dd>Macro to generate an LED-panel struct type (includes syntax details). device_<wbr>kit::<wbr>led2d::<wbr>layout</a></h2></div></div></nav><div class="sidebar-resizer" title="Drag to resize sidebar"></div><main><div class="width-limiter"><section id="main-content" class="content"><div class="main-heading"><div class="rustdoc-breadcrumbs"><a href="../../index.html">device_kit</a>::<wbr><a href="../index.html">led2d</a>::<wbr><a href="index.html">layout</a></div><h1>Struct <span class="struct">LedLayout</span>&nbsp;<button id="copy-path" title="Copy item path to clipboard">Copy item path</button></h1><rustdoc-toolbar></rustdoc-toolbar><span class="sub-heading"><a class="src" href="../../../src/device_kit/led2d/layout.rs.html#82-84">Source</a> </span></div><pre class="rust item-decl"><code>pub struct LedLayout&lt;const N: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.usize.html">usize</a>, const W: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.usize.html">usize</a>, const H: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.usize.html">usize</a>&gt; { <span class="comment">/* private fields */</span> }</code></pre><details class="toggle top-doc" open><summary class="hideme"><span>Expand description</span></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Compile-time description of panel geometry and wiring, including dimensions (with examples).</p>
<p><code>LedLayout</code> defines how a rectangular <code>(x, y)</code> panel of LEDs maps to the linear
wiring order of LEDs on a NeoPixel-style (WS2812) panel.</p>
<p>For examples of <code>LedLayout</code> in use, see the <a href="../index.html" title="mod device_kit::led2d"><code>led2d</code></a> module,
<a href="../struct.Frame2d.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::Frame2d"><code>Frame2d</code></a>, and the example below.</p>
<p><strong>What <code>LedLayout</code> does:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Lets you describe panel wiring once</li>
<li>Enables drawing text, graphics, and animations in <code>(x, y)</code> space</li>
<li>Hides LED strip order from rendering code</li>
</ul>
<p>Coordinates use a screen-style convention:</p>
<ul>
<li><code>(0, 0)</code> is the top-left corner</li>
<li><code>x</code> increases to the right</li>
<li><code>y</code> increases downward</li>
</ul>
<p>Most users should start with one of the constructors below and then apply
transforms (<a href="struct.LedLayout.html#method.rotate_cw" title="method device_kit::led2d::layout::LedLayout::rotate_cw">rotate_cw</a>, <a href="struct.LedLayout.html#method.flip_h" title="method device_kit::led2d::layout::LedLayout::flip_h">flip_h</a>, <a href="struct.LedLayout.html#method.combine_v" title="method device_kit::led2d::layout::LedLayout::combine_v">combine_v</a>, etc.)
as needed.</p>
<h3 id="constructing-layouts"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#constructing-layouts">§</a>Constructing layouts</h3>
<p>Prefer the built-in constructors when possible:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="struct.LedLayout.html#method.serpentine_row_major" title="associated function device_kit::led2d::layout::LedLayout::serpentine_row_major"><code>serpentine_row_major</code></a></li>
<li><a href="struct.LedLayout.html#method.serpentine_column_major" title="associated function device_kit::led2d::layout::LedLayout::serpentine_column_major"><code>serpentine_column_major</code></a></li>
<li><a href="struct.LedLayout.html#method.linear_h" title="associated function device_kit::led2d::layout::LedLayout::linear_h"><code>linear_h</code></a> / <a href="struct.LedLayout.html#method.linear_v" title="associated function device_kit::led2d::layout::LedLayout::linear_v"><code>linear_v</code></a></li>
</ul>
<p>For unusual wiring, you can construct a layout directly with <a href="struct.LedLayout.html#method.new" title="associated function device_kit::led2d::layout::LedLayout::new"><code>LedLayout::new</code></a>
by listing <code>(x, y)</code> for each LED in the order the strip is wired.</p>
<p><strong>The example below shows both construction methods.</strong> Also, the documentation for every constructor
and method includes illustrations of use.</p>
<h3 id="transforming-layouts"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#transforming-layouts">§</a>Transforming layouts</h3>
<p>You can adapt a layout without rewriting it:</p>
<ul>
<li>rotate: <a href="struct.LedLayout.html#method.rotate_cw" title="method device_kit::led2d::layout::LedLayout::rotate_cw"><code>rotate_cw</code></a>, <a href="struct.LedLayout.html#method.rotate_ccw" title="method device_kit::led2d::layout::LedLayout::rotate_ccw"><code>rotate_ccw</code></a>, <a href="struct.LedLayout.html#method.rotate_180" title="method device_kit::led2d::layout::LedLayout::rotate_180"><code>rotate_180</code></a></li>
<li>flip: <a href="struct.LedLayout.html#method.flip_h" title="method device_kit::led2d::layout::LedLayout::flip_h"><code>flip_h</code></a>, <a href="struct.LedLayout.html#method.flip_v" title="method device_kit::led2d::layout::LedLayout::flip_v"><code>flip_v</code></a></li>
<li>combine: <a href="struct.LedLayout.html#method.combine_h" title="method device_kit::led2d::layout::LedLayout::combine_h"><code>combine_h</code></a>, <a href="struct.LedLayout.html#method.combine_v" title="method device_kit::led2d::layout::LedLayout::combine_v"><code>combine_v</code></a>  (join two layouts into a larger one)</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="validation"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#validation">§</a>Validation</h3>
<p>Layouts are validated at <strong>compile time</strong>:</p>
<ul>
<li>coordinates must be in-bounds</li>
<li>every <code>(x, y)</code> cell must appear exactly once</li>
</ul>
<p>If you want the final mapping, use <a href="struct.LedLayout.html#method.index_to_xy" title="method device_kit::led2d::layout::LedLayout::index_to_xy"><code>index_to_xy</code></a>.</p>
<h2 id="example"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#example">§</a>Example</h2>
<p>Rotate a serpentine-wired 3×2 panel into a 2×3 layout and verify the result at compile time:</p>

<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::led2d::layout::LedLayout;

<span class="kw">const </span>ROTATED: LedLayout&lt;<span class="number">6</span>, <span class="number">2</span>, <span class="number">3</span>&gt; = LedLayout::serpentine_column_major().rotate_cw();
<span class="kw">const </span>EXPECTED: LedLayout&lt;<span class="number">6</span>, <span class="number">2</span>, <span class="number">3</span>&gt; =
    LedLayout::new([(<span class="number">1</span>, <span class="number">0</span>), (<span class="number">0</span>, <span class="number">0</span>), (<span class="number">0</span>, <span class="number">1</span>), (<span class="number">1</span>, <span class="number">1</span>), (<span class="number">1</span>, <span class="number">2</span>), (<span class="number">0</span>, <span class="number">2</span>)]);
<span class="kw">const _</span>: () = <span class="macro">assert!</span>(ROTATED.equals(<span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>EXPECTED)); <span class="comment">// Compile-time assert</span></code></pre></div><div class="example-wrap"><pre class="language-text"><code>Serpentine 3×2 rotated to 2×3:

  Before:              After:
    LED0  LED3  LED4     LED1  LED0
    LED1  LED2  LED5     LED2  LED3
                         LED5  LED4</code></pre></div></div></details><h2 id="implementations" class="section-header">Implementations<a href="#implementations" class="anchor">§</a></h2><div id="implementations-list"><details class="toggle implementors-toggle" open><summary><section id="impl-LedLayout%3CN,+W,+H%3E" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="../../../src/device_kit/led2d/layout.rs.html#86-665">Source</a><a href="#impl-LedLayout%3CN,+W,+H%3E" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;const N: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.usize.html">usize</a>, const W: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.usize.html">usize</a>, const H: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.usize.html">usize</a>&gt; <a class="struct" href="struct.LedLayout.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::layout::LedLayout">LedLayout</a>&lt;N, W, H&gt;</h3></section></summary><div class="impl-items"><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.index_to_xy" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../../src/device_kit/led2d/layout.rs.html#89-91">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.index_to_xy" class="fn">index_to_xy</a>(&amp;self) -&gt; &amp;[(<a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.u16.html">u16</a>, <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.u16.html">u16</a>); <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.array.html">N</a>]</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Return the array mapping LED wiring order to <code>(x, y)</code> coordinates.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.width" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../../src/device_kit/led2d/layout.rs.html#95-97">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.width" class="fn">width</a>(&amp;self) -&gt; <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.usize.html">usize</a></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>The width of the layout.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.height" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../../src/device_kit/led2d/layout.rs.html#101-103">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.height" class="fn">height</a>(&amp;self) -&gt; <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.usize.html">usize</a></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>The height of the layout.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.len" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../../src/device_kit/led2d/layout.rs.html#107-109">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.len" class="fn">len</a>(&amp;self) -&gt; <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.usize.html">usize</a></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Total LEDs in this layout (width × height).</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.equals" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../../src/device_kit/led2d/layout.rs.html#170-179">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.equals" class="fn">equals</a>(&amp;self, other: &amp;Self) -&gt; <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.bool.html">bool</a></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Const equality helper for doctests/examples.</p>

<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::led2d::layout::LedLayout;

<span class="kw">const </span>LINEAR: LedLayout&lt;<span class="number">4</span>, <span class="number">4</span>, <span class="number">1</span>&gt; = LedLayout::linear_h();
<span class="kw">const </span>ROTATED: LedLayout&lt;<span class="number">4</span>, <span class="number">4</span>, <span class="number">1</span>&gt; = LedLayout::linear_v().rotate_cw();

<span class="kw">const _</span>: () = <span class="macro">assert!</span>(LINEAR.equals(<span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>LINEAR));   <span class="comment">// assert equal
</span><span class="kw">const _</span>: () = <span class="macro">assert!</span>(!LINEAR.equals(<span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>ROTATED)); <span class="comment">// assert not equal</span></code></pre></div><div class="example-wrap"><pre class="language-text"><code>LINEAR:  LED0  LED1  LED2  LED3
ROTATED: LED3  LED2  LED1  LED0</code></pre></div></div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.new" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../../src/device_kit/led2d/layout.rs.html#222-251">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.new" class="fn">new</a>(map: [(<a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.u16.html">u16</a>, <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.u16.html">u16</a>); <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.array.html">N</a>]) -&gt; Self</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Construct a <code>LedLayout</code> by explicitly specifying the wiring order.</p>
<p>Use this constructor when your panel wiring does not match one of the
built-in patterns (linear, serpentine, etc.). You provide the <code>(x, y)</code>
coordinate for <strong>each LED in strip order</strong>, and <code>LedLayout</code> derives the
panel geometry from that mapping.</p>
<p>This constructor is <code>const</code> and is intended to be used in a <code>const</code>
definition, so layout errors are caught at <strong>compile time</strong>, not at runtime.</p>

<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::led2d::layout::LedLayout;

<span class="comment">// 3×2 panel (landscape, W×H)
</span><span class="kw">const </span>MAP: LedLayout&lt;<span class="number">6</span>, <span class="number">3</span>, <span class="number">2</span>&gt; =
    LedLayout::new([(<span class="number">0</span>, <span class="number">0</span>), (<span class="number">1</span>, <span class="number">0</span>), (<span class="number">2</span>, <span class="number">0</span>), (<span class="number">2</span>, <span class="number">1</span>), (<span class="number">1</span>, <span class="number">1</span>), (<span class="number">0</span>, <span class="number">1</span>)]);

<span class="comment">// Rotate to portrait (CW)
</span><span class="kw">const </span>ROTATED: LedLayout&lt;<span class="number">6</span>, <span class="number">2</span>, <span class="number">3</span>&gt; = MAP.rotate_cw();

<span class="comment">// Expected: 2×3 panel (W×H)
</span><span class="kw">const </span>EXPECTED: LedLayout&lt;<span class="number">6</span>, <span class="number">2</span>, <span class="number">3</span>&gt; =
    LedLayout::new([(<span class="number">1</span>, <span class="number">0</span>), (<span class="number">1</span>, <span class="number">1</span>), (<span class="number">1</span>, <span class="number">2</span>), (<span class="number">0</span>, <span class="number">2</span>), (<span class="number">0</span>, <span class="number">1</span>), (<span class="number">0</span>, <span class="number">0</span>)]);

<span class="kw">const _</span>: () = <span class="macro">assert!</span>(ROTATED.equals(<span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>EXPECTED));</code></pre></div><div class="example-wrap"><pre class="language-text"><code>3×2 input (col,row by LED index):
  LED0  LED1  LED2
  LED5  LED4  LED3

After rotate to 2×3:
  LED1  LED0
  LED2  LED3
  LED5  LED4</code></pre></div></div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.linear_h" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../../src/device_kit/led2d/layout.rs.html#273-284">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.linear_h" class="fn">linear_h</a>() -&gt; Self</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Linear row-major mapping for a single-row strip (cols increase left-to-right).</p>

<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::led2d::layout::LedLayout;

<span class="kw">const </span>LINEAR: LedLayout&lt;<span class="number">6</span>, <span class="number">6</span>, <span class="number">1</span>&gt; = LedLayout::linear_h();
<span class="kw">const </span>EXPECTED: LedLayout&lt;<span class="number">6</span>, <span class="number">6</span>, <span class="number">1</span>&gt; =
    LedLayout::new([(<span class="number">0</span>, <span class="number">0</span>), (<span class="number">1</span>, <span class="number">0</span>), (<span class="number">2</span>, <span class="number">0</span>), (<span class="number">3</span>, <span class="number">0</span>), (<span class="number">4</span>, <span class="number">0</span>), (<span class="number">5</span>, <span class="number">0</span>)]);
<span class="kw">const _</span>: () = <span class="macro">assert!</span>(LINEAR.equals(<span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>EXPECTED));</code></pre></div><div class="example-wrap"><pre class="language-text"><code>6×1 strip maps to single row:
  LED0  LED1  LED2  LED3  LED4  LED5</code></pre></div></div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.linear_v" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../../src/device_kit/led2d/layout.rs.html#311-322">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.linear_v" class="fn">linear_v</a>() -&gt; Self</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Linear column-major mapping for a single-column strip (rows increase top-to-bottom).</p>

<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::led2d::layout::LedLayout;

<span class="kw">const </span>LINEAR: LedLayout&lt;<span class="number">6</span>, <span class="number">1</span>, <span class="number">6</span>&gt; = LedLayout::linear_v();
<span class="kw">const </span>EXPECTED: LedLayout&lt;<span class="number">6</span>, <span class="number">1</span>, <span class="number">6</span>&gt; =
    LedLayout::new([(<span class="number">0</span>, <span class="number">0</span>), (<span class="number">0</span>, <span class="number">1</span>), (<span class="number">0</span>, <span class="number">2</span>), (<span class="number">0</span>, <span class="number">3</span>), (<span class="number">0</span>, <span class="number">4</span>), (<span class="number">0</span>, <span class="number">5</span>)]);

  LED0
  LED1
  LED2
  LED3
  LED4
  LED5</code></pre></div></div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.serpentine_column_major" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../../src/device_kit/led2d/layout.rs.html#345-367">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.serpentine_column_major" class="fn">serpentine_column_major</a>() -&gt; Self</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Serpentine column-major mapping returned as a checked <code>LedLayout</code>.</p>

<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::led2d::layout::LedLayout;

<span class="kw">const </span>MAP: LedLayout&lt;<span class="number">6</span>, <span class="number">3</span>, <span class="number">2</span>&gt; = LedLayout::serpentine_column_major();
<span class="kw">const </span>EXPECTED: LedLayout&lt;<span class="number">6</span>, <span class="number">3</span>, <span class="number">2</span>&gt; =
    LedLayout::new([(<span class="number">0</span>, <span class="number">0</span>), (<span class="number">0</span>, <span class="number">1</span>), (<span class="number">1</span>, <span class="number">1</span>), (<span class="number">1</span>, <span class="number">0</span>), (<span class="number">2</span>, <span class="number">0</span>), (<span class="number">2</span>, <span class="number">1</span>)]);

  LED0  LED3  LED4
  LED1  LED2  LED5</code></pre></div></div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.serpentine_row_major" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../../src/device_kit/led2d/layout.rs.html#390-410">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.serpentine_row_major" class="fn">serpentine_row_major</a>() -&gt; Self</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Serpentine row-major mapping (alternating left-to-right and right-to-left across rows).</p>

  LED0  LED1  LED2
  LED5  LED4  LED3</code></pre></div></div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.rotate_cw" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../../src/device_kit/led2d/layout.rs.html#434-445">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.rotate_cw" class="fn">rotate_cw</a>(self) -&gt; <a class="struct" href="struct.LedLayout.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::layout::LedLayout">LedLayout</a>&lt;N, H, W&gt;</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Rotate 90° clockwise (dims swap).</p>

<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::led2d::layout::LedLayout;

<span class="kw">const </span>ROTATED: LedLayout&lt;<span class="number">6</span>, <span class="number">2</span>, <span class="number">3</span>&gt; = LedLayout::serpentine_column_major().rotate_cw();

                          LED5  LED4</code></pre></div></div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.flip_h" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../../src/device_kit/led2d/layout.rs.html#468-478">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.flip_h" class="fn">flip_h</a>(self) -&gt; Self</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Flip horizontally (mirror columns).</p>

<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::led2d::layout::LedLayout;

<span class="kw">const _</span>: () = <span class="macro">assert!</span>(FLIPPED.equals(<span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>EXPECTED));</code></pre></div><div class="example-wrap"><pre class="language-text"><code>Before (serpentine): After:
  LED0  LED3  LED4      LED4  LED3  LED0
  LED1  LED2  LED5      LED5  LED2  LED1</code></pre></div></div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.rotate_180" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../../src/device_kit/led2d/layout.rs.html#501-503">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.rotate_180" class="fn">rotate_180</a>(self) -&gt; Self</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Rotate 180° derived from rotate_cw.</p>

<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::led2d::layout::LedLayout;

<span class="kw">const </span>ROTATED: LedLayout&lt;<span class="number">6</span>, <span class="number">3</span>, <span class="number">2</span>&gt; = LedLayout::serpentine_column_major().rotate_180();
<span class="kw">const </span>EXPECTED: LedLayout&lt;<span class="number">6</span>, <span class="number">3</span>, <span class="number">2</span>&gt; =
    LedLayout::new([(<span class="number">2</span>, <span class="number">1</span>), (<span class="number">2</span>, <span class="number">0</span>), (<span class="number">1</span>, <span class="number">0</span>), (<span class="number">1</span>, <span class="number">1</span>), (<span class="number">0</span>, <span class="number">1</span>), (<span class="number">0</span>, <span class="number">0</span>)]);
<span class="kw">const _</span>: () = <span class="macro">assert!</span>(ROTATED.equals(<span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>EXPECTED));</code></pre></div><div class="example-wrap"><pre class="language-text"><code>Before (3×2 serpentine): After 180°:
  LED0  LED3  LED4        LED5  LED2  LED1
  LED1  LED2  LED5        LED4  LED3  LED0</code></pre></div></div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.rotate_ccw" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../../src/device_kit/led2d/layout.rs.html#527-529">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.rotate_ccw" class="fn">rotate_ccw</a>(self) -&gt; <a class="struct" href="struct.LedLayout.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::layout::LedLayout">LedLayout</a>&lt;N, H, W&gt;</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Rotate 90° counter-clockwise derived from rotate_cw.</p>

<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::led2d::layout::LedLayout;

<span class="kw">const </span>ROTATED: LedLayout&lt;<span class="number">6</span>, <span class="number">2</span>, <span class="number">3</span>&gt; = LedLayout::serpentine_column_major().rotate_ccw();
<span class="kw">const </span>EXPECTED: LedLayout&lt;<span class="number">6</span>, <span class="number">2</span>, <span class="number">3</span>&gt; =
    LedLayout::new([(<span class="number">0</span>, <span class="number">2</span>), (<span class="number">1</span>, <span class="number">2</span>), (<span class="number">1</span>, <span class="number">1</span>), (<span class="number">0</span>, <span class="number">1</span>), (<span class="number">0</span>, <span class="number">0</span>), (<span class="number">1</span>, <span class="number">0</span>)]);
<span class="kw">const _</span>: () = <span class="macro">assert!</span>(ROTATED.equals(<span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>EXPECTED));</code></pre></div><div class="example-wrap"><pre class="language-text"><code>Before (3×2 serpentine): After (2×3):
  LED0  LED3  LED4        LED4  LED5
  LED1  LED2  LED5        LED3  LED2
                          LED0  LED1</code></pre></div></div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.flip_v" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../../src/device_kit/led2d/layout.rs.html#552-554">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.flip_v" class="fn">flip_v</a>(self) -&gt; Self</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Flip vertically derived from rotation + horizontal flip.</p>

<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::led2d::layout::LedLayout;

<span class="kw">const </span>FLIPPED: LedLayout&lt;<span class="number">6</span>, <span class="number">3</span>, <span class="number">2</span>&gt; = LedLayout::serpentine_column_major().flip_v();
<span class="kw">const </span>EXPECTED: LedLayout&lt;<span class="number">6</span>, <span class="number">3</span>, <span class="number">2</span>&gt; =
    LedLayout::new([(<span class="number">0</span>, <span class="number">1</span>), (<span class="number">0</span>, <span class="number">0</span>), (<span class="number">1</span>, <span class="number">0</span>), (<span class="number">1</span>, <span class="number">1</span>), (<span class="number">2</span>, <span class="number">1</span>), (<span class="number">2</span>, <span class="number">0</span>)]);
<span class="kw">const _</span>: () = <span class="macro">assert!</span>(FLIPPED.equals(<span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>EXPECTED));</code></pre></div><div class="example-wrap"><pre class="language-text"><code>Before (serpentine): After:
  LED0  LED3  LED4      LED1  LED2  LED5
  LED1  LED2  LED5      LED0  LED3  LED4</code></pre></div></div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.combine_h" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../../src/device_kit/led2d/layout.rs.html#584-612">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.combine_h" class="fn">combine_h</a>&lt;const N2: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.usize.html">usize</a>, const OUT_N: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.usize.html">usize</a>, const W2: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.usize.html">usize</a>, const OUT_W: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.usize.html">usize</a>&gt;(
    self,
    right: <a class="struct" href="struct.LedLayout.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::layout::LedLayout">LedLayout</a>&lt;N2, W2, H&gt;,
) -&gt; <a class="struct" href="struct.LedLayout.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::layout::LedLayout">LedLayout</a>&lt;OUT_N, OUT_W, H&gt;</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Concatenate horizontally with another mapping sharing the same rows.</p>

<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::led2d::layout::LedLayout;

<span class="kw">const </span>LED_LAYOUT: LedLayout&lt;<span class="number">6</span>, <span class="number">3</span>, <span class="number">2</span>&gt; = LedLayout::serpentine_column_major();
<span class="kw">const </span>COMBINED: LedLayout&lt;<span class="number">12</span>, <span class="number">6</span>, <span class="number">2</span>&gt; = LED_LAYOUT.combine_h::&lt;<span class="number">6</span>, <span class="number">12</span>, <span class="number">3</span>, <span class="number">6</span>&gt;(LED_LAYOUT);
<span class="kw">const </span>EXPECTED: LedLayout&lt;<span class="number">12</span>, <span class="number">6</span>, <span class="number">2</span>&gt; = LedLayout::new([
    (<span class="number">0</span>, <span class="number">0</span>), (<span class="number">0</span>, <span class="number">1</span>), (<span class="number">1</span>, <span class="number">1</span>), (<span class="number">1</span>, <span class="number">0</span>), (<span class="number">2</span>, <span class="number">0</span>), (<span class="number">2</span>, <span class="number">1</span>), (<span class="number">3</span>, <span class="number">0</span>), (<span class="number">3</span>, <span class="number">1</span>), (<span class="number">4</span>, <span class="number">1</span>),
    (<span class="number">4</span>, <span class="number">0</span>), (<span class="number">5</span>, <span class="number">0</span>), (<span class="number">5</span>, <span class="number">1</span>),
]);
<span class="kw">const _</span>: () = <span class="macro">assert!</span>(COMBINED.equals(<span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>EXPECTED));</code></pre></div><div class="example-wrap"><pre class="language-text"><code>Left serpentine (3×2):    Right serpentine (3×2):
  0  3  4                   6  9 10
  1  2  5                   7  8 11

Combined (6×2):
  0  3  4  6  9 10
  1  2  5  7  8 11</code></pre></div></div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.combine_v" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../../src/device_kit/led2d/layout.rs.html#644-664">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.combine_v" class="fn">combine_v</a>&lt;const N2: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.usize.html">usize</a>, const OUT_N: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.usize.html">usize</a>, const H2: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.usize.html">usize</a>, const OUT_H: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.usize.html">usize</a>&gt;(

<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::led2d::layout::LedLayout;

<span class="kw">const </span>LED_LAYOUT: LedLayout&lt;<span class="number">6</span>, <span class="number">3</span>, <span class="number">2</span>&gt; = LedLayout::serpentine_column_major();

<span class="kw">const </span>EXPECTED: LedLayout&lt;<span class="number">12</span>, <span class="number">3</span>, <span class="number">4</span>&gt; = LedLayout::new([
    (<span class="number">0</span>, <span class="number">0</span>), (<span class="number">0</span>, <span class="number">1</span>), (<span class="number">1</span>, <span class="number">1</span>), (<span class="number">1</span>, <span class="number">0</span>), (<span class="number">2</span>, <span class="number">0</span>), (<span class="number">2</span>, <span class="number">1</span>), (<span class="number">0</span>, <span class="number">2</span>), (<span class="number">0</span>, <span class="number">3</span>), (<span class="number">1</span>, <span class="number">3</span>),
    (<span class="number">1</span>, <span class="number">2</span>), (<span class="number">2</span>, <span class="number">2</span>), (<span class="number">2</span>, <span class="number">3</span>),
]);
<span class="kw">const _</span>: () = <span class="macro">assert!</span>(COMBINED.equals(<span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>EXPECTED));</code></pre></div><div class="example-wrap"><pre class="language-text"><code>Top serpentine (3×2):    Bottom serpentine (3×2):
  0  3  4                   6  9 10
  1  2  5                   7  8 11

  0  3  4
  1  2  5
  6  9 10

item-decl"><code>pub struct Led2dGenerated;</code></pre><details class="toggle top-doc" open><summary class="hideme"><span>Expand description</span></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Sample struct type generated by the <a href="../../macro.led2d.html" title="macro device_kit::led2d"><code>led2d!</code></a> macro, showing all methods and constants.</p>
<p>This page serves as the definitive reference for what a generated LED panel type
provides. For first-time readers, start with the examples in the <a href="../index.html" title="mod device_kit::led2d"><code>led2d</code></a> module
documentation, then return here for a complete list of available methods and
associated constants.</p>
<p>Auto-generated.</p>

</div></details><details class="toggle" open><summary><section id="associatedconstant.MAX_BRIGHTNESS" class="associatedconstant"><a class="src rightside" href="../../../src/device_kit/led2d/led2d_generated.rs.html#109-110">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub const <a href="#associatedconstant.MAX_BRIGHTNESS" class="constant">MAX_BRIGHTNESS</a>: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.u8.html">u8</a> = 255u8</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Maximum brightness level, automatically limited by the power budget specified in <code>max_current</code>.</p>
<p>We assume each LED draws 60 mA at full brightness. The actual limit depends on
the power budget you specified in the <a href="../../macro.led2d.html" title="macro device_kit::led2d"><code>led2d!</code></a> or <a href="../../macro.led_strips.html" title="macro device_kit::led_strips"><code>led_strips!</code></a> macro.
This constant is the result
of calculating how much brightness is safe given that budget and the number of LEDs.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle" open><summary><section id="associatedconstant.MAX_FRAMES" class="associatedconstant"><a class="src rightside" href="../../../src/device_kit/led2d/led2d_generated.rs.html#114">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub const <a href="#associatedconstant.MAX_FRAMES" class="constant">MAX_FRAMES</a>: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.usize.html">usize</a> = 16usize</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Maximum number of animation frames allowed.</p>
<p>Specified in the <a href="../../macro.led2d.html" title="macro device_kit::led2d"><code>led2d!</code></a> or <a href="../../macro.led_strips.html" title="macro device_kit::led_strips"><code>led_strips!</code></a> macro.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.new" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../../src/device_kit/led2d/led2d_generated.rs.html#143-151">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub fn <a href="#method.new" class="fn">new</a>(
    pin: Peri&lt;'static, PIN_3&gt;,
    pio: Peri&lt;'static, PIO0&gt;,
    dma: Peri&lt;'static, DMA_CH0&gt;,
    spawner: Spawner,
) -&gt; <a class="type" href="../../type.Result.html" title="type device_kit::Result">Result</a>&lt;Self&gt;</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Create a new LED panel instance of the struct type
defined by <a href="../../macro.led2d.html" title="macro device_kit::led2d"><code>led2d!</code></a>.</p>
<p>See the <a href="../index.html" title="mod device_kit::led2d"><code>led2d</code></a> module docs for usage.</p>
<p>The <code>pin</code>, <code>pio</code>, and <code>dma</code> parameters must correspond to the
GPIO pin, PIO resource, and DMA channel specified in the macro.</p>
<p>The <a href="../../macro.led2d.html" title="macro device_kit::led2d"><code>led2d!</code></a> macro defaults to <code>PIO0</code> and <code>DMA_CH0</code> if not specified.</p>
<h5 id="parameters"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#parameters">§</a>Parameters</h5>
<ul>
<li><code>pin</code>: GPIO pin for LED data signal</li>
<li><code>pio</code>: PIO resource</li>
<li><code>dma</code>: DMA channel for LED data transfer</li>
<li><code>spawner</code>: Task spawner for background operations</li>
</ul>

</div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#767-769">Source</a><a href="#impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;T, U&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html" title="trait core::convert::Into">Into</a>&lt;U&gt; for T<div class="where">where

<p>That is, this conversion is whatever the implementation of
<code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt; for U</code> chooses to do.</p>

class="sidebar-crate"><h2><a href="../../device_kit/index.html">device_<wbr>kit</a><span class="version">0.0.1-alpha</span></h2></div><div class="sidebar-elems"><section id="rustdoc-toc"><h2 class="location"><a href="#">led2d</a></h2><h3><a href="#">Sections</a></h3><ul class="block top-toc"><li><a href="#fields-1" title="Fields">Fields</a></li><li><a href="#current-limiting" href="../index.html">device_kit</a>::<wbr><a href="index.html">led2d</a></div><h1>Macro <span class="macro">led2d</span>&nbsp;<button id="copy-path" title="Copy item path to clipboard">Copy item path</button></h1><rustdoc-toolbar></rustdoc-toolbar><span class="sub-heading"><a class="src" href="../../src/device_kit/led2d.rs.html#1048-1050">Source</a> </span></div><pre class="rust item-decl"><code>macro_rules! led2d {
    ($($tt:tt)*) =&gt; { ... };
}</code></pre><details class="toggle top-doc" open><summary class="hideme"><span>Expand description</span></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Macro to generate an LED-panel struct type (includes syntax details). See <a href="led2d_generated/struct.Led2dGenerated.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::led2d_generated::Led2dGenerated"><code>Led2dGenerated</code></a> for a sample of a generated type.</p>
<p><strong>See the <a href="index.html" title="mod device_kit::led2d">led2d module</a> for usage examples.</strong></p>
<h2 id="fields-1"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#fields-1">§</a>Fields</h2>
<p><strong>Required fields:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><code>pin</code> — GPIO pin for LED data</li>
<li><code>led_layout</code> — LED strip physical layout (see <a href="layout/struct.LedLayout.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::layout::LedLayout"><code>LedLayout</code></a>); this defines the panel size</li>
<li><code>font</code> — Built-in font variant (see <a href="enum.Led2dFont.html" title="enum device_kit::led2d::Led2dFont"><code>Led2dFont</code></a>), e.g. <code>Led2dFont::Font4x6Trim</code></li>
</ul>
<p>The <code>led_layout</code> value must be a const so its dimensions can be derived at compile time.</p>
<p><strong>Optional fields:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><code>pio</code> — PIO resource to use (default: <code>PIO0</code>)</li>
<li><code>dma</code> — DMA channel (default: <code>DMA_CH0</code>)</li>
<li><code>max_current</code> — Electrical current budget (default: 250 mA)</li>
<li><code>gamma</code> — Color curve (default: <code>Gamma::Gamma2_2</code>)</li>
<li><code>max_frames</code> — Maximum number of animation frames for the generated strip (default: 16 frames)</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="current-limiting"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#current-limiting">§</a>Current Limiting</h2>
<p>The <code>max_current</code> field automatically scales brightness to stay within your electrical current budget.</p>
<p>Each WS2812 LED is assumed to draw 60 mA at full brightness. For example:</p>
<ul>
<li>16 LEDs × 60 mA = 960 mA at full brightness</li>
<li>With <code>max_current: Current::Milliamps(1000)</code>, all LEDs fit at 100% brightness</li>
<li>With the default electrical current limit (250 mA), the generated <code>MAX_BRIGHTNESS</code> limits LEDs to ~26% brightness</li>
</ul>
<p>The electrical current limit is baked into a compile-time lookup table, so it has no runtime cost.</p>
<p><strong>Powering LEDs from the Pico’s pin 40 (VBUS):</strong> Pin 40 is the USB 5 V rail pass-through, but the Pico itself has practical electrical current limits — the USB connector, cable, and internal circuitry aren’t designed for heavy loads. Small LED panels (a few hundred mA) can usually power from pin 40 with a decent USB supply; for larger loads (1 A+), use a separate 5 V supply and share ground with the Pico.</p>
<h2 id="color-correction-gamma"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#color-correction-gamma">§</a>Color Correction (Gamma)</h2>
<p>The <code>gamma</code> field applies a color response curve to make colors look more natural:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="../led_strip/enum.Gamma.html#variant.Linear" title="variant device_kit::led_strip::Gamma::Linear"><code>Gamma::Linear</code></a> — No correction (raw values)</li>
<li><a href="../led_strip/enum.Gamma.html#variant.Gamma2_2" title="variant device_kit::led_strip::Gamma::Gamma2_2"><code>Gamma::Gamma2_2</code></a> — sRGB-like curve (default; often looks most natural)</li>
</ul>
<p>The gamma curve is baked into a compile-time lookup table, so it has no runtime cost.</p>
<h2 id="related-macros"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#related-macros">§</a>Related Macros</h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="../macro.led_strips.html" title="macro device_kit::led_strips"><code>led_strips!</code></a> — Alternative macro to share a PIO resource with other panels or LED strips (includes examples)</li>
<li><a href="../led_strip/index.html" title="mod device_kit::led_strip"><code>led_strip!</code></a> — For 1-dimensional LED strips</li>
</ul>
</div></details></section></div></main></body></html>

device_<wbr>kit::<wbr>led2d</a></h2></div></div></nav><div class="sidebar-resizer" title="Drag to resize sidebar"></div><main><div class="width-limiter"><section id="main-content" class="content"><div class="main-heading"><div class="rustdoc-breadcrumbs"><a href="../index.html">device_kit</a>::<wbr><a href="index.html">led2d</a></div><h1>Struct <span class="struct">Frame2d</span>&nbsp;<button id="copy-path" title="Copy item path to clipboard">Copy item path</button></h1><rustdoc-toolbar></rustdoc-toolbar><span class="sub-heading"><a class="src" href="../../src/device_kit/led2d.rs.html#517">Source</a> </span></div><pre class="rust item-decl"><code>pub struct Frame2d&lt;const W: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.usize.html">usize</a>, const H: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.usize.html">usize</a>&gt;(pub [[<a class="type" href="../led_strip/type.RGB8.html" title="type device_kit::led_strip::RGB8">RGB8</a>; <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.array.html">W</a>]; <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.array.html">H</a>]);</code></pre><details class="toggle top-doc" open><summary class="hideme"><span>Expand description</span></summary><div class="docblock"><p>2D pixel array used for general graphics on LED panels (includes examples).</p>
<p>This page provides the primary documentation for drawing onto LED panels.</p>
<p><strong>Read the examples below first.</strong> After that, keep these details in mind:</p>
<ul>
<li>Use a frame to prepare an image before sending it to the panel.</li>
<li>Coordinates are <code>(x, y)</code> with <code>(0, 0)</code> at the top-left. The x-axis increases to the right,
and the y-axis increases downward.</li>
<li>Set pixels using tuple indexing: <code>frame[(x, y)] = colors::RED;</code>.</li>
<li>For shapes, lines, and text rendering, use the <a href="https://docs.rs/embedded-graphics"><code>embedded-graphics</code></a> crate.</li>
<li>Frames are rendered by a panel type generated with <a href="../macro.led2d.html" title="macro device_kit::led2d"><code>led2d!</code></a>.
See <a href="led2d_generated/struct.Led2dGenerated.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::led2d_generated::Led2dGenerated"><code>Led2dGenerated</code></a> for the full API of the generated panel type.</li>
<li>For animation, call <a href="led2d_generated/struct.Led2dGenerated.html#method.animate" title="method device_kit::led2d::led2d_generated::Led2dGenerated::animate"><code>animate</code></a> with a sequence
of <code>(</code><a href="struct.Frame2d.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::Frame2d"><code>Frame2d</code></a><code>, </code><a href="https://docs.rs/embassy-time/latest/embassy_time/struct.Duration.html"><code>Duration</code></a><code>)</code>
pairs. See the <a href="index.html" title="mod device_kit::led2d">led2d</a> module for an example.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="indexing-and-storage"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#indexing-and-storage">§</a>Indexing and storage</h3>
<p><code>Frame2d</code> supports both:</p>
<ul>
<li><code>(x, y)</code> tuple indexing: <code>frame[(x, y)]</code></li>
<li>Row-major array indexing: <code>frame[y][x]</code></li>
</ul>
<p>Tuple indexing matches display coordinates. Array indexing matches the underlying storage.</p>
<h3 id="rendering-pipeline-what-happens-when-you-display-a-frame"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#rendering-pipeline-what-happens-when-you-display-a-frame">§</a>Rendering pipeline (what happens when you display a frame)</h3>
<p><code>Frame2d</code> is only pixel storage. When you render a frame through a generated panel type,
the device abstraction:</p>
<ul>
<li>Maps <code>(x, y)</code> pixels to the physical LED wiring order</li>
<li>Applies gamma correction</li>
<li>Scales brightness to respect the configured electrical current budget</li>
</ul>
<p>These steps are implemented using two <strong>compile-time–generated lookup tables</strong>.
Writing a frame performs only indexed memory reads and writes.</p>
<h2 id="example-draw-pixels-both-directly-and-with-embedded-graphics"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#example-draw-pixels-both-directly-and-with-embedded-graphics">§</a>Example: Draw pixels both directly and with <a href="https://docs.rs/embedded-graphics"><code>embedded-graphics</code></a>:</h2>
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="LED panel preview" /></p>

<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::{led2d::Frame2d, led_strip::ToRgb888};
<span class="kw">use </span>embedded_graphics::{
    prelude::<span class="kw-2">*</span>,
    primitives::{Circle, PrimitiveStyle, Rectangle},
};
<span class="kw">use </span>smart_leds::colors;

<span class="kw">type </span>Frame = Frame2d&lt;<span class="number">12</span>, <span class="number">8</span>&gt;;

<span class="doccomment">/// Calculate the top-left corner position to center a shape within a bounding box.
</span><span class="kw">const fn </span>centered_top_left(width: usize, height: usize, size: usize) -&gt; Point {
    <span class="macro">assert!</span>(size &lt;= width);
    <span class="macro">assert!</span>(size &lt;= height);
    Point::new(((width - size) / <span class="number">2</span>) <span class="kw">as </span>i32, ((height - size) / <span class="number">2</span>) <span class="kw">as </span>i32)
}

<span class="comment">// Create a frame to draw on. This is just an in-memory 2D pixel buffer.
</span><span class="kw">let </span><span class="kw-2">mut </span>frame = Frame::new();

<span class="comment">// Use the embedded-graphics crate to draw a red rectangle border around the edge of the frame.
// We use `to_rgb888()` to convert from smart-leds RGB8 to embedded-graphics Rgb888.
</span>Rectangle::new(Frame::TOP_LEFT, Frame::SIZE)
    .into_styled(PrimitiveStyle::with_stroke(colors::RED.to_rgb888(), <span class="number">1</span>))
    .draw(<span class="kw-2">&amp;mut </span>frame)
    .expect(<span class="string">"rectangle draw must succeed"</span>);

<span class="comment">// Direct pixel access: set the upper-left LED pixel (x = 0, y = 0).
// Frame2d stores LED colors directly, so we write an LED color here.
</span>frame[(<span class="number">0</span>, <span class="number">0</span>)] = colors::CYAN;

<span class="comment">// Use the embedded-graphics crate to draw a green circle centered in the frame.
</span><span class="kw">const </span>DIAMETER: u32 = <span class="number">6</span>;
<span class="kw">const </span>CIRCLE_TOP_LEFT: Point = centered_top_left(Frame::WIDTH, Frame::HEIGHT, DIAMETER <span class="kw">as </span>usize);
Circle::new(CIRCLE_TOP_LEFT, DIAMETER)
    .into_styled(PrimitiveStyle::with_stroke(colors::LIME.to_rgb888(), <span class="number">1</span>))
    .draw(<span class="kw-2">&amp;mut </span>frame)
    .expect(<span class="string">"circle draw must succeed"</span>);</code></pre></div></div></details><h2 id="fields" class="fields section-header">Tuple Fields<a href="#fields" class="anchor">§</a></h2><span id="structfield.0" class="structfield section-header"><a href="#structfield.0" class="anchor field">§</a><code>0: [[<a class="type" href="../led_strip/type.RGB8.html" title="type device_kit::led_strip::RGB8">RGB8</a>; <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.array.html">W</a>]; <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.array.html">H</a>]</code></span><h2 id="implementations" class="section-header">Implementations<a href="#implementations" class="anchor">§</a></h2><div id="implementations-list"><details class="toggle implementors-toggle" open><summary><section id="impl-Frame2d%3CW,+H%3E" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/led2d.rs.html#519-558">Source</a><a href="#impl-Frame2d%3CW,+H%3E" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;const W: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.usize.html">usize</a>, const H: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.usize.html">usize</a>&gt; <a class="struct" href="struct.Frame2d.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::Frame2d">Frame2d</a>&lt;W, H&gt;</h3></section></summary><div class="impl-items"><details class="toggle" open><summary><section id="associatedconstant.WIDTH" class="associatedconstant"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/led2d.rs.html#521">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub const <a href="#associatedconstant.WIDTH" class="constant">WIDTH</a>: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.usize.html">usize</a> = W</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>The width of the frame.</p>

</div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#767-769">Source</a><a href="#impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;T, U&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html" title="trait core::convert::Into">Into</a>&lt;U&gt; for T<div class="where">where
    U: <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt;,</div></h3></section></summary><div class="impl-items"><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.into" class="method trait-impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#777">Source</a><a href="#method.into" class="anchor">§</a><h4 class="code-header">fn <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html#tymethod.into" class="fn">into</a>(self) -&gt; U</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Calls <code>U::from(self)</code>.</p>
<p>That is, this conversion is whatever the implementation of
<code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt; for U</code> chooses to do.</p>

class="width-limiter"><section id="main-content" class="content"><div class="main-heading"><div class="rustdoc-breadcrumbs"><a href="../index.html">device_kit</a>::<wbr><a href="index.html">led2d</a></div><h1>Struct <span class="struct">Point</span>&nbsp;<button id="copy-path" title="Copy item path to clipboard">Copy item path</button></h1><rustdoc-toolbar></rustdoc-toolbar><span class="sub-heading"></span></div><pre class="rust item-decl"><code>pub struct Point {
    pub x: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.i32.html">i32</a>,
    pub y: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.i32.html">i32</a>,
}</code></pre><details class="toggle top-doc" open><summary class="hideme"><span>Expand description</span></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Re-exported from the <a href="https://docs.rs/embedded-graphics"><code>embedded-graphics</code></a> crate.</p>
<h2 id="embedded-graphicssize-documentation"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#embedded-graphicssize-documentation">§</a><a href="https://docs.rs/embedded-graphics/latest/embedded_graphics/geometry/struct.Point.html"><code>embedded-graphics::Size</code></a> Documentation:</h2>
<p>2D point.</p>
<p>A point can be used to define the position of a graphics object. For example, a <a href="crate::primitives::rectangle::Rectangle"><code>Rectangle</code></a>
may be defined that has its top left corner at <code>(-1, -2)</code>. To specify the size of an object
<a href="struct.Size.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::Size"><code>Size</code></a> should be used instead.</p>
<p><a href="https://docs.rs/nalgebra">Nalgebra</a> support can be enabled with the <code>nalgebra_support</code> feature. This implements
<code>From&lt;Vector2&lt;N&gt;&gt;</code> and <code>From&lt;&amp;Vector2&lt;N&gt;&gt;</code> where <code>N</code> is <code>Scalar + Into&lt;i32&gt;</code>. This allows use
of Nalgebra’s <a href="https://docs.rs/nalgebra/0.18.0/nalgebra/base/type.Vector2.html"><code>Vector2</code></a> with embedded-graphics where <code>i8</code>, <code>i16</code>, <code>i32</code>, <code>u16</code> or <code>u8</code> is used
for value storage.</p>
<h2 id="examples"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#examples">§</a>Examples</h2><h3 id="create-a-point-from-two-integers"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#create-a-point-from-two-integers">§</a>Create a <code>Point</code> from two integers</h3>
<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>embedded_graphics::geometry::Point;

<span class="comment">// Create a coord using the `new` constructor method
</span><span class="kw">let </span>p = Point::new(<span class="number">10</span>, <span class="number">20</span>);</code></pre></div><h3 id="create-a-point-from-a-nalgebra-vector2"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#create-a-point-from-a-nalgebra-vector2">§</a>Create a <code>Point</code> from a Nalgebra <code>Vector2</code></h3>
<p><em>Be sure to enable the <code>nalgebra_support</code> feature to get <a href="https://docs.rs/nalgebra">Nalgebra</a> integration.</em></p>

<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>embedded_graphics::geometry::Point;
<span class="kw">use </span>nalgebra::Vector2;

<span class="kw">let </span>n_coord = Vector2::new(<span class="number">10i32</span>, <span class="number">20</span>);

<span class="macro">assert_eq!</span>(Point::from(n_coord), Point::new(<span class="number">10</span>, <span class="number">20</span>));</code></pre></div><h3 id="convert-a-vector2u8-into-a-point"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#convert-a-vector2u8-into-a-point">§</a>Convert a <code>Vector2&lt;u8&gt;</code> into a <code>Point</code></h3>
<p><em>Be sure to enable the <code>nalgebra_support</code> feature to get <a href="https://docs.rs/nalgebra">Nalgebra</a> integration.</em></p>
<p>Smaller unsigned types that can be converted to <code>i32</code> are also supported in conversions.</p>

<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>embedded_graphics::geometry::Point;
<span class="kw">use </span>nalgebra::Vector2;

<span class="kw">let </span>n_coord = Vector2::new(<span class="number">10u8</span>, <span class="number">20</span>);

<span class="macro">assert_eq!</span>(Point::from(n_coord), Point::new(<span class="number">10</span>, <span class="number">20</span>));</code></pre></div></div></details><h2 id="fields" class="fields section-header">Fields<a href="#fields" class="anchor">§</a></h2><span id="structfield.x" class="structfield section-header"><a href="#structfield.x" class="anchor field">§</a><code>x: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.i32.html">i32</a></code></span><div class="docblock"><p>The x coordinate.</p>
</div><span id="structfield.y" class="structfield section-header"><a href="#structfield.y" class="anchor field">§</a><code>y: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.i32.html">i32</a></code></span><div class="docblock"><p>The y coordinate.</p>
</div><h2 id="implementations" class="section-header">Implementations<a href="#implementations" class="anchor">§</a></h2><div id="implementations-list"><details class="toggle implementors-toggle" open><summary><section id="impl-Point" class="impl"><a href="#impl-Point" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl <a class="struct" href="struct.Point.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::Point">Point</a></h3></section></summary><div class="impl-items"><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.new" class="method"><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.new" class="fn">new</a>(x: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.i32.html">i32</a>, y: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.i32.html">i32</a>) -&gt; <a class="struct" href="struct.Point.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::Point">Point</a></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Creates a point from  X and Y coordinates.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.new_equal" class="method"><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.new_equal" class="fn">new_equal</a>(value: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.i32.html">i32</a>) -&gt; <a class="struct" href="struct.Point.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::Point">Point</a></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Creates a point with X and Y values set to an equal value.</p>
<h5 id="examples-1"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#examples-1">§</a>Examples</h5>
<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>embedded_graphics::geometry::Point;

<span class="kw">let </span>point = Point::new_equal(<span class="number">11</span>);

<span class="macro">assert_eq!</span>(point, Point { x: <span class="number">11</span>, y: <span class="number">11 </span>});</code></pre></div></div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.zero" class="method"><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.zero" class="fn">zero</a>() -&gt; <a class="struct" href="struct.Point.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::Point">Point</a></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Creates a point with X and Y equal to zero.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.x_axis" class="method"><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.x_axis" class="fn">x_axis</a>(self) -&gt; <a class="struct" href="struct.Point.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::Point">Point</a></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Returns a point with equal <code>x</code> value and <code>y</code> set to <code>0</code>.</p>
<h5 id="examples-2"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#examples-2">§</a>Examples</h5><h6 id="move-a-point-along-the-x-axis"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#move-a-point-along-the-x-axis">§</a>Move a <code>Point</code> along the X axis.</h6>
<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>embedded_graphics::geometry::Point;

<span class="kw">let </span>translate = Point::new(<span class="number">20</span>, <span class="number">30</span>);

<span class="kw">let </span>point = Point::new(<span class="number">10</span>, <span class="number">15</span>);

<span class="kw">let </span>moved_x = point + translate.x_axis();

<span class="macro">assert_eq!</span>(moved_x, Point::new(<span class="number">30</span>, <span class="number">15</span>));</code></pre></div></div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.y_axis" class="method"><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.y_axis" class="fn">y_axis</a>(self) -&gt; <a class="struct" href="struct.Point.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::Point">Point</a></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Returns a point with equal <code>y</code> value and <code>x</code> set to <code>0</code>.</p>
<h5 id="examples-3"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#examples-3">§</a>Examples</h5><h6 id="move-a-point-along-the-y-axis"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#move-a-point-along-the-y-axis">§</a>Move a <code>Point</code> along the Y axis.</h6>

<h5 id="panics"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#panics">§</a>Panics</h5>
<p>Panics if one of the components of <code>other</code> equals zero.</p>

<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>embedded_graphics::geometry::Point;

<span class="kw">let </span>result = Point::new(<span class="number">20</span>, <span class="number">30</span>).component_div(Point::new(<span class="number">10</span>, -<span class="number">3</span>));

<span class="macro">assert_eq!</span>(result, Point::new(<span class="number">2</span>, -<span class="number">10</span>));</code></pre></div></div></details></div></details></div><h2 id="trait-implementations" class="section-header">Trait Implementations<a href="#trait-implementations" class="anchor">§</a></h2><div id="trait-implementations-list"><details class="toggle implementors-toggle" open><summary><section id="impl-Add%3CSize%3E-for-Point" class="impl"><a href="#impl-Add%3CSize%3E-for-Point" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/ops/arith/trait.Add.html" title="trait core::ops::arith::Add">Add</a>&lt;<a class="struct" href="struct.Size.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::Size">Size</a>&gt; for <a class="struct" href="struct.Point.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::Point">Point</a></h3></section></summary><div class="impl-items"><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.add-1" class="method trait-impl"><a href="#method.add-1" class="anchor">§</a><h4 class="code-header">fn <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/ops/arith/trait.Add.html#tymethod.add" class="fn">add</a>(self, other: <a class="struct" href="struct.Size.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::Size">Size</a>) -&gt; <a class="struct" href="struct.Point.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::Point">Point</a></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Offsets a point by adding a size.</p>

<h5 id="panics-3"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#panics-3">§</a>Panics</h5>
<p>This function will panic if <code>width</code> or <code>height</code> are too large to be represented as an <code>i32</code>
and debug assertions are enabled.</p>

(<code>clone_to_uninit</code>)</span></div></span><div class='docblock'>Performs copy-assignment from <code>self</code> to <code>dest</code>. <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/clone/trait.CloneToUninit.html#tymethod.clone_to_uninit">Read more</a></div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-From%3CT%3E-for-T" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#785">Source</a><a href="#impl-From%3CT%3E-for-T" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;T&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt; for T</h3></section></summary><div class="impl-items"><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.from-4" class="method trait-impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#788">Source</a><a href="#method.from-4" class="anchor">§</a><h4 class="code-header">fn <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html#tymethod.from" class="fn">from</a>(t: T) -&gt; T</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Returns the argument unchanged.</p>
</div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#767-769">Source</a><a href="#impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;T, U&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html" title="trait core::convert::Into">Into</a>&lt;U&gt; for T<div class="where">where
    U: <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt;,</div></h3></section></summary><div class="impl-items"><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.into" class="method trait-impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#777">Source</a><a href="#method.into" class="anchor">§</a><h4 class="code-header">fn <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html#tymethod.into" class="fn">into</a>(self) -&gt; U</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Calls <code>U::from(self)</code>.</p>
<p>That is, this conversion is whatever the implementation of
<code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt; for U</code> chooses to do.</p>

    Dst: <a class="trait" href="https://docs.rs/fixed/~1.28/fixed/traits/trait.LosslessTryFrom.html" title="trait fixed::traits::LosslessTryFrom">LosslessTryFrom</a>&lt;Src&gt;,</div></h3></section></summary><div class="impl-items"><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.lossless_try_into" class="method trait-impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://docs.rs/fixed/~1.28/src/fixed/traits.rs.html#3664">Source</a><a href="#method.lossless_try_into" class="anchor">§</a><h4 class="code-header">fn <a href="https://docs.rs/fixed/~1.28/fixed/traits/trait.LosslessTryInto.html#tymethod.lossless_try_into" class="fn">lossless_try_into</a>(self) -&gt; <a class="enum" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/option/enum.Option.html" title="enum core::option::Option">Option</a>&lt;Dst&gt;</h4></section></summary><div class='docblock'>Performs the conversion.</div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-LossyInto%3CDst%3E-for-Src" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://docs.rs/fixed/~1.28/src/fixed/traits.rs.html#3711-3713">Source</a><a href="#impl-LossyInto%3CDst%3E-for-Src" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;Src, Dst&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://docs.rs/fixed/~1.28/fixed/traits/trait.LossyInto.html" title="trait fixed::traits::LossyInto">LossyInto</a>&lt;Dst&gt; for Src<div class="where">where
