device_<wbr>kit::<wbr>led2d</a></h2></div></div></nav><div class="sidebar-resizer" title="Drag to resize sidebar"></div><main><div class="width-limiter"><section id="main-content" class="content"><div class="main-heading"><div class="rustdoc-breadcrumbs"><a href="../index.html">device_kit</a>::<wbr><a href="index.html">led2d</a></div><h1>Struct <span class="struct">Size</span>&nbsp;<button id="copy-path" title="Copy item path to clipboard">Copy item path</button></h1><rustdoc-toolbar></rustdoc-toolbar><span class="sub-heading"></span></div><pre class="rust item-decl"><code>pub struct Size {
    pub width: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.u32.html">u32</a>,
    pub height: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.u32.html">u32</a>,
}</code></pre><details class="toggle top-doc" open><summary class="hideme"><span>Expand description</span></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Re-exported from the <a href="https://docs.rs/embedded-graphics"><code>embedded-graphics</code></a> crate.</p>
<h2 id="embedded-graphicssize-documentation"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#embedded-graphicssize-documentation">§</a><a href="https://docs.rs/embedded-graphics/latest/embedded_graphics/geometry/struct.Size.html"><code>embedded-graphics::Size</code></a> Documentation:</h2>
<p>2D size.</p>
<p><code>Size</code> is used to define the width and height of an object.</p>
<p><a href="https://docs.rs/nalgebra">Nalgebra</a> support can be enabled with the <code>nalgebra_support</code> feature. This implements
<code>From&lt;Vector2&lt;N&gt;&gt;</code> and <code>From&lt;&amp;Vector2&lt;N&gt;&gt;</code> where <code>N</code> is <code>Scalar + Into&lt;u32&gt;</code>. This allows use
of Nalgebra’s <a href="https://docs.rs/nalgebra/0.18.0/nalgebra/base/type.Vector2.html"><code>Vector2</code></a> with embedded-graphics where <code>u32</code>, <code>u16</code> or <code>u8</code> is used for value
storage.</p>
<h2 id="examples"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#examples">§</a>Examples</h2><h3 id="create-a-size-from-two-integers"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#create-a-size-from-two-integers">§</a>Create a <code>Size</code> from two integers</h3>
<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>embedded_graphics::geometry::Size;

<span class="comment">// Create a size using the `new` constructor method
</span><span class="kw">let </span>s = Size::new(<span class="number">10</span>, <span class="number">20</span>);</code></pre></div><h3 id="create-a-size-from-a-nalgebra-vector2"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#create-a-size-from-a-nalgebra-vector2">§</a>Create a <code>Size</code> from a Nalgebra <code>Vector2</code></h3>
<p><em>Be sure to enable the <code>nalgebra_support</code> feature to get <a href="https://docs.rs/nalgebra">Nalgebra</a> integration.</em></p>
<p>Any <code>Vector2&lt;N&gt;</code> can be used where <code>N: Into&lt;u32&gt; + nalgebra::Scalar</code>. This includes the primitive types <code>u32</code>, <code>u16</code> and <code>u8</code>.</p>

<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>embedded_graphics::geometry::Size;
<span class="kw">use </span>nalgebra::Vector2;

<span class="macro">assert_eq!</span>(Size::from(Vector2::new(<span class="number">10u32</span>, <span class="number">20</span>)), Size::new(<span class="number">10u32</span>, <span class="number">20</span>));
<span class="macro">assert_eq!</span>(Size::from(Vector2::new(<span class="number">10u16</span>, <span class="number">20</span>)), Size::new(<span class="number">10u32</span>, <span class="number">20</span>));
<span class="macro">assert_eq!</span>(Size::from(Vector2::new(<span class="number">10u8</span>, <span class="number">20</span>)), Size::new(<span class="number">10u32</span>, <span class="number">20</span>));</code></pre></div>
<p><code>.into()</code> can also be used, but may require more type annotations:</p>

<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>embedded_graphics::geometry::Size;
<span class="kw">use </span>nalgebra::Vector2;

<span class="kw">let </span>c: Size = Vector2::new(<span class="number">10u32</span>, <span class="number">20</span>).into();

<span class="macro">assert_eq!</span>(c, Size::new(<span class="number">10u32</span>, <span class="number">20</span>));</code></pre></div></div></details><h2 id="fields" class="fields section-header">Fields<a href="#fields" class="anchor">§</a></h2><span id="structfield.width" class="structfield section-header"><a href="#structfield.width" class="anchor field">§</a><code>width: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.u32.html">u32</a></code></span><div class="docblock"><p>The width.</p>
</div><span id="structfield.height" class="structfield section-header"><a href="#structfield.height" class="anchor field">§</a><code>height: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.u32.html">u32</a></code></span><div class="docblock"><p>The height.</p>
</div><h2 id="implementations" class="section-header">Implementations<a href="#implementations" class="anchor">§</a></h2><div id="implementations-list"><details class="toggle implementors-toggle" open><summary><section id="impl-Size" class="impl"><a href="#impl-Size" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl <a class="struct" href="struct.Size.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::Size">Size</a></h3></section></summary><div class="impl-items"><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.new" class="method"><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.new" class="fn">new</a>(width: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.u32.html">u32</a>, height: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.u32.html">u32</a>) -&gt; <a class="struct" href="struct.Size.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::Size">Size</a></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Creates a size from a width and a height.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.new_equal" class="method"><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.new_equal" class="fn">new_equal</a>(value: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.u32.html">u32</a>) -&gt; <a class="struct" href="struct.Size.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::Size">Size</a></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Creates a size with width and height set to an equal value.</p>

<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>embedded_graphics::geometry::Size;

<span class="macro">assert_eq!</span>(
    size,
    Size {
        width: <span class="number">11</span>,
        height: <span class="number">11
    </span>}
);</code></pre></div></div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.zero" class="method"><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.zero" class="fn">zero</a>() -&gt; <a class="struct" href="struct.Size.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::Size">Size</a></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Creates a size with width and height equal to zero.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.x_axis" class="method"><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.x_axis" class="fn">x_axis</a>(self) -&gt; <a class="struct" href="struct.Size.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::Size">Size</a></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Returns a size with equal <code>width</code> value and <code>height</code> set to <code>0</code>.</p>
<h5 id="examples-1"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#examples-1">§</a>Examples</h5><h6 id="move-a-point-along-the-x-axis"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#move-a-point-along-the-x-axis">§</a>Move a <code>Point</code> along the X axis.</h6>
<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>embedded_graphics::geometry::{Point, Size};

<span class="kw">let </span>size = Size::new(<span class="number">20</span>, <span class="number">30</span>);

<span class="kw">let </span>point = Point::new(<span class="number">10</span>, <span class="number">15</span>);

<span class="kw">let </span>moved_x = point + size.x_axis();

<span class="macro">assert_eq!</span>(moved_x, Point::new(<span class="number">30</span>, <span class="number">15</span>));</code></pre></div></div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.y_axis" class="method"><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.y_axis" class="fn">y_axis</a>(self) -&gt; <a class="struct" href="struct.Size.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::Size">Size</a></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Returns a size with equal <code>height</code> value and <code>width</code> set to <code>0</code>.</p>
<h5 id="examples-2"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#examples-2">§</a>Examples</h5><h6 id="move-a-point-along-the-y-axis"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#move-a-point-along-the-y-axis">§</a>Move a <code>Point</code> along the Y axis.</h6>
<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>embedded_graphics::geometry::{Point, Size};

<span class="kw">let </span>size = Size::new(<span class="number">20</span>, <span class="number">30</span>);

<span class="kw">let </span>point = Point::new(<span class="number">10</span>, <span class="number">15</span>);

<span class="kw">let </span>moved_y = point + size.y_axis();

<span class="macro">assert_eq!</span>(moved_y, Point::new(<span class="number">10</span>, <span class="number">45</span>));</code></pre></div></div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.saturating_add" class="method"><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.saturating_add" class="fn">saturating_add</a>(self, other: <a class="struct" href="struct.Size.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::Size">Size</a>) -&gt; <a class="struct" href="struct.Size.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::Size">Size</a></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Saturating addition.</p>
<p>Returns <code>u32::max_value()</code> for <code>width</code> and/or <code>height</code> instead of overflowing.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.saturating_sub" class="method"><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.saturating_sub" class="fn">saturating_sub</a>(self, other: <a class="struct" href="struct.Size.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::Size">Size</a>) -&gt; <a class="struct" href="struct.Size.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::Size">Size</a></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Saturating subtraction.</p>
<p>Returns <code>0</code> for <code>width</code> and/or <code>height</code> instead of overflowing, if the
value in <code>other</code> is larger then in <code>self</code>.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.component_min" class="method"><h4 class="code-header">pub fn <a href="#method.component_min" class="fn">component_min</a>(self, other: <a class="struct" href="struct.Size.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::Size">Size</a>) -&gt; <a class="struct" href="struct.Size.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::Size">Size</a></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Returns the componentwise minimum of two <code>Size</code>s.</p>

<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>embedded_graphics::geometry::Size;

<span class="kw">let </span>min = Size::new(<span class="number">20</span>, <span class="number">30</span>).component_min(Size::new(<span class="number">15</span>, <span class="number">50</span>));

<span class="macro">assert_eq!</span>(min, Size::new(<span class="number">15</span>, <span class="number">30</span>));</code></pre></div></div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.component_max" class="method"><h4 class="code-header">pub fn <a href="#method.component_max" class="fn">component_max</a>(self, other: <a class="struct" href="struct.Size.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::Size">Size</a>) -&gt; <a class="struct" href="struct.Size.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::Size">Size</a></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Returns the componentwise maximum of two <code>Size</code>s.</p>

<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>embedded_graphics::geometry::Size;

<span class="kw">let </span>min = Size::new(<span class="number">20</span>, <span class="number">30</span>).component_max(Size::new(<span class="number">15</span>, <span class="number">50</span>));

<span class="macro">assert_eq!</span>(min, Size::new(<span class="number">20</span>, <span class="number">50</span>));</code></pre></div></div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.component_mul" class="method"><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.component_mul" class="fn">component_mul</a>(self, other: <a class="struct" href="struct.Size.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::Size">Size</a>) -&gt; <a class="struct" href="struct.Size.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::Size">Size</a></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Returns the componentwise multiplication of two <code>Size</code>s.</p>

<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>embedded_graphics::geometry::Size;

<span class="kw">let </span>result = Size::new(<span class="number">20</span>, <span class="number">30</span>).component_mul(Size::new(<span class="number">2</span>, <span class="number">3</span>));

<span class="macro">assert_eq!</span>(result, Size::new(<span class="number">40</span>, <span class="number">90</span>));</code></pre></div></div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.component_div" class="method"><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.component_div" class="fn">component_div</a>(self, other: <a class="struct" href="struct.Size.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::Size">Size</a>) -&gt; <a class="struct" href="struct.Size.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::Size">Size</a></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Returns the componentwise division of two <code>Size</code>s.</p>
<h5 id="panics"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#panics">§</a>Panics</h5>
<p>Panics if one of the components of <code>other</code> equals zero.</p>

<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>embedded_graphics::geometry::Size;

<span class="kw">let </span>result = Size::new(<span class="number">20</span>, <span class="number">30</span>).component_div(Size::new(<span class="number">5</span>, <span class="number">10</span>));

<span class="macro">assert_eq!</span>(result, Size::new(<span class="number">4</span>, <span class="number">3</span>));</code></pre></div></div></details></div></details></div><h2 id="trait-implementations" class="section-header">Trait Implementations<a href="#trait-implementations" class="anchor">§</a></h2><div id="trait-implementations-list"><details class="toggle implementors-toggle" open><summary><section id="impl-Add%3CSize%3E-for-Point" class="impl"><a href="#impl-Add%3CSize%3E-for-Point" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/ops/arith/trait.Add.html" title="trait core::ops::arith::Add">Add</a>&lt;<a class="struct" href="struct.Size.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::Size">Size</a>&gt; for <a class="struct" href="struct.Point.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::Point">Point</a></h3></section></summary><div class="impl-items"><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.add" class="method trait-impl"><a href="#method.add" class="anchor">§</a><h4 class="code-header">fn <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/ops/arith/trait.Add.html#tymethod.add" class="fn">add</a>(self, other: <a class="struct" href="struct.Size.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::Size">Size</a>) -&gt; <a class="struct" href="struct.Point.html" title="struct device_kit::led2d::Point">Point</a></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Offsets a point by adding a size.</p>
<h5 id="panics-1"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#panics-1">§</a>Panics</h5>

and debug assertions are enabled.</p>

<h5 id="panics-3"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#panics-3">§</a>Panics</h5>
<p>This function will panic if <code>width</code> or <code>height</code> are too large to be represented as an <code>i32</code>
and debug assertions are enabled.</p>

<h5 id="panics-4"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#panics-4">§</a>Panics</h5>
<p>This function will panic if <code>width</code> or <code>height</code> are too large to be represented as an <code>i32</code>
and debug assertions are enabled.</p>

</div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#767-769">Source</a><a href="#impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;T, U&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html" title="trait core::convert::Into">Into</a>&lt;U&gt; for T<div class="where">where
    U: <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt;,</div></h3></section></summary><div class="impl-items"><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.into" class="method trait-impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#777">Source</a><a href="#method.into" class="anchor">§</a><h4 class="code-header">fn <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html#tymethod.into" class="fn">into</a>(self) -&gt; U</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Calls <code>U::from(self)</code>.</p>
<p>That is, this conversion is whatever the implementation of
<code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt; for U</code> chooses to do.</p>
</div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-LosslessTryInto%3CDst%3E-for-Src" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://docs.rs/fixed/~1.28/src/fixed/traits.rs.html#3660-3662">Source</a><a href="#impl-LosslessTryInto%3CDst%3E-for-Src" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;Src, Dst&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://docs.rs/fixed/~1.28/fixed/traits/trait.LosslessTryInto.html" title="trait fixed::traits::LosslessTryInto">LosslessTryInto</a>&lt;Dst&gt; for Src<div class="where">where

id="rustdoc-modnav"><h2><a href="index.html">In device_<wbr>kit::<wbr>led4</a></h2></div></div></nav><div class="sidebar-resizer" title="Drag to resize sidebar"></div><main><div class="width-limiter"><section id="main-content" class="content"><div class="main-heading"><div class="rustdoc-breadcrumbs"><a href="../index.html">device_kit</a>::<wbr><a href="index.html">led4</a></div><h1>Enum <span class="enum">Blink<wbr>State</span>&nbsp;<button id="copy-path" title="Copy item path to clipboard">Copy item path</button></h1><rustdoc-toolbar></rustdoc-toolbar><span class="sub-heading"><a class="src" href="../../src/device_kit/led4.rs.html#66-71">Source</a> </span></div><pre class="rust item-decl"><code>pub enum BlinkState {
    Solid,
    BlinkingAndOn,
    BlinkingButOff,
}</code></pre><details class="toggle top-doc" open><summary class="hideme"><span>Expand description</span></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Blinking behavior for 4-digit LED displays.</p>
<p>Used with <a href="struct.Led4.html#method.write_text" title="method device_kit::led4::Led4::write_text"><code>Led4::write_text()</code></a> to control whether the display blinks.
See the <a href="struct.Led4.html" title="struct device_kit::led4::Led4"><code>Led4</code></a> documentation for usage examples.</p>

</div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#767-769">Source</a><a href="#impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;T, U&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html" title="trait core::convert::Into">Into</a>&lt;U&gt; for T<div class="where">where

<p>That is, this conversion is whatever the implementation of
<code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt; for U</code> chooses to do.</p>

device_<wbr>kit::<wbr>led4</a></h2></div></div></nav><div class="sidebar-resizer" title="Drag to resize sidebar"></div><main><div class="width-limiter"><section id="main-content" class="content"><div class="main-heading"><div class="rustdoc-breadcrumbs"><a href="../index.html">device_kit</a>::<wbr><a href="index.html">led4</a></div><h1>Function <span class="fn">circular_<wbr>outline_<wbr>animation</span>&nbsp;<button id="copy-path" title="Copy item path to clipboard">Copy item path</button></h1><rustdoc-toolbar></rustdoc-toolbar><span class="sub-heading"><a class="src" href="../../src/device_kit/led4.rs.html#358-389">Source</a> </span></div><pre class="rust item-decl"><code>pub fn circular_outline_animation(
    clockwise: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.bool.html">bool</a>,
) -&gt; Vec&lt;<a class="struct" href="struct.AnimationFrame.html" title="struct device_kit::led4::AnimationFrame">AnimationFrame</a>, ANIMATION_MAX_FRAMES&gt;</code></pre><details class="toggle top-doc" open><summary class="hideme"><span>Expand description</span></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Creates a circular outline animation that chases around the edges of the display.</p>
<p>Returns an animation with 8 frames showing a segment moving clockwise or
counter-clockwise around the perimeter of the 4-digit display.</p>
<h2 id="arguments"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#arguments">§</a>Arguments</h2>
<ul>
<li><code>clockwise</code> - If <code>true</code>, animates clockwise; if <code>false</code>, counter-clockwise</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="example"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#example">§</a>Example</h2>
<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::led4::{Led4, circular_outline_animation};

<span class="kw">async fn </span>example(led4: <span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>Led4&lt;<span class="lifetime">'_</span>&gt;) {
    <span class="comment">// Animate clockwise
    </span>led4.animate_text(circular_outline_animation(<span class="bool-val">true</span>));

    <span class="comment">// Animate counter-clockwise
    </span>led4.animate_text(circular_outline_animation(<span class="bool-val">false</span>));
}</code></pre></div></div></details></section></div></main></body></html>

open><summary class="hideme"><span>Expand description</span></summary><div class="docblock"><p>A device abstraction for a 4-digit, 7-segment LED display for text with optional animation and blinking.</p>
<p>See <a href="struct.Led4.html" title="struct device_kit::led4::Led4"><code>Led4</code></a> for the primary text/blinking example and <a href="struct.Led4.html#method.animate_text" title="method device_kit::led4::Led4::animate_text"><code>Led4::animate_text</code></a> for the animation example.</p>
<p>This module provides device abstraction for controlling common-cathode
4-digit 7-segment LED displays. Supports displaying text and numbers with
optional blinking.</p>

    pub text: [<a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.char.html">char</a>; <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.array.html">4</a>],

}</code></pre><details class="toggle top-doc" open><summary class="hideme"><span>Expand description</span></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Frame of animated text for <a href="struct.Led4.html#method.animate_text" title="method device_kit::led4::Led4::animate_text"><code>Led4::animate_text</code></a>. See that method’s example for usage.</p>

(<code>clone_to_uninit</code>)</span></div></span><div class='docblock'>Performs copy-assignment from <code>self</code> to <code>dest</code>. <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/clone/trait.CloneToUninit.html#tymethod.clone_to_uninit">Read more</a></div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-From%3CT%3E-for-T" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#785">Source</a><a href="#impl-From%3CT%3E-for-T" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;T&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt; for T</h3></section></summary><div class="impl-items"><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.from" class="method trait-impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#788">Source</a><a href="#method.from" class="anchor">§</a><h4 class="code-header">fn <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html#tymethod.from" class="fn">from</a>(t: T) -&gt; T</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Returns the argument unchanged.</p>
</div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#767-769">Source</a><a href="#impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;T, U&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html" title="trait core::convert::Into">Into</a>&lt;U&gt; for T<div class="where">where
    U: <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt;,</div></h3></section></summary><div class="impl-items"><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.into" class="method trait-impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#777">Source</a><a href="#method.into" class="anchor">§</a><h4 class="code-header">fn <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html#tymethod.into" class="fn">into</a>(self) -&gt; U</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Calls <code>U::from(self)</code>.</p>
<p>That is, this conversion is whatever the implementation of
<code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt; for U</code> chooses to do.</p>
</div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-LosslessTryInto%3CDst%3E-for-Src" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://docs.rs/fixed/~1.28/src/fixed/traits.rs.html#3660-3662">Source</a><a href="#impl-LosslessTryInto%3CDst%3E-for-Src" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;Src, Dst&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://docs.rs/fixed/~1.28/fixed/traits/trait.LosslessTryInto.html" title="trait fixed::traits::LosslessTryInto">LosslessTryInto</a>&lt;Dst&gt; for Src<div class="where">where
    Dst: <a class="trait" href="https://docs.rs/fixed/~1.28/fixed/traits/trait.LosslessTryFrom.html" title="trait fixed::traits::LosslessTryFrom">LosslessTryFrom</a>&lt;Src&gt;,</div></h3></section></summary><div class="impl-items"><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.lossless_try_into" class="method trait-impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://docs.rs/fixed/~1.28/src/fixed/traits.rs.html#3664">Source</a><a href="#method.lossless_try_into" class="anchor">§</a><h4 class="code-header">fn <a href="https://docs.rs/fixed/~1.28/fixed/traits/trait.LosslessTryInto.html#tymethod.lossless_try_into" class="fn">lossless_try_into</a>(self) -&gt; <a class="enum" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/option/enum.Option.html" title="enum core::option::Option">Option</a>&lt;Dst&gt;</h4></section></summary><div class='docblock'>Performs the conversion.</div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-LossyInto%3CDst%3E-for-Src" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://docs.rs/fixed/~1.28/src/fixed/traits.rs.html#3711-3713">Source</a><a href="#impl-LossyInto%3CDst%3E-for-Src" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;Src, Dst&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://docs.rs/fixed/~1.28/fixed/traits/trait.LossyInto.html" title="trait fixed::traits::LossyInto">LossyInto</a>&lt;Dst&gt; for Src<div class="where">where

id="rustdoc-modnav"><h2><a href="index.html">In device_<wbr>kit::<wbr>led4</a></h2></div></div></nav><div class="sidebar-resizer" title="Drag to resize sidebar"></div><main><div class="width-limiter"><section id="main-content" class="content"><div class="main-heading"><div class="rustdoc-breadcrumbs"><a href="../index.html">device_kit</a>::<wbr><a href="index.html">led4</a></div><h1>Struct <span class="struct">Led4</span>&nbsp;<button id="copy-path" title="Copy item path to clipboard">Copy item path</button></h1><rustdoc-toolbar></rustdoc-toolbar><span class="sub-heading"><a class="src" href="../../src/device_kit/led4.rs.html#156">Source</a> </span></div><pre class="rust item-decl"><code>pub struct Led4&lt;'a&gt;(<span class="comment">/* private fields */</span>);</code></pre><details class="toggle top-doc" open><summary class="hideme"><span>Expand description</span></summary><div class="docblock"><p>A device abstraction for a 4-digit, 7-segment LED display with blinking support.</p>
<h2 id="hardware-requirements"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#hardware-requirements">§</a>Hardware Requirements</h2>
<p>This abstraction is designed for common-cathode 7-segment displays where:</p>
<ul>
<li>Cell pins control which digit is active (LOW = on, HIGH = off)</li>
<li>Segment pins control which segments light up (HIGH = on, LOW = off)</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="example"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#example">§</a>Example</h2>
<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::{Error, led4::{BlinkState, Led4, Led4Static, OutputArray}};

<span class="kw">async fn </span>example(p: embassy_rp::Peripherals, spawner: embassy_executor::Spawner) -&gt; <span class="prelude-ty">Result</span>&lt;(), Error&gt; {
    <span class="comment">// Set up cell pins (control which digit is active)
    </span><span class="kw">let </span>cells = OutputArray::new([
        embassy_rp::gpio::Output::new(p.PIN_1, embassy_rp::gpio::Level::High),
        embassy_rp::gpio::Output::new(p.PIN_2, embassy_rp::gpio::Level::High),
        embassy_rp::gpio::Output::new(p.PIN_3, embassy_rp::gpio::Level::High),
        embassy_rp::gpio::Output::new(p.PIN_4, embassy_rp::gpio::Level::High),
    ]);

    <span class="comment">// Set up segment pins (control which segments light up)
    </span><span class="kw">let </span>segments = OutputArray::new([
        embassy_rp::gpio::Output::new(p.PIN_5, embassy_rp::gpio::Level::Low),  <span class="comment">// Segment A
        </span>embassy_rp::gpio::Output::new(p.PIN_6, embassy_rp::gpio::Level::Low),  <span class="comment">// Segment B
        </span>embassy_rp::gpio::Output::new(p.PIN_7, embassy_rp::gpio::Level::Low),  <span class="comment">// Segment C
        </span>embassy_rp::gpio::Output::new(p.PIN_8, embassy_rp::gpio::Level::Low),  <span class="comment">// Segment D
        </span>embassy_rp::gpio::Output::new(p.PIN_9, embassy_rp::gpio::Level::Low),  <span class="comment">// Segment E
        </span>embassy_rp::gpio::Output::new(p.PIN_10, embassy_rp::gpio::Level::Low), <span class="comment">// Segment F
        </span>embassy_rp::gpio::Output::new(p.PIN_11, embassy_rp::gpio::Level::Low), <span class="comment">// Segment G
        </span>embassy_rp::gpio::Output::new(p.PIN_12, embassy_rp::gpio::Level::Low), <span class="comment">// Decimal point
    </span>]);

    <span class="comment">// Create the display
    </span><span class="kw">static </span>LED4_STATIC: Led4Static = Led4::new_static();
    <span class="kw">let </span>display = Led4::new(<span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>LED4_STATIC, cells, segments, spawner)<span class="question-mark">?</span>;

    <span class="comment">// Display "1234" (solid)
    </span>display.write_text([<span class="string">'1'</span>, <span class="string">'2'</span>, <span class="string">'3'</span>, <span class="string">'4'</span>], BlinkState::Solid);
     
    <span class="comment">// Display "rUSt" blinking
    </span>display.write_text([<span class="string">'r'</span>, <span class="string">'U'</span>, <span class="string">'S'</span>, <span class="string">'t'</span>], BlinkState::BlinkingAndOn);
     
    <span class="prelude-val">Ok</span>(())
}</code></pre></div>
<p>cmk should the example include animation?
Beyond simple text, the driver can loop animations via <a href="struct.Led4.html#method.animate_text" title="method device_kit::led4::Led4::animate_text"><code>Led4::animate_text</code></a>.
The struct owns the background task and signal wiring; create it once with
<a href="struct.Led4.html#method.new" title="associated function device_kit::led4::Led4::new"><code>Led4::new</code></a> and use the returned handle for all display updates.</p>
</div></details><h2 id="implementations" class="section-header">Implementations<a href="#implementations" class="anchor">§</a></h2><div id="implementations-list"><details class="toggle implementors-toggle" open><summary><section id="impl-Led4%3C'_%3E" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/led4.rs.html#180-255">Source</a><a href="#impl-Led4%3C'_%3E" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl <a class="struct" href="struct.Led4.html" title="struct device_kit::led4::Led4">Led4</a>&lt;'_&gt;</h3></section></summary><div class="impl-items"><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.new" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/led4.rs.html#183-194">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub fn <a href="#method.new" class="fn">new</a>(
    led4_static: &amp;'static <a class="struct" href="struct.Led4Static.html" title="struct device_kit::led4::Led4Static">Led4Static</a>,
    cell_pins: <a class="struct" href="struct.OutputArray.html" title="struct device_kit::led4::OutputArray">OutputArray</a>&lt;'static, CELL_COUNT&gt;,
    segment_pins: <a class="struct" href="struct.OutputArray.html" title="struct device_kit::led4::OutputArray">OutputArray</a>&lt;'static, SEGMENT_COUNT&gt;,
    spawner: Spawner,
) -&gt; <a class="type" href="../type.Result.html" title="type device_kit::Result">Result</a>&lt;Self&gt;</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Creates the display device and spawns its background task; see <a href="struct.Led4.html" title="struct device_kit::led4::Led4"><code>Led4</code></a> docs.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.new_static" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/led4.rs.html#198-200">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.new_static" class="fn">new_static</a>() -&gt; <a class="struct" href="struct.Led4Static.html" title="struct device_kit::led4::Led4Static">Led4Static</a></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Creates static channel resources for <a href="struct.Led4.html#method.new" title="associated function device_kit::led4::Led4::new"><code>Led4::new</code></a>; see <a href="struct.Led4.html" title="struct device_kit::led4::Led4"><code>Led4</code></a> docs.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.write_text" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/led4.rs.html#205-209">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub fn <a href="#method.write_text" class="fn">write_text</a>(&amp;self, text: [<a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.char.html">char</a>; <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.array.html">4</a>], blink_state: <a class="enum" href="enum.BlinkState.html" title="enum device_kit::led4::BlinkState">BlinkState</a>)</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Sends text to the display with optional blinking.</p>
<p>See the main <a href="struct.Led4.html" title="struct device_kit::led4::Led4"><code>Led4</code></a> example for end-to-end usage.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.animate_text" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/led4.rs.html#252-254">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub fn <a href="#method.animate_text" class="fn">animate_text</a>(&amp;self, animation: Vec&lt;<a class="struct" href="struct.AnimationFrame.html" title="struct device_kit::led4::AnimationFrame">AnimationFrame</a>, ANIMATION_MAX_FRAMES&gt;)</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Plays a looped text animation using the provided frames.</p>
<h5 id="example-1"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#example-1">§</a>Example</h5>
<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::{<span class="prelude-ty">Result</span>, led4::{AnimationFrame, Led4, Led4Static, OutputArray}};
<span class="kw">use </span>embassy_time::Duration;
<span class="kw">async fn </span>demo(p: embassy_rp::Peripherals, spawner: Spawner) -&gt; <span class="prelude-ty">Result</span>&lt;()&gt; {
    <span class="kw">let </span>cells = OutputArray::new([
        Output::new(p.PIN_1, Level::High),
        Output::new(p.PIN_2, Level::High),
        Output::new(p.PIN_3, Level::High),
        Output::new(p.PIN_4, Level::High),
    ]);
    <span class="kw">let </span>segments = OutputArray::new([
        Output::new(p.PIN_5, Level::Low),
        Output::new(p.PIN_6, Level::Low),
        Output::new(p.PIN_7, Level::Low),
        Output::new(p.PIN_8, Level::Low),
        Output::new(p.PIN_9, Level::Low),
        Output::new(p.PIN_10, Level::Low),
        Output::new(p.PIN_11, Level::Low),
        Output::new(p.PIN_12, Level::Low),
    ]);
    <span class="kw">static </span>LED4_STATIC: Led4Static = Led4::new_static();
    <span class="kw">let </span>display = Led4::new(<span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>LED4_STATIC, cells, segments, spawner)<span class="question-mark">?</span>;
    <span class="kw">const </span>FRAME_DURATION: Duration = Duration::from_millis(<span class="number">120</span>);
    <span class="kw">let </span><span class="kw-2">mut </span>animation: heapless::Vec&lt;AnimationFrame, <span class="number">16</span>&gt; = heapless::Vec::new();
    animation.push(AnimationFrame::new([<span class="string">'-'</span>, <span class="string">'-'</span>, <span class="string">'-'</span>, <span class="string">'-'</span>], FRAME_DURATION)).unwrap();
    animation.push(AnimationFrame::new([<span class="string">' '</span>, <span class="string">' '</span>, <span class="string">' '</span>, <span class="string">' '</span>], FRAME_DURATION)).unwrap();
    animation.push(AnimationFrame::new([<span class="string">'1'</span>, <span class="string">'2'</span>, <span class="string">'3'</span>, <span class="string">'4'</span>], FRAME_DURATION)).unwrap();
    display.animate_text(animation);
    <span class="prelude-val">Ok</span>(())
}</code></pre></div>
<p>See the example below for how to build animations.</p>
</div></details></div></details></div><h2 id="synthetic-implementations" class="section-header">Auto Trait Implementations<a href="#synthetic-implementations" class="anchor">§</a></h2><div id="synthetic-implementations-list"><section id="impl-Freeze-for-Led4%3C'a%3E" class="impl"><a href="#impl-Freeze-for-Led4%3C'a%3E" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;'a&gt; </div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#767-769">Source</a><a href="#impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;T, U&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html" title="trait core::convert::Into">Into</a>&lt;U&gt; for T<div class="where">where

<p>That is, this conversion is whatever the implementation of
<code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt; for U</code> chooses to do.</p>

</div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#767-769">Source</a><a href="#impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;T, U&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html" title="trait core::convert::Into">Into</a>&lt;U&gt; for T<div class="where">where

<p>That is, this conversion is whatever the implementation of
<code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt; for U</code> chooses to do.</p>

</div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#767-769">Source</a><a href="#impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;T, U&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html" title="trait core::convert::Into">Into</a>&lt;U&gt; for T<div class="where">where

<p>That is, this conversion is whatever the implementation of
<code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt; for U</code> chooses to do.</p>

title="Drag to resize sidebar"></div><main><div class="width-limiter"><section id="main-content" class="content"><div class="main-heading"><div class="rustdoc-breadcrumbs"><a href="../../index.html">device_kit</a>::<wbr><a href="../index.html">led_strip</a></div><h1>Module <span>colors</span>&nbsp;<button id="copy-path" title="Copy item path to clipboard">Copy item path</button></h1><rustdoc-toolbar></rustdoc-toolbar><span class="sub-heading"></span></div><details class="toggle top-doc" open><summary class="hideme"><span>Expand description</span></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Module containing predefined <a href="../type.RGB8.html" title="type device_kit::led_strip::RGB8"><code>RGB8</code></a> color constants, re-exported from the
<a href="https://docs.rs/smart-leds/latest/smart_leds/index.html"><code>smart_leds</code></a> crate.</p>
<p>These constants follow CSS/Web color names. In particular, <code>GREEN</code> is
<code>(0, 128, 0)</code> and <code>LIME</code> is <code>(0, 255, 0)</code>. If you want “full green,” use
<code>LIME</code>.</p>
<p>All examples in this crate use <code>smart_leds::colors::*</code> as the single source
of named colors; when an embedded-graphics API needs <a href="../struct.Rgb888.html" title="struct device_kit::led_strip::Rgb888"><code>Rgb888</code></a>, convert with
<a href="../trait.ToRgb888.html#tymethod.to_rgb888" title="method device_kit::led_strip::ToRgb888::to_rgb888"><code>ToRgb888::to_rgb888</code></a>.</p>
</div></details><h2 id="constants" class="section-header">Constants<a href="#constants" class="anchor">§</a></h2><dl class="item-table"><dt><a class="constant" href="constant.ALICE_BLUE.html" id="rustdoc-modnav"><h2><a href="index.html">In device_<wbr>kit::<wbr>led_<wbr>strip</a></h2></div></div></nav><div class="sidebar-resizer" title="Drag to resize sidebar"></div><main><div class="width-limiter"><section id="main-content" class="content"><div class="main-heading"><div class="rustdoc-breadcrumbs"><a href="../index.html">device_kit</a>::<wbr><a href="index.html">led_strip</a></div><h1>Enum <span class="enum">Current</span>&nbsp;<button id="copy-path" title="Copy item path to clipboard">Copy item path</button></h1><rustdoc-toolbar></rustdoc-toolbar><span class="sub-heading"><a class="src" href="../../src/device_kit/led_strip.rs.html#3182-3199">Source</a> </span></div><pre class="rust item-decl"><code>pub enum Current {
    Milliamps(<a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.u16.html">u16</a>),
    Unlimited,
}</code></pre><details class="toggle top-doc" open><summary class="hideme"><span>Expand description</span></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Electrical current budget configuration for LED strips.</p>
<p>See the <a href="../macro.led_strip.html" title="macro device_kit::led_strip"><code>led_strip!</code></a>, <a href="../macro.led_strips.html" title="macro device_kit::led_strips"><code>led_strips!</code></a>,
and <a href="../led2d/index.html" title="mod device_kit::led2d"><code>led2d!</code></a> macro docs for usage and context.</p>
</div></details><h2 id="variants" class="variants section-header">Variants<a href="#variants" class="anchor">§</a></h2><div class="variants"><section id="variant.Milliamps" class="variant"><a href="#variant.Milliamps" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">Milliamps(<a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.u16.html">u16</a>)</h3></section><div class="docblock"><p>Limit brightness to stay within a specific milliamp budget.</p>
<p>The <code>max_brightness</code> is automatically calculated to ensure the worst-case electrical current
(all LEDs at full brightness) does not exceed this limit. For example, a 16-LED strip
draws 960 mA at full brightness (assuming 60 mA per LED); with the default electrical current
limit, brightness is capped at ~26%.</p>
<p>See the <a href="../macro.led_strip.html" title="macro device_kit::led_strip"><code>led_strip!</code></a>, <a href="../macro.led_strips.html" title="macro device_kit::led_strips"><code>led_strips!</code></a>,
and <a href="../led2d/index.html" title="mod device_kit::led2d"><code>led2d!</code></a> macro docs for usage and context.</p>
</div><section id="variant.Unlimited" class="variant"><a href="#variant.Unlimited" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">Unlimited</h3></section><div class="docblock"><p>No limit — brightness stays at 100% (subject to practical hardware constraints like
USB power delivery and the Pico’s circuitry).</p>
<p>See the <a href="../macro.led_strip.html" title="macro device_kit::led_strip"><code>led_strip!</code></a>, <a href="../macro.led_strips.html" title="macro device_kit::led_strips"><code>led_strips!</code></a>,
and <a href="../led2d/index.html" title="mod device_kit::led2d"><code>led2d!</code></a> macro docs for usage and context.</p>
</div></div><h2 id="trait-implementations" class="section-header">Trait Implementations<a href="#trait-implementations" class="anchor">§</a></h2><div id="trait-implementations-list"><details device_<wbr>kit::<wbr>led_<wbr>strip</a></h2></div></div></nav><div class="sidebar-resizer" title="Drag to resize sidebar"></div><main><div class="width-limiter"><section id="main-content" class="content"><div class="main-heading"><div class="rustdoc-breadcrumbs"><a href="../index.html">device_kit</a>::<wbr><a href="index.html">led_strip</a></div><h1>Enum <span class="enum">Gamma</span>&nbsp;<button id="copy-path" title="Copy item path to clipboard">Copy item path</button></h1><rustdoc-toolbar></rustdoc-toolbar><span class="sub-heading"><a class="src" href="../../src/device_kit/led_strip.rs.html#272-277">Source</a> </span></div><pre class="rust item-decl"><code>pub enum Gamma {
    Linear,
    Gamma2_2,
}</code></pre><details class="toggle top-doc" open><summary class="hideme"><span>Expand description</span></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Gamma correction configuration for LED strips.</p>
<p>See the <a href="../macro.led_strip.html" title="macro device_kit::led_strip"><code>led_strip!</code></a>, <a href="../macro.led_strips.html" title="macro device_kit::led_strips"><code>led_strips!</code></a>,
and <a href="../led2d/index.html" title="mod device_kit::led2d"><code>led2d!</code></a> macro docs for usage and context.</p>
<p>For background on gamma correction, see the
<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gamma_correction">Wikipedia article on gamma correction</a>.</p>
</div></details><h2 id="variants" class="variants section-header">Variants<a href="#variants" class="anchor">§</a></h2><div class="variants"><section id="variant.Linear" class="variant"><a href="#variant.Linear" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">Linear</h3></section><div class="docblock"><p>Linear gamma (no correction). Gamma = 1.0</p>
</div><section id="variant.Gamma2_2" class="variant"><a href="#variant.Gamma2_2" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">Gamma2_2</h3></section><div class="docblock"><p>Standard gamma 2.2 correction for perceived brightness.</p>

(<code>clone_to_uninit</code>)</span></div></span><div class='docblock'>Performs copy-assignment from <code>self</code> to <code>dest</code>. <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/clone/trait.CloneToUninit.html#tymethod.clone_to_uninit">Read more</a></div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-From%3CT%3E-for-T" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#785">Source</a><a href="#impl-From%3CT%3E-for-T" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;T&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt; for T</h3></section></summary><div class="impl-items"><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.from" class="method trait-impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#788">Source</a><a href="#method.from" class="anchor">§</a><h4 class="code-header">fn <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html#tymethod.from" class="fn">from</a>(t: T) -&gt; T</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Returns the argument unchanged.</p>
</div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#767-769">Source</a><a href="#impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;T, U&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html" title="trait core::convert::Into">Into</a>&lt;U&gt; for T<div class="where">where
    U: <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt;,</div></h3></section></summary><div class="impl-items"><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.into" class="method trait-impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#777">Source</a><a href="#method.into" class="anchor">§</a><h4 class="code-header">fn <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html#tymethod.into" class="fn">into</a>(self) -&gt; U</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Calls <code>U::from(self)</code>.</p>
<p>That is, this conversion is whatever the implementation of
<code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt; for U</code> chooses to do.</p>

id="rustdoc-toc"><h2 class="location"><a href="#">Module led_<wbr>strip</a></h2><h3><a href="#">Sections</a></h3><ul class="block top-toc"><li><a href="#example-write-a-single-1-dimensional-frame" title="Example: Write a Single 1-Dimensional Frame">Example: Write a Single 1-Dimensional Frame</a></li><li><a href="#example-animate-a-sequence" title="Example: Animate a Sequence">Example: Animate a Sequence</a></li></ul><h3><a href="#modules">Module Items</a></h3><ul class="block"><li><a href="#modules" title="Modules">Modules</a></li><li><a href="#macros" title="Macros">Macros</a></li><li><a href="#structs" title="Structs">Structs</a></li><li><a href="#enums" title="Enums">Enums</a></li><li><a href="#traits" title="Traits">Traits</a></li><li><a href="#types" title="Type Aliases">Type resize sidebar"></div><main><div class="width-limiter"><section id="main-content" class="content"><div class="main-heading"><div class="rustdoc-breadcrumbs"><a href="../index.html">device_kit</a></div><h1>Module <span>led_<wbr>strip</span>&nbsp;<button id="copy-path" title="Copy item path to clipboard">Copy item path</button></h1><rustdoc-toolbar></rustdoc-toolbar><span class="sub-heading"><a class="src" href="../../src/device_kit/led_strip.rs.html#1-3233">Source</a> </span></div><details class="toggle top-doc" open><summary class="hideme"><span>Expand description</span></summary><div class="docblock"><p>A device abstraction for 1-dimensional NeoPixel-style (WS2812) LED strips. For 2-dimensional
panels, see the <a href="../led2d/index.html" title="mod device_kit::led2d"><code>led2d</code></a> module.</p>
<p>This page provides the primary documentation and examples for programming LED strips.
The device abstraction supports pixel patterns and animation on the LED strip.</p>
<p><strong>After reading the examples below, see also:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><a href="../macro.led_strip.html" title="macro device_kit::led_strip"><code>led_strip!</code></a> — Macro to generate an LED strip struct type (includes syntax details). See <a href="led_strip_generated/struct.LedStripGenerated.html" title="struct device_kit::led_strip::led_strip_generated::LedStripGenerated"><code>LedStripGenerated</code></a> for a sample of a generated type.</li>
<li><a href="led_strip_generated/struct.LedStripGenerated.html" title="struct device_kit::led_strip::led_strip_generated::LedStripGenerated"><code>LedStripGenerated</code></a> — Sample struct type showing all methods and associated constants.</li>
<li><a href="struct.Frame1d.html" title="struct device_kit::led_strip::Frame1d"><code>Frame1d</code></a> — 1D pixel array used to describe LED strip patterns.</li>
<li><a href="../macro.led_strips.html" title="macro device_kit::led_strips"><code>led_strips!</code></a> — Alternative macro to share a PIO resource with other strips or panels (includes examples).</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="example-write-a-single-1-dimensional-frame"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#example-write-a-single-1-dimensional-frame">§</a>Example: Write a Single 1-Dimensional Frame</h2>
<p>In this example, we set every other LED to blue and gray. Here, the generated struct type is
named <code>LedStripSimple</code>.</p>
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="LED strip preview" /></p>

<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::{<span class="prelude-ty">Result</span>, led_strip::{Frame1d, colors}};
<span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::led_strip;

<span class="comment">// Define LedStripSimple, a struct type for an 8-LED strip on PIN_0.
</span><span class="macro">led_strip!</span> {
    LedStripSimple {
        pin: PIN_0,  <span class="comment">// GPIO pin for LED data
        </span>len: <span class="number">8</span>,      <span class="comment">// 8 LEDs
        // other inputs set to their defaults
    </span>}
}

<span class="kw">async fn </span>example(spawner: embassy_executor::Spawner) -&gt; <span class="prelude-ty">Result</span>&lt;Infallible&gt; {
    <span class="kw">let </span>p = embassy_rp::init(Default::default());
    <span class="comment">// Create a LedStripSimple instance.
    </span><span class="kw">let </span>led_strip_simple = LedStripSimple::new(p.PIN_0, p.PIO0, p.DMA_CH0, spawner)<span class="question-mark">?</span>;

    <span class="comment">// Create and write a frame with alternating blue and gray pixels.
    </span><span class="kw">let </span><span class="kw-2">mut </span>frame = Frame1d::new();
    <span class="kw">for </span>pixel_index <span class="kw">in </span><span class="number">0</span>..LedStripSimple::LEN {
        <span class="comment">// Directly index into the frame buffer.
        </span>frame[pixel_index] = [colors::BLUE, colors::GRAY][pixel_index % <span class="number">2</span>];
    }

    <span class="comment">// Display the frame on the LED strip (until replaced).
    </span>led_strip_simple.write_frame(frame).<span class="kw">await</span><span class="question-mark">?</span>;

    core::future::pending().<span class="kw">await </span><span class="comment">// run forever
</span>}</code></pre></div><h2 id="example-animate-a-sequence"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#example-animate-a-sequence">§</a>Example: Animate a Sequence</h2>
<p>This example animates a 96-LED strip through red, green, and blue frames, cycling continuously.
Here, the generated struct type is named <code>LedStripAnimated</code>.</p>
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="LED strip preview" /></p>

<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::{<span class="prelude-ty">Result</span>, led_strip::{Current, Frame1d, Gamma, colors}};
<span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::led_strip;

<span class="comment">// Define LedStripAnimated, a struct type for a 96-LED strip on PIN_4.
// We change some defaults including setting a 1A power budget and disabling gamma correction.
</span><span class="macro">led_strip!</span> {
    <span class="kw">pub</span>(<span class="self">self</span>) LedStripAnimated {               <span class="comment">// Can provide a visibility modifier
        </span>pin: PIN_4,                            <span class="comment">// GPIO pin for LED data
        </span>len: <span class="number">96</span>,                               <span class="comment">// 96 LEDs
        </span>pio: PIO1,                             <span class="comment">// Use PIO resource 1
        </span>dma: DMA_CH3,                          <span class="comment">// Use DMA channel 3
        </span>max_current: Current::Milliamps(<span class="number">1000</span>), <span class="comment">// 1A power budget
        </span>gamma: Gamma::Linear,                  <span class="comment">// No color correction
        </span>max_frames: <span class="number">3</span>,                         <span class="comment">// Up to 3 animation frames
    </span>}
}

<span class="kw">async fn </span>example(spawner: embassy_executor::Spawner) -&gt; <span class="prelude-ty">Result</span>&lt;Infallible&gt; {
    <span class="kw">let </span>p = embassy_rp::init(Default::default());
    <span class="kw">let </span>led_strip_animated = LedStripAnimated::new(p.PIN_4, p.PIO1, p.DMA_CH3, spawner)<span class="question-mark">?</span>;

    <span class="comment">// Create a sequence of frames and durations and then animate them (looping, until replaced).
    </span><span class="kw">let </span>frame_duration = embassy_time::Duration::from_millis(<span class="number">300</span>);
    led_strip_animated
        .animate([
            (Frame1d::filled(colors::RED), frame_duration),
            (Frame1d::filled(colors::GREEN), frame_duration),
            (Frame1d::filled(colors::BLUE), frame_duration),
        ])
        .<span class="kw">await</span><span class="question-mark">?</span>;

    core::future::pending().<span class="kw">await </span><span class="comment">// run forever
</span>}</code></pre></div></div></details><h2 id="modules" class="section-header">Modules<a href="#modules" class="anchor">§</a></h2><dl class="item-table"><dt><a class="mod" href="colors/index.html" title="mod device_kit::led_strip::colors">colors</a></dt><dd>Module containing predefined <a href="type.RGB8.html" title="type device_kit::led_strip::RGB8"><code>RGB8</code></a> color constants, re-exported from the
<a href="https://docs.rs/smart-leds/latest/smart_leds/index.html"><code>smart_leds</code></a> crate.</dd><dt><a class="mod" href="led_strip_generated/index.html" title="mod device_kit::led_strip::led_strip_generated">led_<wbr>strip_<wbr>generated</a></dt><dd>Module containing <a href="led_strip_generated/struct.LedStripGenerated.html" title="struct device_kit::led_strip::led_strip_generated::LedStripGenerated"><code>LedStripGenerated</code></a>, the sample struct type generated by the
<a href="../macro.led_strip.html" title="macro device_kit::led_strip"><code>led_strip!</code></a> macro.</dd></dl><h2 id="macros" class="section-header">Macros<a href="#macros" class="anchor">§</a></h2><dl class="item-table"><dt><a class="macro" href="macro.led_strip.html" title="macro device_kit::led_strip::led_strip">led_<wbr>strip</a></dt><dd>Macro to generate an LED-strip struct type (includes syntax details). See
<a href="led_strip_generated/struct.LedStripGenerated.html" title="struct device_kit::led_strip::led_strip_generated::LedStripGenerated"><code>LedStripGenerated</code></a> for a sample of a generated type.</dd><dt><a class="macro" href="macro.led_strips.html" title="macro device_kit::led_strip::led_strips">led_<wbr>strips</a></dt><dd>Macro to generate multiple LED strip and panel struct types that share a single
<a href="../index.html#glossary" title="mod device_kit">PIO resource</a> (includes syntax details).</dd></dl><h2 id="structs" class="section-header">Structs<a href="#structs" class="anchor">§</a></h2><dl class="item-table"><dt><a class="struct" href="struct.Frame1d.html" title="struct device_kit::led_strip::Frame1d">Frame1d</a></dt><dd>1D pixel array used to describe LED strip patterns.</dd><dt><a class="struct" href="struct.Rgb888.html" title="struct device_kit::led_strip::Rgb888">Rgb888</a></dt><dd>8-bit-per-channel RGB color re-exported from the
<a href="https://docs.rs/embedded-graphics"><code>embedded-graphics</code></a> crate.</dd></dl><h2 id="enums" class="section-header">Enums<a href="#enums" class="anchor">§</a></h2><dl class="item-table"><dt><a class="enum" href="enum.Current.html" title="enum device_kit::led_strip::Current">Current</a></dt><dd>Electrical current budget configuration for LED strips.</dd><dt><a class="enum" href="enum.Gamma.html" title="enum device_kit::led_strip::Gamma">Gamma</a></dt><dd>Gamma correction configuration for LED strips.</dd></dl><h2 id="traits" class="section-header">Traits<a href="#traits" class="anchor">§</a></h2><dl class="item-table"><dt><a class="trait" href="trait.ToRgb8.html" title="trait device_kit::led_strip::ToRgb8">ToRgb8</a></dt><dd>Convert colors to <a href="type.RGB8.html" title="type device_kit::led_strip::RGB8"><code>RGB8</code></a> for LED strip rendering.</dd><dt><a class="trait" href="trait.ToRgb888.html" title="trait device_kit::led_strip::ToRgb888">ToRgb888</a></dt><dd>Convert colors to <a href="struct.Rgb888.html" title="struct device_kit::led_strip::Rgb888"><code>Rgb888</code></a> for embedded-graphics rendering.</dd></dl><h2 id="types" class="section-header">Type Aliases<a href="#types" class="anchor">§</a></h2><dl class="item-table"><dt><a class="type" href="type.RGB8.html" title="type device_kit::led_strip::RGB8">RGB8</a></dt><dd>8-bit-per-channel RGB color re-exported from the
<a href="https://docs.rs/smart-leds/latest/smart_leds/index.html"><code>smart_leds</code></a> crate.</dd></dl></section></div></main></body></html>

top-doc" open><summary class="hideme"><span>Expand description</span></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Sample struct type generated by the <a href="../../macro.led_strip.html" title="macro device_kit::led_strip"><code>led_strip!</code></a> macro, showing all methods and constants.</p>
<p>This page serves as the definitive reference for what a generated LED strip type
provides. For first-time readers, start with the examples in the <a href="../index.html" title="mod device_kit::led_strip"><code>led_strip</code></a> module
documentation, then return here for a complete list of available methods and
associated constants.</p>
<p>Auto-generated.</p>
</div></details><h2 id="implementations" class="section-header">Implementations<a href="#implementations" class="anchor">§</a></h2><div id="implementations-list"><details class="toggle implementors-toggle" open><summary><section id="impl-LedStripGenerated" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="../../../src/device_kit/led_strip/led_strip_generated.rs.html#45-122">Source</a><a href="#impl-LedStripGenerated" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl <a class="struct" href="struct.LedStripGenerated.html" title="struct device_kit::led_strip::led_strip_generated::LedStripGenerated">LedStripGenerated</a></h3></section></summary><div class="impl-items"><details class="toggle" open><summary><section id="associatedconstant.LEN" class="associatedconstant"><a class="src rightside" href="../../../src/device_kit/led_strip/led_strip_generated.rs.html#47">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub const <a href="#associatedconstant.LEN" class="constant">LEN</a>: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.usize.html">usize</a> = 48usize</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Number of LEDs in this strip.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle" open><summary><section id="associatedconstant.MAX_BRIGHTNESS" class="associatedconstant"><a class="src rightside" href="../../../src/device_kit/led_strip/led_strip_generated.rs.html#55-56">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub const <a href="#associatedconstant.MAX_BRIGHTNESS" class="constant">MAX_BRIGHTNESS</a>: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.u8.html">u8</a> = 255u8</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Maximum brightness level, automatically limited by the power budget specified in <code>max_current</code>.</p>
<p>We assume each LED draws 60 mA at full brightness. The actual limit depends on
the power budget you specified in the <a href="../../macro.led_strip.html" title="macro device_kit::led_strip"><code>led_strip!</code></a>
or <a href="../../macro.led_strips.html" title="macro device_kit::led_strips"><code>led_strips!</code></a> macro.
This constant is the result
of calculating how much brightness is safe given that budget and the number of LEDs.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle" open><summary><section id="associatedconstant.MAX_FRAMES" class="associatedconstant"><a class="src rightside" href="../../../src/device_kit/led_strip/led_strip_generated.rs.html#61">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub const <a href="#associatedconstant.MAX_FRAMES" class="constant">MAX_FRAMES</a>: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.usize.html">usize</a> = 16usize</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Maximum number of animation frames allowed.</p>
<p>Specified in the <a href="../../macro.led_strip.html" title="macro device_kit::led_strip"><code>led_strip!</code></a>
or <a href="../../macro.led_strips.html" title="macro device_kit::led_strips"><code>led_strips!</code></a> macro.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.new" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../../src/device_kit/led_strip/led_strip_generated.rs.html#90-99">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub fn <a href="#method.new" class="fn">new</a>(
    pin: Peri&lt;'static, PIN_3&gt;,
    pio: Peri&lt;'static, PIO0&gt;,
    dma: Peri&lt;'static, DMA_CH0&gt;,
    spawner: Spawner,
) -&gt; <a class="type" href="../../type.Result.html" title="type device_kit::Result">Result</a>&lt;&amp;'static Self&gt;</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Create a new LED strip instance of the struct type
defined by <a href="../../macro.led_strip.html" title="macro device_kit::led_strip"><code>led_strip!</code></a>.</p>
<p>See the <a href="../index.html" title="mod device_kit::led_strip"><code>led_strip</code></a> module docs for usage.</p>
<p>The <code>pin</code>, <code>pio</code>, and <code>dma</code> parameters must correspond to the
GPIO pin, PIO resource, and DMA channel specified in the macro.</p>
<p>The <a href="../../macro.led_strip.html" title="macro device_kit::led_strip"><code>led_strip!</code></a> macro defaults to <code>PIO0</code> and <code>DMA_CH0</code> if not specified.</p>
<h5 id="parameters"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#parameters">§</a>Parameters</h5>
<ul>
<li><code>pin</code>: GPIO pin for LED data signal</li>
<li><code>pio</code>: PIO resource</li>
<li><code>dma</code>: DMA channel for LED data transfer</li>
<li><code>spawner</code>: Task spawner for background operations</li>
</ul>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.write_frame" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../../src/device_kit/led_strip/led_strip_generated.rs.html#104-110">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub async fn <a href="#method.write_frame" class="fn">write_frame</a>(&amp;self, frame: <a class="struct" href="../struct.Frame1d.html" title="struct device_kit::led_strip::Frame1d">Frame1d</a>&lt;{ Self::LEN }&gt;) -&gt; <a class="type" href="../../type.Result.html" title="type device_kit::Result">Result</a>&lt;<a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.unit.html">()</a>&gt;</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Write a frame to the LED strip.</p>

</div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#767-769">Source</a><a href="#impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;T, U&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html" title="trait core::convert::Into">Into</a>&lt;U&gt; for T<div class="where">where
    U: <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt;,</div></h3></section></summary><div class="impl-items"><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.into" class="method trait-impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#777">Source</a><a href="#method.into" class="anchor">§</a><h4 class="code-header">fn <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html#tymethod.into" class="fn">into</a>(self) -&gt; U</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Calls <code>U::from(self)</code>.</p>
<p>That is, this conversion is whatever the implementation of
<code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt; for U</code> chooses to do.</p>

class="width-limiter"><section id="main-content" class="content"><div class="main-heading"><div class="rustdoc-breadcrumbs"><a href="../index.html">device_kit</a>::<wbr><a href="index.html">led_strip</a></div><h1>Macro <span class="macro">led_<wbr>strip</span>&nbsp;<button id="copy-path" title="Copy item path to clipboard">Copy item path</button></h1><rustdoc-toolbar></rustdoc-toolbar><span class="sub-heading"><a class="src" href="../../src/device_kit/led_strip.rs.html#2666-2668">Source</a> </span></div><pre class="rust item-decl"><code>macro_rules! led_strip {
    ($($tt:tt)*) =&gt; { ... };
}</code></pre><details class="toggle top-doc" open><summary class="hideme"><span>Expand description</span></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Macro to generate an LED-strip struct type (includes syntax details). See
<a href="led_strip_generated/struct.LedStripGenerated.html" title="struct device_kit::led_strip::led_strip_generated::LedStripGenerated"><code>LedStripGenerated</code></a> for a sample of a generated type.</p>
<p><strong>See the <a href="index.html" title="mod device_kit::led_strip">led_strip module documentation</a> for usage examples.</strong></p>
<p><strong>Required fields:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><code>pin</code> — GPIO pin for LED data</li>
<li><code>len</code> — Number of LEDs</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Optional fields:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><code>pio</code> — PIO resource (default: <code>PIO0</code>)</li>
<li><code>dma</code> — DMA channel (default: <code>DMA_CH0</code>)</li>
<li><code>max_current</code> — Electrical current budget (default: 250 mA)</li>
<li><code>gamma</code> — Color curve (default: <code>Gamma::Gamma2_2</code>)</li>
<li><code>max_frames</code> — Maximum number of animation frames (default: 16 frames)</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="current-limiting"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#current-limiting">§</a>Current Limiting</h2>
<p>The <code>max_current</code> field automatically scales brightness to stay within your electrical current budget.</p>
<p>Each WS2812 LED is assumed to draw 60 mA at full brightness. For example:</p>
<ul>
<li>16 LEDs × 60 mA = 960 mA at full brightness</li>
<li>With <code>max_current: Current::Milliamps(1000)</code>, all LEDs fit at 100% brightness</li>
<li>With the default electrical current limit (250 mA), the generated <code>MAX_BRIGHTNESS</code> limits LEDs to ~26% brightness</li>
</ul>
<p>The electrical current limit is baked into a compile-time lookup table, so it has no runtime cost.</p>
<p><strong>Powering LEDs from the Pico’s pin 40 (VBUS):</strong> Pin 40 is the USB 5 V rail pass-through, but the Pico itself has practical electrical current limits — the USB connector, cable, and internal circuitry aren’t designed for heavy loads. Small LED panels (a few hundred mA) can usually power from pin 40 with a decent USB supply; for larger loads (1 A+), use a separate 5 V supply and share ground with the Pico.</p>
<h2 id="color-correction-gamma"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#color-correction-gamma">§</a>Color Correction (Gamma)</h2>
<p>The <code>gamma</code> field applies a color response curve to make colors look more natural:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="enum.Gamma.html#variant.Linear" title="variant device_kit::led_strip::Gamma::Linear"><code>Gamma::Linear</code></a> — No correction (raw values)</li>
<li><a href="enum.Gamma.html#variant.Gamma2_2" title="variant device_kit::led_strip::Gamma::Gamma2_2"><code>Gamma::Gamma2_2</code></a> — sRGB-like curve (default; often looks most natural)</li>
</ul>
<p>The gamma curve is baked into a compile-time lookup table, so it has no runtime cost.</p>
<h2 id="related-macros"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#related-macros">§</a>Related Macros</h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="../macro.led_strips.html" title="macro device_kit::led_strips"><code>led_strips!</code></a> — Alternative macro to share a PIO resource with other strips or panels (includes examples)</li>
<li><a href="../led2d/index.html" title="mod device_kit::led2d"><code>led2d!</code></a> — For 2-dimensional LED panels</li>
</ul>
</div></details></section></div></main></body></html>

href="../../static.files/favicon-32x32-eab170b8.png"><link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="../../static.files/favicon-044be391.svg"></head><body class="rustdoc macro"><!--[if lte IE 11]><div class="sidebar"><div class="sidebar-crate"><h2><a href="../../device_kit/index.html">device_<wbr>kit</a><span class="version">0.0.1-alpha</span></h2></div><div class="sidebar-elems"><section href="#example-connect-three-led-stripspanels-to-one-pio-resource" title="Example: Connect Three LED Strips/Panels to One PIO Resource">Example: Connect Three LED Strips/Panels to One PIO Resource</a></li><li><a href="#configuration" title="Configuration">Configuration</a><ul><li><a href="#shared-pio-resource" title="Shared PIO Resource">Shared PIO Resource</a></li><li><a
