item-decl"><code>pub struct Servo&lt;'d&gt; { <span class="comment">/* private fields */</span> }</code></pre><details class="toggle top-doc" open><summary class="hideme"><span>Expand description</span></summary><div class="docblock"><p>A device abstraction for SG90 servo motors.</p>
<h2 id="examples"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#examples">§</a>Examples</h2>
<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::servo::servo_odd;
<span class="kw">async fn </span>example(p: embassy_rp::Peripherals) {
    <span class="comment">// Create a servo on GPIO 15 with pulse range 500-2500 microseconds
    // (500µs = 0°, 2500µs = 180° for typical SG90)
    // GPIO 15 is odd. Calculate slice: (15 / 2) % 8 = 7 % 8 = 7 → PWM_SLICE7
    </span><span class="kw">let </span><span class="kw-2">mut </span>servo = <span class="macro">servo_odd!</span>(p.PIN_15, p.PWM_SLICE7, <span class="number">500</span>, <span class="number">2500</span>);

    servo.set_degrees(<span class="number">45</span>);  <span class="comment">// Move to 45 degrees
    </span>servo.center();          <span class="comment">// Move to center position
</span>}</code></pre></div></div></details><h2 id="implementations" class="section-header">Implementations<a href="#implementations" class="anchor">§</a></h2><div id="implementations-list"><details class="toggle implementors-toggle" open><summary><section id="impl-Servo%3C'd%3E" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/servo.rs.html#91-206">Source</a><a href="#impl-Servo%3C'd%3E" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;'d&gt; <a class="struct" href="struct.Servo.html" title="struct device_kit::servo::Servo">Servo</a>&lt;'d&gt;</h3></section></summary><div class="impl-items"><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.new" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/servo.rs.html#109-111">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub fn <a href="#method.new" class="fn">new</a>(
    pwm: Pwm&lt;'d&gt;,
    channel: <a class="enum" href="enum.ServoChannel.html" title="enum device_kit::servo::ServoChannel">ServoChannel</a>,
    min_us: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.u16.html">u16</a>,
    max_us: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.u16.html">u16</a>,
) -&gt; Self</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Create a servo on a PWM output channel.</p>
<p>Consider using the <a href="macro.servo_even.html" title="macro device_kit::servo::servo_even"><code>servo_even!</code></a> or <a href="macro.servo_odd.html" title="macro device_kit::servo::servo_odd"><code>servo_odd!</code></a> macros instead for simpler usage.</p>
<h5 id="examples-1"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#examples-1">§</a>Examples</h5>
<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::servo::{Servo, ServoChannel};
<span class="kw">async fn </span>example(p: embassy_rp::Peripherals) {
    <span class="comment">// GPIO 15 is odd, uses channel B. Calculate slice: (15 / 2) % 8 = 7
    </span><span class="kw">let </span>pwm = embassy_rp::pwm::Pwm::new_output_b(p.PWM_SLICE7, p.PIN_15, embassy_rp::pwm::Config::default());
    <span class="kw">let </span><span class="kw-2">mut </span>servo = Servo::new(pwm, ServoChannel::B, <span class="number">500</span>, <span class="number">2500</span>);
}</code></pre></div></div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.center" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/servo.rs.html#160-162">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub fn <a href="#method.center" class="fn">center</a>(&amp;mut self)</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Center (~midpoint of min/max).</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.set_degrees" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/servo.rs.html#165-171">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub fn <a href="#method.set_degrees" class="fn">set_degrees</a>(&amp;mut self, degrees: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.u16.html">u16</a>)</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Set position in degrees 0..=180 mapped into [min_us, max_us].</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.disable" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/servo.rs.html#194-197">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub fn <a href="#method.disable" class="fn">disable</a>(&amp;mut self)</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Stop sending control signals to the servo.</p>
<p>This allows the servo to relax and move freely, reducing power consumption
and mechanical stress.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.enable" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/servo.rs.html#202-205">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub fn <a href="#method.enable" class="fn">enable</a>(&amp;mut self)</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Resume sending control signals to the servo.</p>
<p>The servo will move back to its last commanded position.</p>
</div></details></div></details></div><h2 id="synthetic-implementations" class="section-header">Auto Trait Implementations<a href="#synthetic-implementations" class="anchor">§</a></h2><div id="synthetic-implementations-list"><section id="impl-Freeze-for-Servo%3C'd%3E" class="impl"><a href="#impl-Freeze-for-Servo%3C'd%3E" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;'d&gt; </div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#767-769">Source</a><a href="#impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;T, U&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html" title="trait core::convert::Into">Into</a>&lt;U&gt; for T<div class="where">where
    U: <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt;,</div></h3></section></summary><div class="impl-items"><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.into" class="method trait-impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#777">Source</a><a href="#method.into" class="anchor">§</a><h4 class="code-header">fn <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html#tymethod.into" class="fn">into</a>(self) -&gt; U</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Calls <code>U::from(self)</code>.</p>
<p>That is, this conversion is whatever the implementation of
<code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt; for U</code> chooses to do.</p>
</div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-LosslessTryInto%3CDst%3E-for-Src" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://docs.rs/fixed/~1.28/src/fixed/traits.rs.html#3660-3662">Source</a><a href="#impl-LosslessTryInto%3CDst%3E-for-Src" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;Src, Dst&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://docs.rs/fixed/~1.28/fixed/traits/trait.LosslessTryInto.html" title="trait fixed::traits::LosslessTryInto">LosslessTryInto</a>&lt;Dst&gt; for Src<div class="where">where

item-decl"><code>pub fn concat_steps&lt;const CAP: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.usize.html">usize</a>&gt;(sequences: &amp;[&amp;[<a class="struct" CAP&gt;</code></pre><details class="toggle top-doc" open><summary class="hideme"><span>Expand description</span></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Concatenate arrays of animation <a href="struct.Step.html" title="struct device_kit::servo_animate::Step"><code>Step</code></a> values into a single sequence.</p>
<p>Provide the capacity as a const generic and pass slices of step arrays.
Import with <code>use device_kit::servo_animate::concat_steps;</code>.</p>
</div></details></section></div></main></body></html>

class="struct">Servo<wbr>Animate</span>&nbsp;<button id="copy-path" title="Copy item path to clipboard">Copy item path</button></h1><rustdoc-toolbar></rustdoc-toolbar><span class="sub-heading"><a class="src" href="../../src/device_kit/servo_animate.rs.html#139-141">Source</a> </span></div><pre class="rust item-decl"><code>pub struct ServoAnimate { <span class="comment">/* private fields */</span> }</code></pre><details class="toggle top-doc" open><summary class="hideme"><span>Expand description</span></summary><div class="docblock"><p>A device abstraction that drives a single servo with scripted animation sequences.</p>
<p>See <a href="../servo/struct.Servo.html" title="struct device_kit::servo::Servo"><code>Servo</code></a> for servo setup guidance and <a href="struct.ServoAnimate.html" title="struct device_kit::servo_animate::ServoAnimate"><code>ServoAnimate</code></a> for usage.</p>
<h2 id="example"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#example">§</a>Example</h2>
<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::servo_animate::{concat_steps, linear, ServoAnimate, ServoAnimateStatic, Step, servo_even};
<span class="kw">use </span>embassy_time::Duration;

<span class="kw">async fn </span>demo(p: embassy_rp::Peripherals, spawner: embassy_executor::Spawner) {
    <span class="kw">static </span>SERVO_ANIMATE_STATIC: ServoAnimateStatic = ServoAnimate::new_static();
    <span class="kw">let </span>servo = ServoAnimate::new(
        <span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>SERVO_ANIMATE_STATIC,
        <span class="macro">servo_even!</span>(p.PIN_0, p.PWM_SLICE0, <span class="number">500</span>, <span class="number">2500</span>),
        spawner,
    )
    .unwrap();

    <span class="comment">// Sweep down from 180 to 0 over 5 seconds, hold, then repeat.
    </span><span class="kw">const </span>FIVE_SECONDS: Duration = Duration::from_secs(<span class="number">5</span>);
    <span class="kw">const </span>HALF_SECOND: Duration = Duration::from_millis(<span class="number">500</span>);
    <span class="kw">let </span>sweep = linear::&lt;<span class="number">11</span>&gt;(<span class="number">180</span>, <span class="number">0</span>, FIVE_SECONDS);
    <span class="kw">let </span>sequence = concat_steps::&lt;<span class="number">16</span>&gt;(<span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>[
        <span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>sweep,
        <span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>[
            Step {
                degrees: <span class="number">0</span>,
                duration: HALF_SECOND,
            },
        ],
    ]);
    servo.animate(<span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>sequence).<span class="kw">await</span>;
}</code></pre></div></div></details><h2 id="implementations" class="section-header">Implementations<a href="#implementations" class="anchor">§</a></h2><div id="implementations-list"><details class="toggle implementors-toggle" open><summary><section id="impl-ServoAnimate" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/servo_animate.rs.html#143-188">Source</a><a href="#impl-ServoAnimate" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl <a class="struct" href="struct.ServoAnimate.html" title="struct device_kit::servo_animate::ServoAnimate">ServoAnimate</a></h3></section></summary><div class="impl-items"><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.new_static" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/servo_animate.rs.html#146-148">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.new_static" class="fn">new_static</a>() -&gt; <a class="struct" href="struct.ServoAnimateStatic.html" title="struct device_kit::servo_animate::ServoAnimateStatic">ServoAnimateStatic</a></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Create static resources for a servo animator.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.new" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/servo_animate.rs.html#156-166">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub fn <a href="#method.new" class="fn">new</a>(
    servo_animate_static: &amp;'static <a class="struct" href="struct.ServoAnimateStatic.html" title="struct device_kit::servo_animate::ServoAnimateStatic">ServoAnimateStatic</a>,
    servo: <a class="struct" href="../servo/struct.Servo.html" title="struct device_kit::servo::Servo">Servo</a>&lt;'static&gt;,
    spawner: Spawner,
) -&gt; <a class="enum" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/result/enum.Result.html" title="enum core::result::Result">Result</a>&lt;Self, SpawnError&gt;</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Create the servo animator and spawn its task. See <a href="struct.ServoAnimate.html" title="struct device_kit::servo_animate::ServoAnimate"><code>ServoAnimate</code></a> for a full example.</p>
<h5 id="errors"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#errors">§</a>Errors</h5>
<p>Returns an error if the task cannot be spawned.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.set" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/servo_animate.rs.html#169-172">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub async fn <a href="#method.set" class="fn">set</a>(&amp;self, degrees: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.u16.html">u16</a>)</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Set the target angle (0..=180). See <a href="struct.ServoAnimate.html" title="struct device_kit::servo_animate::ServoAnimate"><code>ServoAnimate</code></a> for usage.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.animate" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/servo_animate.rs.html#176-187">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub async fn <a href="#method.animate" class="fn">animate</a>(&amp;self, steps: &amp;[<a class="struct" href="struct.Step.html" title="struct device_kit::servo_animate::Step">Step</a>])</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Animate the servo through a sequence of angles with per-step hold durations.
The sequence repeats until interrupted by a new command.</p>
</div></details></div></details></div><h2 id="synthetic-implementations" class="section-header">Auto Trait Implementations<a href="#synthetic-implementations" class="anchor">§</a></h2><div id="synthetic-implementations-list"><section id="impl-Freeze-for-ServoAnimate" class="impl"><a href="#impl-Freeze-for-ServoAnimate" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/marker/trait.Freeze.html" title="trait core::marker::Freeze">Freeze</a> for <a class="struct" href="struct.ServoAnimate.html" title="struct device_kit::servo_animate::ServoAnimate">ServoAnimate</a></h3></section><section id="impl-RefUnwindSafe-for-ServoAnimate" class="impl"><a href="#impl-RefUnwindSafe-for-ServoAnimate" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl !<a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/panic/unwind_safe/trait.RefUnwindSafe.html" title="trait </div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#767-769">Source</a><a href="#impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;T, U&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html" title="trait core::convert::Into">Into</a>&lt;U&gt; for T<div class="where">where

<p>That is, this conversion is whatever the implementation of
<code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt; for U</code> chooses to do.</p>

</div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#767-769">Source</a><a href="#impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;T, U&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html" title="trait core::convert::Into">Into</a>&lt;U&gt; for T<div class="where">where
    U: <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt;,</div></h3></section></summary><div class="impl-items"><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.into" class="method trait-impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#777">Source</a><a href="#method.into" class="anchor">§</a><h4 class="code-header">fn <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html#tymethod.into" class="fn">into</a>(self) -&gt; U</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Calls <code>U::from(self)</code>.</p>
<p>That is, this conversion is whatever the implementation of
<code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt; for U</code> chooses to do.</p>

class="toggle top-doc" open><summary class="hideme"><span>Expand description</span></summary><div class="docblock"><p>A device abstraction for Network Time Protocol (NTP) time synchronization over WiFi.</p>
<p>This version uses an existing network stack (e.g., from <code>WifiAuto</code>).</p>
<p>See <a href="struct.TimeSync.html" title="struct device_kit::time_sync::TimeSync"><code>TimeSync</code></a> for usage examples.</p>
</div></details><h2 id="structs" class="section-header">Structs<a href="#structs" class="anchor">§</a></h2><dl class="item-table"><dt><a class="struct" href="struct.TimeSync.html" title="struct device_kit::time_sync::TimeSync">Time<wbr>Sync</a></dt><dd>Device abstraction that manages Network Time Protocol (NTP) synchronization over WiFi.</dd><dt><a class="struct" href="struct.TimeSyncStatic.html" title="struct device_kit::time_sync::TimeSyncStatic">Time<wbr>Sync<wbr>Static</a></dt><dd>Resources needed to construct a <a href="struct.TimeSync.html" title="struct device_kit::time_sync::TimeSync"><code>TimeSync</code></a> (see <a href="struct.TimeSync.html" title="struct device_kit::time_sync::TimeSync"><code>TimeSync</code></a> docs).</dd><dt><a class="struct" href="struct.UnixSeconds.html" title="struct device_kit::time_sync::UnixSeconds">Unix<wbr>Seconds</a></dt><dd>Units-safe wrapper for Unix timestamps (seconds since 1970-01-01 00:00:00 UTC).</dd></dl><h2 id="enums" class="section-header">Enums<a href="#enums" class="anchor">§</a></h2><dl class="item-table"><dt><a class="enum" href="enum.TimeSyncEvent.html" title="enum device_kit::time_sync::TimeSyncEvent">Time<wbr>Sync<wbr>Event</a></dt><dd>Events emitted by <a href="struct.TimeSync.html" title="struct device_kit::time_sync::TimeSync"><code>TimeSync</code></a>. device_<wbr>kit::<wbr>time_<wbr>sync</a></h2></div></div></nav><div class="sidebar-resizer" title="Drag to resize sidebar"></div><main><div class="width-limiter"><section id="main-content" class="content"><div class="main-heading"><div class="rustdoc-breadcrumbs"><a href="../index.html">device_kit</a>::<wbr><a href="index.html">time_sync</a></div><h1>Struct <span class="struct">Time<wbr>Sync</span>&nbsp;<button id="copy-path" title="Copy item path to clipboard">Copy item path</button></h1><rustdoc-toolbar></rustdoc-toolbar><span class="sub-heading"><a class="src" href="../../src/device_kit/time_sync.rs.html#124-126">Source</a> </span></div><pre class="rust item-decl"><code>pub struct TimeSync { <span class="comment">/* private fields */</span> }</code></pre><details class="toggle top-doc" open><summary class="hideme"><span>Expand description</span></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Device abstraction that manages Network Time Protocol (NTP) synchronization over WiFi.</p>
<p>Uses an existing network stack (typically from <a href="../wifi_auto/struct.WifiAuto.html" title="struct device_kit::wifi_auto::WifiAuto"><code>WifiAuto</code></a>).</p>
<h2 id="sync-timing"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#sync-timing">§</a>Sync Timing</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Initial sync</strong>: Fires immediately on start (retries at 10s, 30s, 60s, then 5min intervals if failed)</li>
<li><strong>Periodic sync</strong>: After first success, syncs every hour (retries every 5min on failure)</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="examples"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#examples">§</a>Examples</h2>
<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::time_sync::{TimeSync, TimeSyncEvent, TimeSyncStatic};

<span class="kw">async fn </span>run_time_sync(
    stack: <span class="kw-2">&amp;</span><span class="lifetime">'static </span>embassy_net::Stack&lt;<span class="lifetime">'static</span>&gt;,
    spawner: embassy_executor::Spawner,
) {
    <span class="comment">// Create TimeSync with an existing network stack (often from WifiAuto)
    </span><span class="kw">static </span>TIME_SYNC_STATIC: TimeSyncStatic = TimeSync::new_static();
    <span class="kw">let </span>time_sync = TimeSync::new(<span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>TIME_SYNC_STATIC, stack, spawner);

    <span class="comment">// Wait for sync events
    </span><span class="kw">loop </span>{
        <span class="kw">match </span>time_sync.wait_for_sync().<span class="kw">await </span>{
            TimeSyncEvent::Success { unix_seconds } =&gt; {
                <span class="macro">defmt::info!</span>(<span class="string">"Time synced: {} seconds"</span>, unix_seconds.as_i64());
            }
            TimeSyncEvent::Failed(message) =&gt; {
                <span class="macro">defmt::info!</span>(<span class="string">"time sync failed: {}. Will continue trying"</span>, message);
            }
        }
    }
}</code></pre></div></div></details><h2 id="implementations" class="section-header">Implementations<a href="#implementations" class="anchor">§</a></h2><div id="implementations-list"><details class="toggle implementors-toggle" open><summary><section id="impl-TimeSync" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/time_sync.rs.html#128-161">Source</a><a href="#impl-TimeSync" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl <a class="struct" href="struct.TimeSync.html" title="struct device_kit::time_sync::TimeSync">TimeSync</a></h3></section></summary><div class="impl-items"><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.new_static" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/time_sync.rs.html#131-136">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.new_static" class="fn">new_static</a>() -&gt; <a class="struct" href="struct.TimeSyncStatic.html" title="struct device_kit::time_sync::TimeSyncStatic">TimeSyncStatic</a></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Create <a href="struct.TimeSync.html" title="struct device_kit::time_sync::TimeSync"><code>TimeSync</code></a> resources. See <a href="struct.TimeSync.html" title="struct device_kit::time_sync::TimeSync"><code>TimeSync</code></a> docs for usage.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.new" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/time_sync.rs.html#142-155">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub fn <a href="#method.new" class="fn">new</a>(
    time_sync_static: &amp;'static <a class="struct" href="struct.TimeSyncStatic.html" title="struct device_kit::time_sync::TimeSyncStatic">TimeSyncStatic</a>,
    stack: &amp;'static Stack&lt;'static&gt;,
    spawner: Spawner,
) -&gt; &amp;'static Self</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Create a <a href="struct.TimeSync.html" title="struct device_kit::time_sync::TimeSync"><code>TimeSync</code></a> that uses an existing Embassy stack.</p>
<p>WiFi is managed elsewhere (e.g. via <a href="../wifi_auto/struct.WifiAuto.html" title="struct device_kit::wifi_auto::WifiAuto"><code>WifiAuto</code></a>)
and the networking stack is already initialized in client mode.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.wait_for_sync" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/time_sync.rs.html#158-160">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub async fn <a href="#method.wait_for_sync" class="fn">wait_for_sync</a>(&amp;self) -&gt; <a class="enum" href="enum.TimeSyncEvent.html" title="enum device_kit::time_sync::TimeSyncEvent">TimeSyncEvent</a></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Wait for and return the next <a href="enum.TimeSyncEvent.html" title="enum device_kit::time_sync::TimeSyncEvent"><code>TimeSyncEvent</code></a>. See <a href="struct.TimeSync.html" title="struct device_kit::time_sync::TimeSync"><code>TimeSync</code></a> docs for an example.</p>

</div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#767-769">Source</a><a href="#impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;T, U&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html" title="trait core::convert::Into">Into</a>&lt;U&gt; for T<div class="where">where
    U: <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt;,</div></h3></section></summary><div class="impl-items"><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.into" class="method trait-impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#777">Source</a><a href="#method.into" class="anchor">§</a><h4 class="code-header">fn <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html#tymethod.into" class="fn">into</a>(self) -&gt; U</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Calls <code>U::from(self)</code>.</p>
<p>That is, this conversion is whatever the implementation of
<code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt; for U</code> chooses to do.</p>

</div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#767-769">Source</a><a href="#impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;T, U&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html" title="trait core::convert::Into">Into</a>&lt;U&gt; for T<div class="where">where

<p>That is, this conversion is whatever the implementation of
<code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt; for U</code> chooses to do.</p>

</div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#767-769">Source</a><a href="#impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;T, U&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html" title="trait core::convert::Into">Into</a>&lt;U&gt; for T<div class="where">where

<p>That is, this conversion is whatever the implementation of
<code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt; for U</code> chooses to do.</p>

href="index.html">wifi_auto</a></div><h1>Enum <span class="enum">Wifi<wbr>Auto<wbr>Event</span>&nbsp;<button id="copy-path" title="Copy item path to clipboard">Copy item path</button></h1><rustdoc-toolbar></rustdoc-toolbar><span class="sub-heading"><a class="src" href="../../src/device_kit/wifi_auto.rs.html#50-64">Source</a> </span></div><pre class="rust item-decl"><code>pub enum WifiAutoEvent {
    CaptivePortalReady,
    Connecting {
        try_index: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.u8.html">u8</a>,
        try_count: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.u8.html">u8</a>,
    },
    Connected,
    ConnectionFailed,
}</code></pre><details class="toggle top-doc" open><summary class="hideme"><span>Expand description</span></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Events emitted while provisioning or connecting.</p>
</div></details><h2 id="variants" class="variants section-header">Variants<a href="#variants" class="anchor">§</a></h2><div class="variants"><section id="variant.CaptivePortalReady" class="variant"><a href="#variant.CaptivePortalReady" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">CaptivePortalReady</h3></section><div class="docblock"><p>Captive portal is ready and waiting for user configuration.</p>
</div><section id="variant.Connecting" class="variant"><a href="#variant.Connecting" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">Connecting</h3></section><div class="docblock"><p>Attempting to connect to WiFi network.</p>
</div><div class="sub-variant" id="variant.Connecting.fields"><h4>Fields</h4><div class="sub-variant-field"><span id="variant.Connecting.field.try_index" class="section-header"><a href="#variant.Connecting.field.try_index" class="anchor field">§</a><code>try_index: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.u8.html">u8</a></code></span><div class="docblock"><p>Current attempt number (0-based).</p>
</div></div><div class="sub-variant-field"><span id="variant.Connecting.field.try_count" class="section-header"><a href="#variant.Connecting.field.try_count" class="anchor field">§</a><code>try_count: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.u8.html">u8</a></code></span><div class="docblock"><p>Total number of attempts that will be made.</p>
</div></div></div><section id="variant.Connected" class="variant"><a href="#variant.Connected" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">Connected</h3></section><div class="docblock"><p>Successfully connected to WiFi network.</p>
</div><section id="variant.ConnectionFailed" class="variant"><a href="#variant.ConnectionFailed" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">ConnectionFailed</h3></section><div class="docblock"><p>Connection failed after all attempts, device will reset.</p>

</div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#767-769">Source</a><a href="#impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;T, U&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html" title="trait core::convert::Into">Into</a>&lt;U&gt; for T<div class="where">where

<p>That is, this conversion is whatever the implementation of
<code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt; for U</code> chooses to do.</p>

</div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#767-769">Source</a><a href="#impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;T, U&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html" title="trait core::convert::Into">Into</a>&lt;U&gt; for T<div class="where">where

<p>That is, this conversion is whatever the implementation of
<code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt; for U</code> chooses to do.</p>

configuration beyond WiFi credentials.</p>

href="../index.html">wifi_auto</a>::<wbr><a href="index.html">fields</a></div><h1>Struct <span class="struct">Text<wbr>Field</span>&nbsp;<button id="copy-path" title="Copy item path to clipboard">Copy item path</button></h1><rustdoc-toolbar></rustdoc-toolbar><span class="sub-heading"><a class="src" href="../../../src/device_kit/wifi_auto/fields.rs.html#431-436">Source</a> </span></div><pre class="rust item-decl"><code>pub struct TextField&lt;const N: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.usize.html">usize</a>&gt; { <span class="comment">/* private fields */</span> }</code></pre><details class="toggle top-doc" open><summary class="hideme"><span>Expand description</span></summary><div class="docblock"><p>A generic text input field for collecting user input during WiFi provisioning.</p>
<p>Presents a customizable text input box in the captive portal that validates and stores
user-provided text to flash. Can be used for device names, locations, or any other
text-based configuration.</p>
<p>Multiple <code>TextField</code> instances can be created with different labels and field names
to collect various pieces of information during the provisioning process.</p>
<h2 id="example"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#example">§</a>Example</h2>
<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::button::PressedTo;
<span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::flash_array::{FlashArray, FlashArrayStatic, FlashBlock};
<span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::wifi_auto::WifiAuto;
<span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::wifi_auto::fields::{TextField, TextFieldStatic};
<span class="kw">async fn </span>example(
    spawner: embassy_executor::Spawner,
    p: embassy_rp::Peripherals,
) -&gt; <span class="prelude-ty">Result</span>&lt;(), device_kit::Error&gt; {
    <span class="comment">// Set up flash storage
    </span><span class="kw">static </span>FLASH_STATIC: FlashArrayStatic = FlashArray::&lt;<span class="number">2</span>&gt;::new_static();
    <span class="kw">let </span>[wifi_flash, device_name_flash] =
        FlashArray::new(<span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>FLASH_STATIC, p.FLASH)<span class="question-mark">?</span>;

    <span class="comment">// Create device name field (max 32 chars)
    </span><span class="kw">static </span>DEVICE_NAME_STATIC: TextFieldStatic&lt;<span class="number">32</span>&gt; = TextField::new_static();
    <span class="kw">let </span>device_name_field = TextField::new(
        <span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>DEVICE_NAME_STATIC,
        device_name_flash,
        <span class="string">"device_name"</span>,    <span class="comment">// HTML field name
        </span><span class="string">"Device Name"</span>,    <span class="comment">// Label text
        </span><span class="string">"Pico"</span>,           <span class="comment">// Default value
    </span>);

    <span class="comment">// Pass to WifiAuto
    </span><span class="kw">let </span>wifi_auto = WifiAuto::new(
        p.PIN_23,
        p.PIN_25,
        p.PIO0,
        p.PIN_24,
        p.PIN_29,
        p.DMA_CH0,
        wifi_flash,
        p.PIN_13,
        PressedTo::Ground,
        <span class="string">"Pico"</span>,
        [device_name_field],  <span class="comment">// Custom fields array
        </span>spawner,
    )<span class="question-mark">?</span>;

    <span class="comment">// Later, retrieve the device name
    </span><span class="kw">let </span>device_name = device_name_field.text()<span class="question-mark">?</span>.unwrap_or_default();
    <span class="prelude-val">Ok</span>(())
}</code></pre></div></div></details><h2 id="implementations" class="section-header">Implementations<a href="#implementations" class="anchor">§</a></h2><div id="implementations-list"><details class="toggle implementors-toggle" open><summary><section id="impl-TextField%3CN%3E" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="../../../src/device_kit/wifi_auto/fields.rs.html#457-524">Source</a><a href="#impl-TextField%3CN%3E" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;const N: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.usize.html">usize</a>&gt; <a class="struct" href="struct.TextField.html" title="struct device_kit::wifi_auto::fields::TextField">TextField</a>&lt;N&gt;</h3></section></summary><div class="impl-items"><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.new_static" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../../src/device_kit/wifi_auto/fields.rs.html#461-463">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.new_static" class="fn">new_static</a>() -&gt; <a class="struct" href="struct.TextFieldStatic.html" title="struct device_kit::wifi_auto::fields::TextFieldStatic">TextFieldStatic</a>&lt;N&gt;</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Create static resources for <a href="struct.TextField.html" title="struct device_kit::wifi_auto::fields::TextField"><code>TextField</code></a>.</p>
<p>See <a href="struct.TextField.html" title="struct device_kit::wifi_auto::fields::TextField"><code>TextField</code></a> for a complete example.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.new" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../../src/device_kit/wifi_auto/fields.rs.html#477-487">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub fn <a href="#method.new" class="fn">new</a>(
    text_field_static: &amp;'static <a class="struct" href="struct.TextFieldStatic.html" title="struct device_kit::wifi_auto::fields::TextFieldStatic">TextFieldStatic</a>&lt;N&gt;,
    flash: <a class="struct" href="../../flash_array/struct.FlashBlock.html" title="struct device_kit::flash_array::FlashBlock">FlashBlock</a>,
    field_name: &amp;'static <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.str.html">str</a>,
    label: &amp;'static <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.str.html">str</a>,
    default_value: &amp;'static <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.str.html">str</a>,
) -&gt; &amp;'static Self</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Initialize a new text input field.</p>
<h5 id="parameters"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#parameters">§</a>Parameters</h5>
<ul>
<li><code>text_field_static</code>: Static resources for initialization</li>
<li><code>flash</code>: Flash block for persistent storage</li>
<li><code>field_name</code>: HTML form field name (e.g., “device_name”, “location”)</li>
<li><code>label</code>: HTML label text (e.g., “Device Name:”, “Location:”)</li>
<li><code>default_value</code>: Initial value if nothing saved</li>
</ul>
<p>The maximum length is determined by the generic parameter <code>N</code>.</p>
<p>See <a href="struct.TextField.html" title="struct device_kit::wifi_auto::fields::TextField"><code>TextField</code></a> for a complete example.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.text" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../../src/device_kit/wifi_auto/fields.rs.html#508-510">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub fn <a href="#method.text" class="fn">text</a>(&amp;self) -&gt; <a class="type" href="../../type.Result.html" title="type device_kit::Result">Result</a>&lt;<a class="enum" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/option/enum.Option.html" title="enum core::option::Option">Option</a>&lt;String&lt;N&gt;&gt;&gt;</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Load the stored text from flash.</p>
<p>Returns <code>None</code> if no text has been configured yet.</p>
<p>See <a href="struct.TextField.html" title="struct device_kit::wifi_auto::fields::TextField"><code>TextField</code></a> for a complete example.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.set_text" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../../src/device_kit/wifi_auto/fields.rs.html#521-523">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub fn <a href="#method.set_text" class="fn">set_text</a>(&amp;self, text: &amp;String&lt;N&gt;) -&gt; <a class="type" href="../../type.Result.html" title="type device_kit::Result">Result</a>&lt;<a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.unit.html">()</a>&gt;</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Save new text to flash.</p>
<p>This method allows programmatic updates to the field value, such as when
the user modifies configuration via button presses or other UI interactions.</p>
<p>The text must not exceed the maximum length <code>N</code> specified in the type parameter.</p>
<p>Alternatively, you can access the underlying flash block directly for
more control over flash operations.</p>
</div></details></div></details></div><h2 id="trait-implementations" class="section-header">Trait Implementations<a href="#trait-implementations" class="anchor">§</a></h2><div id="trait-implementations-list"><details class="toggle implementors-toggle" open><summary><section id="impl-WifiAutoField-for-TextField%3CN%3E" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="../../../src/device_kit/wifi_auto/fields.rs.html#526-569">Source</a><a href="#impl-WifiAutoField-for-TextField%3CN%3E" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;const N: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.usize.html">usize</a>&gt; </div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#767-769">Source</a><a href="#impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;T, U&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html" title="trait core::convert::Into">Into</a>&lt;U&gt; for T<div class="where">where
    U: <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt;,</div></h3></section></summary><div class="impl-items"><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.into" class="method trait-impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#777">Source</a><a href="#method.into" class="anchor">§</a><h4 class="code-header">fn <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html#tymethod.into" class="fn">into</a>(self) -&gt; U</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Calls <code>U::from(self)</code>.</p>
<p>That is, this conversion is whatever the implementation of
<code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt; for U</code> chooses to do.</p>

</div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#767-769">Source</a><a href="#impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;T, U&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html" title="trait core::convert::Into">Into</a>&lt;U&gt; for T<div class="where">where

<p>That is, this conversion is whatever the implementation of
<code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt; for U</code> chooses to do.</p>

device_<wbr>kit::<wbr>wifi_<wbr>auto::<wbr>fields</a></h2></div></div></nav><div class="sidebar-resizer" title="Drag to resize sidebar"></div><main><div class="width-limiter"><section id="main-content" class="content"><div class="main-heading"><div class="rustdoc-breadcrumbs"><a href="../../index.html">device_kit</a>::<wbr><a href="../index.html">wifi_auto</a>::<wbr><a href="index.html">fields</a></div><h1>Struct <span class="struct">Timezone<wbr>Field</span>&nbsp;<button id="copy-path" title="Copy item path to clipboard">Copy item path</button></h1><rustdoc-toolbar></rustdoc-toolbar><span class="sub-heading"><a class="src" href="../../../src/device_kit/wifi_auto/fields.rs.html#74-76">Source</a> </span></div><pre class="rust item-decl"><code>pub struct TimezoneField { <span class="comment">/* private fields */</span> }</code></pre><details class="toggle top-doc" open><summary class="hideme"><span>Expand description</span></summary><div class="docblock"><p>A timezone selection field for WiFi provisioning.</p>
<p>Allows users to select their timezone from a dropdown during the captive portal
setup. The selected offset (in minutes from UTC) is persisted to flash and can
be retrieved later.</p>
<h2 id="example"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#example">§</a>Example</h2>
<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::button::PressedTo;
<span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::flash_array::{FlashArray, FlashArrayStatic, FlashBlock};
<span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::wifi_auto::WifiAuto;
<span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::wifi_auto::fields::{TimezoneField, TimezoneFieldStatic};
<span class="kw">async fn </span>example(
    spawner: embassy_executor::Spawner,
    p: embassy_rp::Peripherals,
) -&gt; <span class="prelude-ty">Result</span>&lt;(), device_kit::Error&gt; {
    <span class="comment">// Set up flash storage
    </span><span class="kw">static </span>FLASH_STATIC: FlashArrayStatic = FlashArray::&lt;<span class="number">2</span>&gt;::new_static();
    <span class="kw">let </span>[wifi_flash, timezone_flash] =
        FlashArray::new(<span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>FLASH_STATIC, p.FLASH)<span class="question-mark">?</span>;

    <span class="comment">// Create timezone field
    </span><span class="kw">static </span>TIMEZONE_STATIC: TimezoneFieldStatic = TimezoneField::new_static();
    <span class="kw">let </span>timezone_field = TimezoneField::new(<span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>TIMEZONE_STATIC, timezone_flash);

    <span class="comment">// Pass to WifiAuto
    </span><span class="kw">let </span>wifi_auto = WifiAuto::new(
        p.PIN_23,
        p.PIN_25,
        p.PIO0,
        p.PIN_24,
        p.PIN_29,
        p.DMA_CH0,
        wifi_flash,
        p.PIN_13,
        PressedTo::Ground,
        <span class="string">"ClockStation"</span>,
        [timezone_field],  <span class="comment">// Custom fields array
        </span>spawner,
    )<span class="question-mark">?</span>;

    <span class="comment">// Later, retrieve the timezone offset
    </span><span class="kw">let </span>offset_minutes = timezone_field.offset_minutes()<span class="question-mark">?</span>.unwrap_or(<span class="number">0</span>);
    <span class="prelude-val">Ok</span>(())
}</code></pre></div></div></details><h2 id="implementations" class="section-header">Implementations<a href="#implementations" class="anchor">§</a></h2><div id="implementations-list"><details class="toggle implementors-toggle" open><summary><section id="impl-TimezoneField" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="../../../src/device_kit/wifi_auto/fields.rs.html#97-151">Source</a><a href="#impl-TimezoneField" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl <a class="struct" href="struct.TimezoneField.html" title="struct device_kit::wifi_auto::fields::TimezoneField">TimezoneField</a></h3></section></summary><div class="impl-items"><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.new_static" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../../src/device_kit/wifi_auto/fields.rs.html#101-103">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.new_static" class="fn">new_static</a>() -&gt; <a class="struct" href="struct.TimezoneFieldStatic.html" title="struct device_kit::wifi_auto::fields::TimezoneFieldStatic">TimezoneFieldStatic</a></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Create static resources for <a href="struct.TimezoneField.html" title="struct device_kit::wifi_auto::fields::TimezoneField"><code>TimezoneField</code></a>.</p>
<p>See <a href="struct.TimezoneField.html" title="struct device_kit::wifi_auto::fields::TimezoneField"><code>TimezoneField</code></a> for a complete example.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.new" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../../src/device_kit/wifi_auto/fields.rs.html#108-113">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub fn <a href="#method.new" class="fn">new</a>(
    timezone_field_static: &amp;'static <a class="struct" href="struct.TimezoneFieldStatic.html" title="struct device_kit::wifi_auto::fields::TimezoneFieldStatic">TimezoneFieldStatic</a>,
    flash: <a class="struct" href="../../flash_array/struct.FlashBlock.html" title="struct device_kit::flash_array::FlashBlock">FlashBlock</a>,
) -&gt; &amp;'static Self</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Initialize a new timezone field.</p>
<p>See <a href="struct.TimezoneField.html" title="struct device_kit::wifi_auto::fields::TimezoneField"><code>TimezoneField</code></a> for a complete example.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.offset_minutes" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../../src/device_kit/wifi_auto/fields.rs.html#126-128">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub fn <a href="#method.offset_minutes" class="fn">offset_minutes</a>(&amp;self) -&gt; <a class="type" href="../../type.Result.html" title="type device_kit::Result">Result</a>&lt;<a class="enum" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/option/enum.Option.html" title="enum core::option::Option">Option</a>&lt;<a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.i32.html">i32</a>&gt;&gt;</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Load the stored timezone offset in minutes from UTC.</p>
<p>Returns <code>None</code> if no timezone has been configured yet.</p>
<p>See <a href="struct.TimezoneField.html" title="struct device_kit::wifi_auto::fields::TimezoneField"><code>TimezoneField</code></a> for a complete example.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.set_offset_minutes" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../../src/device_kit/wifi_auto/fields.rs.html#139-145">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub fn <a href="#method.set_offset_minutes" class="fn">set_offset_minutes</a>(&amp;self, offset: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.i32.html">i32</a>) -&gt; <a class="type" href="../../type.Result.html" title="type device_kit::Result">Result</a>&lt;<a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.unit.html">()</a>&gt;</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Save a new timezone offset in minutes from UTC to flash.</p>
<p>This method allows programmatic updates to the timezone, such as when
the user adjusts the timezone via button presses or other UI interactions.</p>
<p>Only writes to flash if the value has changed, avoiding unnecessary flash wear.</p>
<p>Alternatively, you can access the underlying flash block directly for
more control over flash operations.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.clear" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../../src/device_kit/wifi_auto/fields.rs.html#148-150">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub fn <a href="#method.clear" class="fn">clear</a>(&amp;self) -&gt; <a class="type" href="../../type.Result.html" title="type device_kit::Result">Result</a>&lt;<a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.unit.html">()</a>&gt;</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Clear the stored timezone offset, returning the field to an unconfigured state.</p>
</div></details></div></details></div><h2 id="trait-implementations" class="section-header">Trait Implementations<a href="#trait-implementations" class="anchor">§</a></h2><div id="trait-implementations-list"><details class="toggle implementors-toggle" open><summary><section id="impl-WifiAutoField-for-TimezoneField" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" id="rustdoc-modnav"><h2><a href="index.html">In device_<wbr>kit::<wbr>wifi_<wbr>auto</a></h2></div></div></nav><div class="sidebar-resizer" title="Drag to resize sidebar"></div><main><div class="width-limiter"><section id="main-content" class="content"><div class="main-heading"><div class="rustdoc-breadcrumbs"><a href="../index.html">device_kit</a>::<wbr><a href="index.html">wifi_auto</a></div><h1>Struct <span class="struct">Wifi</span>&nbsp;<button id="copy-path" title="Copy item path to clipboard">Copy item path</button></h1><rustdoc-toolbar></rustdoc-toolbar><span class="sub-heading"><a class="src" href="../../src/device_kit/wifi_auto/stack.rs.html#250-254">Source</a> </span></div><pre class="rust item-decl"><code>pub struct Wifi { <span class="comment">/* private fields */</span> }</code></pre><details class="toggle top-doc" open><summary class="hideme"><span>Expand description</span></summary><div class="docblock"><p>A device abstraction that manages WiFi connectivity and network stack in both captive portal and client modes.</p>
<p>See the <a href="../wifi/index.html" title="mod device_kit::wifi">module-level documentation</a> for usage examples.</p>
</div></details><h2 id="implementations" class="section-header">Implementations<a href="#implementations" class="anchor">§</a></h2><div id="implementations-list"><details class="toggle implementors-toggle" open><summary><section id="impl-Wifi" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/wifi_auto/stack.rs.html#256-471">Source</a><a href="#impl-Wifi" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl <a class="struct" href="struct.Wifi.html" title="struct device_kit::wifi_auto::Wifi">Wifi</a></h3></section></summary><div class="impl-items"><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.new_static" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/wifi_auto/stack.rs.html#263-269">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.new_static" class="fn">new_static</a>() -&gt; <a class="struct" href="struct.WifiStatic.html" title="struct device_kit::wifi_auto::WifiStatic">WifiStatic</a></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Create WiFi resources (events + storage).</p>
<p>This must be called once to create a static <code>WifiStatic</code> that will be passed to <a href="struct.Wifi.html#method.new" title="associated function device_kit::wifi_auto::Wifi::new"><code>Wifi::new</code></a>.</p>
<p>See the <a href="../wifi/index.html" title="mod device_kit::wifi">module-level documentation</a> for usage examples.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.wait_for_stack" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/wifi_auto/stack.rs.html#279-281">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub async fn <a href="#method.wait_for_stack" class="fn">wait_for_stack</a>(&amp;self) -&gt; &amp;'static Stack&lt;'static&gt;</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Wait for the network stack to be ready and return a reference to it.</p>
<p>This provides access to the Embassy network stack for TCP/UDP operations.
The stack will be configured differently depending on the WiFi mode:</p>
<ul>
<li>In captive portal mode: static IP 192.168.4.1</li>
<li>In client mode: DHCP-assigned IP</li>
</ul>
<p>See the <a href="../wifi/index.html" title="mod device_kit::wifi">module-level documentation</a> for usage examples.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.wait_for_wifi_event" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/wifi_auto/stack.rs.html#290-292">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub async fn <a href="#method.wait_for_wifi_event" class="fn">wait_for_wifi_event</a>(&amp;self) -&gt; <a class="enum" href="enum.WifiEvent.html" title="enum device_kit::wifi_auto::WifiEvent">WifiEvent</a></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Wait for and return the next WiFi event.</p>
<p>This will block until the next <a href="enum.WifiEvent.html" title="enum device_kit::wifi_auto::WifiEvent"><code>WifiEvent</code></a> occurs, such as:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="enum.WifiEvent.html#variant.CaptivePortalReady" title="variant device_kit::wifi_auto::WifiEvent::CaptivePortalReady"><code>WifiEvent::CaptivePortalReady</code></a> when captive portal mode is initialized</li>
<li><a href="enum.WifiEvent.html#variant.ClientReady" title="variant device_kit::wifi_auto::WifiEvent::ClientReady"><code>WifiEvent::ClientReady</code></a> when connected to WiFi and DHCP is configured</li>
</ul>
<p>See the <a href="../wifi/index.html" title="mod device_kit::wifi">module-level documentation</a> for usage examples.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.new" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/wifi_auto/stack.rs.html#312-335">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub fn <a href="#method.new" class="fn">new</a>&lt;PIO: <a class="trait" href="trait.WifiPio.html" title="trait device_kit::wifi_auto::WifiPio">WifiPio</a>&gt;(
    wifi_static: &amp;'static <a class="struct" href="struct.WifiStatic.html" title="struct device_kit::wifi_auto::WifiStatic">WifiStatic</a>,
    pin_23: Peri&lt;'static, PIN_23&gt;,
    pin_25: Peri&lt;'static, PIN_25&gt;,
    pio: Peri&lt;'static, PIO&gt;,
    pin_24: Peri&lt;'static, PIN_24&gt;,
    pin_29: Peri&lt;'static, PIN_29&gt;,
    dma_ch0: Peri&lt;'static, DMA_CH0&gt;,
    credential_store: <a class="struct" href="../flash_array/struct.FlashBlock.html" title="struct device_kit::flash_array::FlashBlock">FlashBlock</a>,
    spawner: Spawner,
) -&gt; &amp;'static Self</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Create a new WiFi device and spawn its background task.</p>
<p>This initializes the WiFi hardware and spawns tasks to manage the WiFi connection
and network stack. Returns a static reference to the WiFi handle.</p>
<h5 id="arguments"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#arguments">§</a>Arguments</h5>
<ul>
<li><code>resources</code> - Static WiFi resources created with <a href="struct.Wifi.html#method.new_static" title="associated function device_kit::wifi_auto::Wifi::new_static"><code>Wifi::new_static</code></a></li>
<li><code>pin_23</code> - WiFi chip power pin (GPIO 23)</li>
<li><code>pin_25</code> - WiFi chip chip select pin (GPIO 25)</li>
<li><code>pio</code> - PIO peripheral for WiFi communication</li>
<li><code>pin_24</code> - WiFi chip clock pin (GPIO 24)</li>
<li><code>pin_29</code> - WiFi chip data pin (GPIO 29)</li>
<li><code>dma_ch0</code> - DMA channel for WiFi SPI communication</li>
<li><code>credential_store</code> - Flash block reserved for WiFi credentials</li>
<li><code>spawner</code> - Embassy task spawner</li>
</ul>
<p>See the <a href="../wifi/index.html" title="mod device_kit::wifi">module-level documentation</a> for usage examples.</p>
</div></details><section id="method.new_with_captive_portal_ssid" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/wifi_auto/stack.rs.html#337-379">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub fn <a href="#method.new_with_captive_portal_ssid" class="fn">new_with_captive_portal_ssid</a>&lt;PIO: <a class="trait" href="trait.WifiPio.html" title="trait device_kit::wifi_auto::WifiPio">WifiPio</a>&gt;(

    dma_ch0: Peri&lt;'static, DMA_CH0&gt;,
    credential_store: <a class="struct" href="../flash_array/struct.FlashBlock.html" title="struct device_kit::flash_array::FlashBlock">FlashBlock</a>,
    captive_portal_ssid: &amp;'static <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.str.html">str</a>,
    spawner: Spawner,
) -&gt; &amp;'static Self</h4></section><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.switch_to_client_mode" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/wifi_auto/stack.rs.html#383-391">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub async fn <a href="#method.switch_to_client_mode" class="fn">switch_to_client_mode</a>(

This is called after collecting credentials in captive portal mode</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.persist_credentials" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/wifi_auto/stack.rs.html#414-420">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub fn <a href="#method.persist_credentials" class="fn">persist_credentials</a>(

id="rustdoc-modnav"><h2><a href="index.html">In device_<wbr>kit::<wbr>wifi_<wbr>auto</a></h2></div></div></nav><div class="sidebar-resizer" title="Drag to resize sidebar"></div><main><div class="width-limiter"><section id="main-content" class="content"><div class="main-heading"><div class="rustdoc-breadcrumbs"><a href="../index.html">device_kit</a>::<wbr><a href="index.html">wifi_auto</a></div><h1>Struct <span class="struct">Wifi<wbr>Auto</span>&nbsp;<button id="copy-path" title="Copy item path to clipboard">Copy item path</button></h1><rustdoc-toolbar></rustdoc-toolbar><span class="sub-heading"><a class="src" href="../../src/device_kit/wifi_auto.rs.html#173-180">Source</a> </span></div><pre class="rust item-decl"><code>pub struct WifiAuto { <span class="comment">/* private fields */</span> }</code></pre><details class="toggle top-doc" open><summary class="hideme"><span>Expand description</span></summary><div class="docblock"><p>WiFi auto-provisioning with captive portal and custom configuration fields.</p>
<p>Manages WiFi connectivity with automatic fallback to a captive portal when credentials
are missing or invalid. Supports collecting additional configuration (e.g., timezone,
device name) through custom <a href="trait.WifiAutoField.html" title="trait device_kit::wifi_auto::WifiAutoField"><code>WifiAutoField</code></a> implementations.</p>
<h2 id="features"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#features">§</a>Features</h2>
<ul>
<li>Automatic captive portal on first boot or failed connections</li>
<li>Customizable configuration fields beyond WiFi credentials</li>
<li>Button-triggered reconfiguration</li>
<li>Event-driven UI updates via <a href="struct.WifiAuto.html#method.connect" title="method device_kit::wifi_auto::WifiAuto::connect"><code>connect</code></a></li>
</ul>
<p>Supports any PIO instance that implements <a href="trait.WifiPio.html" title="trait device_kit::wifi_auto::WifiPio"><code>WifiPio</code></a>, including <code>PIO0</code> and <code>PIO1</code>
(and <code>PIO2</code> on supported boards).</p>
<h2 id="example"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#example">§</a>Example</h2><h2 id="example-1"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#example-1">§</a>Example</h2>
<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::button::PressedTo;
<span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::flash_array::{FlashArray, FlashArrayStatic};
<span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::wifi_auto::{WifiAuto, WifiAutoEvent};
<span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::wifi_auto::fields::{TimezoneField, TimezoneFieldStatic};
<span class="kw">async fn </span>example(
    spawner: embassy_executor::Spawner,
    p: embassy_rp::Peripherals,
) -&gt; <span class="prelude-ty">Result</span>&lt;(), device_kit::Error&gt; {
    <span class="comment">// Set up flash storage for WiFi credentials and timezone
    </span><span class="kw">static </span>FLASH_STATIC: FlashArrayStatic = FlashArray::&lt;<span class="number">2</span>&gt;::new_static();
    <span class="kw">let </span>[wifi_flash, timezone_flash] =
        FlashArray::new(<span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>FLASH_STATIC, p.FLASH)<span class="question-mark">?</span>;

    <span class="comment">// Create a timezone field to collect during provisioning
    </span><span class="kw">static </span>TIMEZONE_STATIC: TimezoneFieldStatic = TimezoneField::new_static();
    <span class="kw">let </span>timezone_field = TimezoneField::new(<span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>TIMEZONE_STATIC, timezone_flash);

    <span class="comment">// Initialize WifiAuto with the custom field
    </span><span class="kw">let </span>wifi_auto = WifiAuto::new(
        p.PIN_23,               <span class="comment">// CYW43 power
        </span>p.PIN_25,               <span class="comment">// CYW43 chip select
        </span>p.PIO0,                 <span class="comment">// CYW43 PIO interface
        </span>p.PIN_24,               <span class="comment">// CYW43 clock
        </span>p.PIN_29,               <span class="comment">// CYW43 data
        </span>p.DMA_CH0,              <span class="comment">// CYW43 DMA
        </span>wifi_flash,             <span class="comment">// Flash for WiFi credentials
        </span>p.PIN_13,               <span class="comment">// Button for forced reconfiguration
        </span>PressedTo::Ground,      <span class="comment">// Button wiring
        </span><span class="string">"PicoAccess"</span>,           <span class="comment">// Captive-portal SSID for provisioning
        </span>[timezone_field],       <span class="comment">// Array of custom fields
        </span>spawner,
    )<span class="question-mark">?</span>;

    <span class="comment">// Connect with UI feedback (blocks until connected)
    // Note: If capturing variables from outer scope, create a reference first:
    //   let display_ref = &amp;display;
    // Then use display_ref inside the closure.
    </span><span class="kw">let </span>(stack, button) = wifi_auto
        .connect(spawner, |event| <span class="kw">async move </span>{
            <span class="kw">match </span>event {
                WifiAutoEvent::CaptivePortalReady =&gt; {
                    <span class="macro">defmt::info!</span>(<span class="string">"Captive portal ready - connect to WiFi network"</span>);
                }
                WifiAutoEvent::Connecting { try_index, try_count } =&gt; {
                    <span class="macro">defmt::info!</span>(<span class="string">"Connecting to WiFi (attempt {} of {})..."</span>, try_index + <span class="number">1</span>, try_count);
                }
                WifiAutoEvent::Connected =&gt; {
                    <span class="macro">defmt::info!</span>(<span class="string">"WiFi connected successfully!"</span>);
                }
                WifiAutoEvent::ConnectionFailed =&gt; {
                    <span class="macro">defmt::info!</span>(<span class="string">"WiFi connection failed - device will reset"</span>);
                }
            }
        })
        .<span class="kw">await</span><span class="question-mark">?</span>;

    <span class="comment">// Now connected - retrieve timezone configuration
    </span><span class="kw">let </span>offset_minutes = timezone_field.offset_minutes()<span class="question-mark">?</span>.unwrap_or(<span class="number">0</span>);

    <span class="comment">// Use stack for internet access and button for user interactions
    // Example: fetch NTP time, make HTTP requests, etc.
    </span><span class="prelude-val">Ok</span>(())
}</code></pre></div></div></details><h2 id="implementations" class="section-header">Implementations<a href="#implementations" class="anchor">§</a></h2><div id="implementations-list"><details class="toggle implementors-toggle" open><summary><section id="impl-WifiAuto" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/wifi_auto.rs.html#213-532">Source</a><a href="#impl-WifiAuto" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl <a class="struct" href="struct.WifiAuto.html" title="struct device_kit::wifi_auto::WifiAuto">WifiAuto</a></h3></section></summary><div class="impl-items"><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.new_static" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/wifi_auto.rs.html#218-220">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub const fn <a href="#method.new_static" class="fn">new_static</a>() -&gt; <a class="struct" href="struct.WifiAutoStatic.html" title="struct device_kit::wifi_auto::WifiAutoStatic">WifiAutoStatic</a></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Create static resources for <a href="struct.WifiAuto.html" title="struct device_kit::wifi_auto::WifiAuto"><code>WifiAuto</code></a>.</p>
<p>See <a href="struct.WifiAuto.html" title="struct device_kit::wifi_auto::WifiAuto"><code>WifiAuto</code></a> for a complete example.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.new" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/wifi_auto.rs.html#226-316">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub fn <a href="#method.new" class="fn">new</a>&lt;const N: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.usize.html">usize</a>, PIO: <a class="trait" href="trait.WifiPio.html" title="trait device_kit::wifi_auto::WifiPio">WifiPio</a>&gt;(

) -&gt; <a class="type" href="../type.Result.html" title="type device_kit::Result">Result</a>&lt;&amp;'static Self&gt;</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Initialize WiFi auto-provisioning with custom configuration fields.</p>
<p>See <a href="struct.WifiAuto.html" title="struct device_kit::wifi_auto::WifiAuto"><code>WifiAuto</code></a> for a complete example.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.wifi" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/wifi_auto.rs.html#325-327">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub fn <a href="#method.wifi" class="fn">wifi</a>(&amp;self) -&gt; &amp;'static <a class="struct" href="struct.Wifi.html" title="struct device_kit::wifi_auto::Wifi">Wifi</a></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Return the underlying WiFi handle for advanced operations such as clearing
credentials. Avoid waiting on WiFi events while <a href="struct.WifiAuto.html" title="struct device_kit::wifi_auto::WifiAuto"><code>WifiAuto</code></a> is running, as it
already owns the event stream.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.connect" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/wifi_auto.rs.html#395-420">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">pub async fn <a href="#method.connect" class="fn">connect</a>&lt;Fut, F&gt;(
    &amp;self,
    spawner: Spawner,
    on_event: F,
) -&gt; <a class="type" href="../type.Result.html" title="type device_kit::Result">Result</a>&lt;(&amp;'static Stack&lt;'static&gt;, <a class="struct" href="../button/struct.Button.html" title="struct device_kit::button::Button">Button</a>&lt;'static&gt;)&gt;<div class="where">where
    F: <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/ops/function/trait.FnMut.html" title="trait core::ops::function::FnMut">FnMut</a>(<a class="enum" href="enum.WifiAutoEvent.html" title="enum device_kit::wifi_auto::WifiAutoEvent">WifiAutoEvent</a>) -&gt; Fut,
    Fut: <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/future/future/trait.Future.html" title="trait core::future::future::Future">Future</a>&lt;Output = <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.unit.html">()</a>&gt;,</div></h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Ensures WiFi connection with UI callback for event-driven status updates.</p>
<p>Automatically monitors connection events and awaits the provided callback for
each event. The callback can be either synchronous (no <code>.await</code> calls) or
asynchronous (with <code>.await</code> calls for async operations like updating displays).</p>
<p>The future resolves once WiFi connectivity is established and returns access to
the network stack plus the reconfiguration button.</p>
<h5 id="examples"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#examples">§</a>Examples</h5>
<p>Synchronous callback (no <code>.await</code> calls):</p>

<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::{wifi_auto::{WifiAuto,WifiAutoEvent}, <span class="prelude-ty">Result</span>};
<span class="kw">async fn </span>connect_sync(wifi_auto: <span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>WifiAuto, spawner: embassy_executor::Spawner) -&gt; <span class="prelude-ty">Result</span>&lt;()&gt; {
    wifi_auto.connect(spawner, |event| <span class="kw">async move </span>{
        <span class="macro">defmt::info!</span>(<span class="string">"Event: {:?}"</span>, event);
    }).<span class="kw">await</span><span class="question-mark">?</span>;
    <span class="prelude-val">Ok</span>(())
}</code></pre></div>
<p>Asynchronous callback (with <code>.await</code> calls):</p>

<div class="example-wrap"><pre class="rust rust-example-rendered"><code><span class="kw">use </span>device_kit::{wifi_auto::{WifiAuto, WifiAutoEvent}, <span class="prelude-ty">Result</span>};
<span class="kw">async fn </span>update_display(event: WifiAutoEvent) {
    <span class="comment">// Update UI asynchronously (placeholder)
    </span>core::future::ready(()).<span class="kw">await</span>;
    <span class="macro">defmt::info!</span>(<span class="string">"Updated display: {:?}"</span>, event);
}

<span class="kw">async fn </span>connect_async(
    wifi_auto: <span class="kw-2">&amp;</span>WifiAuto,
    spawner: embassy_executor::Spawner,
) -&gt; <span class="prelude-ty">Result</span>&lt;()&gt; {
    wifi_auto.connect(spawner, |event| <span class="kw">async move </span>{
        update_display(event).<span class="kw">await</span>;
    }).<span class="kw">await</span><span class="question-mark">?</span>;
    <span class="prelude-val">Ok</span>(())
}</code></pre></div></div></details></div></details></div><h2 id="synthetic-implementations" class="section-header">Auto Trait Implementations<a href="#synthetic-implementations" </div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#767-769">Source</a><a href="#impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;T, U&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html" title="trait core::convert::Into">Into</a>&lt;U&gt; for T<div class="where">where
    U: <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt;,</div></h3></section></summary><div class="impl-items"><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.into" class="method trait-impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#777">Source</a><a href="#method.into" class="anchor">§</a><h4 class="code-header">fn <a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html#tymethod.into" class="fn">into</a>(self) -&gt; U</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Calls <code>U::from(self)</code>.</p>
<p>That is, this conversion is whatever the implementation of
<code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt; for U</code> chooses to do.</p>

<p>That is, this conversion is whatever the implementation of

</div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#767-769">Source</a><a href="#impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;T, U&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html" title="trait core::convert::Into">Into</a>&lt;U&gt; for T<div class="where">where

</div></details></div></details><details class="toggle implementors-toggle"><summary><section id="impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/src/core/convert/mod.rs.html#767-769">Source</a><a href="#impl-Into%3CU%3E-for-T" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;T, U&gt; <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.Into.html" title="trait core::convert::Into">Into</a>&lt;U&gt; for T<div class="where">where

<p>That is, this conversion is whatever the implementation of
<code><a href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/convert/trait.From.html" title="trait core::convert::From">From</a>&lt;T&gt; for U</code> chooses to do.</p>
