</span></div><pre class="rust item-decl"><code>pub trait WifiAutoField: <a class="trait" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/marker/trait.Sync.html" title="trait core::marker::Sync">Sync</a> {
    // Required methods
    fn <a href="#tymethod.render" class="fn">render</a>(&amp;self, page: &amp;mut String&lt;16384&gt;) -&gt; <a class="type" href="../type.Result.html" title="type device_kit::Result">Result</a>&lt;<a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.unit.html">()</a>&gt;;
<span class="item-spacer"></span>    fn <a href="#tymethod.parse" class="fn">parse</a>(&amp;self, form: &amp;FormData&lt;'_&gt;) -&gt; <a class="type" href="../type.Result.html" title="type device_kit::Result">Result</a>&lt;<a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.unit.html">()</a>&gt;;

    // Provided method
    fn <a href="#method.is_satisfied" class="fn">is_satisfied</a>(&amp;self) -&gt; <a class="type" href="../type.Result.html" title="type device_kit::Result">Result</a>&lt;<a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.bool.html">bool</a>&gt; { ... }
}</code></pre><details class="toggle top-doc" open><summary class="hideme"><span>Expand description</span></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Trait for custom configuration fields in the WiFi provisioning portal.</p>
<p>Implement this trait to collect additional configuration beyond WiFi credentials
during the captive portal setup. Fields must be <code>Sync</code> since they’re shared across
async tasks.</p>
<p>See <a href="fields/struct.TimezoneField.html" title="struct device_kit::wifi_auto::fields::TimezoneField"><code>TimezoneField</code></a> and
<a href="fields/struct.TextField.html" title="struct device_kit::wifi_auto::fields::TextField"><code>TextField</code></a> for complete
implementation examples.</p>
<h2 id="methods"><a class="doc-anchor" href="#methods">§</a>Methods</h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="trait.WifiAutoField.html#tymethod.render"><code>render</code></a>: Generate HTML form elements for the captive portal</li>
<li><a href="trait.WifiAutoField.html#tymethod.parse"><code>parse</code></a>: Parse and save submitted form data</li>
<li><a href="trait.WifiAutoField.html#method.is_satisfied"><code>is_satisfied</code></a>: Check if field has valid configuration</li>
</ul>
</div></details><h2 id="required-methods" class="section-header">Required Methods<a href="#required-methods" class="anchor">§</a></h2><div class="methods"><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="tymethod.render" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/wifi_auto/portal.rs.html#41">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">fn <a href="#tymethod.render" class="fn">render</a>(&amp;self, page: &amp;mut String&lt;16384&gt;) -&gt; <a class="type" href="../type.Result.html" title="type device_kit::Result">Result</a>&lt;<a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.unit.html">()</a>&gt;</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Render HTML form elements for this field.</p>
<p>Append form elements (labels, inputs, selects, etc.) to the <code>page</code> buffer.
This is called when generating the captive portal page.</p>
<p>See <a href="fields/struct.TimezoneField.html" title="struct device_kit::wifi_auto::fields::TimezoneField"><code>TimezoneField</code></a> and
<a href="fields/struct.TextField.html" title="struct device_kit::wifi_auto::fields::TextField"><code>TextField</code></a> for examples.</p>
</div></details><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="tymethod.parse" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/wifi_auto/portal.rs.html#50">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">fn <a href="#tymethod.parse" class="fn">parse</a>(&amp;self, form: &amp;FormData&lt;'_&gt;) -&gt; <a class="type" href="../type.Result.html" title="type device_kit::Result">Result</a>&lt;<a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.unit.html">()</a>&gt;</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Parse and save form data submitted by the user.</p>
<p>Extract values from the <code>form</code> data and persist them (typically to flash).
Return an error if validation fails.</p>
<p>See <a href="fields/struct.TimezoneField.html" title="struct device_kit::wifi_auto::fields::TimezoneField"><code>TimezoneField</code></a> and
<a href="fields/struct.TextField.html" title="struct device_kit::wifi_auto::fields::TextField"><code>TextField</code></a> for examples.</p>
</div></details></div><h2 id="provided-methods" class="section-header">Provided Methods<a href="#provided-methods" class="anchor">§</a></h2><div class="methods"><details class="toggle method-toggle" open><summary><section id="method.is_satisfied" class="method"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/wifi_auto/portal.rs.html#60-62">Source</a><h4 class="code-header">fn <a href="#method.is_satisfied" class="fn">is_satisfied</a>(&amp;self) -&gt; <a class="type" href="../type.Result.html" title="type device_kit::Result">Result</a>&lt;<a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.bool.html">bool</a>&gt;</h4></section></summary><div class="docblock"><p>Check if this field has valid configuration.</p>
<p>Returns <code>true</code> if the field has been configured (default implementation always
returns <code>true</code>). If <code>false</code>, the captive portal will be shown even if WiFi
credentials exist.</p>
<p>See <a href="fields/struct.TimezoneField.html" title="struct device_kit::wifi_auto::fields::TimezoneField"><code>TimezoneField</code></a> and
<a href="fields/struct.TextField.html" title="struct device_kit::wifi_auto::fields::TextField"><code>TextField</code></a> for examples.</p>
</div></details></div><h2 id="implementors" class="section-header">Implementors<a href="#implementors" class="anchor">§</a></h2><div id="implementors-list"><section id="impl-WifiAutoField-for-TimezoneField" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/wifi_auto/fields.rs.html#153-189">Source</a><a href="#impl-WifiAutoField-for-TimezoneField" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl <a class="trait" href="trait.WifiAutoField.html" title="trait device_kit::wifi_auto::WifiAutoField">WifiAutoField</a> for <a class="struct" href="fields/struct.TimezoneField.html" title="struct device_kit::wifi_auto::fields::TimezoneField">TimezoneField</a></h3></section><section id="impl-WifiAutoField-for-TextField%3CN%3E" class="impl"><a class="src rightside" href="../../src/device_kit/wifi_auto/fields.rs.html#526-569">Source</a><a href="#impl-WifiAutoField-for-TextField%3CN%3E" class="anchor">§</a><h3 class="code-header">impl&lt;const N: <a class="primitive" href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.92.0/core/primitive.usize.html">usize</a>&gt; <a class="trait" href="trait.WifiAutoField.html" title="trait device_kit::wifi_auto::WifiAutoField">WifiAutoField</a> for <a class="struct" href="fields/struct.TextField.html" title="struct device_kit::wifi_auto::fields::TextField">TextField</a>&lt;N&gt;</h3></section></div><script src="../../trait.impl/device_kit/wifi_auto/portal/trait.WifiAutoField.js" async></script></section></div></main></body></html>
